INSERT INTO organizations VALUES(23,'The Nature Conservancy - Monterey Bay Area','N/A (regional office likely in Monterey or Santa Cruz area)','https://www.nature.org/en-us/get-involved/how-we-work/our-impact/places-we-protect/california/central-california/monterey-bay/','N/A (part of large global NGO, local team size unknown)','N/A (part of large global NGO, local budget unknown, but involved in significant projects)','Working with partners in the Monterey Bay area on coastal resilience, natural infrastructure, and multi-benefit adaptation solutions to address climate change impacts like sea level rise and human development.','Their collaborative approach to ''multi-benefit adaptation solutions'' and developing a ''blueprint for nature-based adaptation'' requires navigating ''cross-sector complexity'' and building ''aligned outcomes'' with diverse partners. Leslie''s expertise in ''stuck partnerships'' and ''truth-telling gaps'' could be valuable in fostering effective collaboration for large-scale environmental projects.','identified','cons','strong','inferred','The Nature Conservancy is actively working with a ''suite of partners'' on complex projects like the Pacific Coast Highway Natural Infrastructure Pilot Project and creating a ''blueprint for nature-based adaptation for Monterey Bay''. This level of multi-stakeholder engagement inherently involves ''stuck partnerships'' and ''alignment issues'' in coordinating diverse interests and goals for regional climate resilience.',36.60020000000000095,-121.8947000000000002,NULL,'2026-03-26 06:31:17','2026-03-26 06:31:17');
INSERT INTO organizations VALUES(24,'Moss Landing Marine Laboratories (MLML)','8272 Moss Landing Rd, Moss Landing, CA 95039','https://www.mlml.calstate.edu/','100','N/A (consortium of CSU campuses, significant public funding)','Providing hands-on, field-oriented marine science education and research through a consortium of California State Universities. Focus areas include oceanography, marine biology, and applied topics relevant to state, federal, and international governance.','As a consortium, MLML likely faces ''cross-sector complexity'' and ''alignment issues'' among its constituent universities, as well as ''decision-making bottlenecks'' related to shared resources and strategic direction. Their emphasis on applied research and training the next generation of scientists suggests a need for strong leadership in translating research into real-world solutions and scaling educational programs.','identified','sci','strong','inferred','MLML is a consortium of seven California State Universities, offering a thesis-based master''s degree. The nature of a consortium implies ongoing ''alignment issues'' and ''cross-sector complexity'' in coordinating research, education, and funding across multiple academic institutions. The expansion of the NOAA-relevant STEM disciplines and social sciences via CCME-II program suggests ''scaling culture'' during growth.',36.80490000000000351,-121.7890000000000014,NULL,'2026-03-26 06:31:23','2026-03-26 06:31:23');
INSERT INTO organizations VALUES(25,'Monterey Bay National Marine Sanctuary (NOAA)','99 Pacific Street, Monterey, CA 93940','https://montereybay.noaa.gov/','N/A (federal agency, local staff size unknown)','N/A (federal agency, likely significant but complex budget)','Protecting incredible marine ecosystems and cultural/maritime resources while promoting sustainable use. Focus on research, conservation, learning, tourism, and recreation across diverse habitats like kelp forests, seamounts, and deep-sea canyons.','As a large, federally protected area, the MBNMS likely deals with ''cross-sector complexity'' in balancing conservation with commercial and recreational activities, and ''multi-stakeholder'' engagement for policy and management. Leslie''s expertise in ''organizational alignment'' and ''decision-making bottlenecks'' could help optimize their initiatives in microplastics research, kelp action plans, and broader ecosystem management.','identified','gov','supplemental','inferred','As a large federal marine protected area, the MBNMS navigates balancing conservation with sustainable use, involving ''multi-stakeholder'' interests (recreational, commercial, research). This inherently creates ''cross-sector complexity'' and potential ''decision-making bottlenecks'' in policy implementation and resource management. Their active programs like ''Following Microplastics from Shore to Sanctuary'' and ''Iconic Kelp Action Plan'' require strong coordination and strategic direction.',36.60269999999999869,-121.8974999999999938,NULL,'2026-03-26 06:31:29','2026-03-26 06:31:29');
INSERT INTO organizations VALUES(26,'California State University Monterey Bay (CSUMB) - Department of Marine Science','100 Campus Center, Seaside, CA 93955 (approx. 5 miles from Monterey)','https://csumb.edu/marinescience/','N/A (part of larger university, department size unknown)','N/A (part of larger university, department budget unknown)','Providing immersive research, fieldwork, and faculty mentorship in marine science. Students study ocean ecosystems while gaining experience in diving, data analysis, and conservation, leveraging the Monterey Bay National Marine Sanctuary as a learning environment.','CSUMB''s Marine Science department, especially with its close ties to the Monterey Bay National Marine Sanctuary and applied research focus, could benefit from Leslie''s expertise in ''alignment issues'' and ''scaling culture.'' As an academic department, there may be challenges in integrating research with practical conservation outcomes, fostering cross-disciplinary partnerships, and managing growth in programs and student engagement.','identified','sci','supplemental','inferred','The department emphasizes ''immersive research, fieldwork, and faculty mentorship'' and states it''s ''being in the field as much as in the classroom''. While not explicitly stating a challenge, this hands-on, expansive approach for students and faculty in a dynamic environment like the Monterey Bay National Marine Sanctuary implies ongoing ''organizational alignment'' needs between academic rigor and practical application, as well as ''scaling culture'' for growing student involvement in research.',36.65079999999999671,-121.7954000000000007,NULL,'2026-03-26 06:31:30','2026-03-26 06:31:30');
INSERT INTO organizations VALUES(27,'Monterey Bay Fisheries Trust','P.O. Box 7255, Santa Cruz, CA 95061 (operates in Monterey Bay area)','https://www.montereybayfisheriestrust.org/','10-20','N/A (non-profit, likely grant and donor funded, specific budget unknown)','Supporting the local fishing community and promoting locally-harvested sustainable seafood from Monterey Bay. Connects fishermen, markets, grocery stores, CSFs, and restaurants.','This trust''s mission to support the local fishing community and foster sustainable seafood practices involves complex ''cross-sector partnerships'' (fishermen, markets, restaurants) and addressing ''alignment issues'' within the seafood supply chain. Leslie could assist in optimizing these partnerships, scaling their impact, and navigating strategic growth challenges in the blue economy.','identified','food','supplemental','inferred','The trust focuses on ''finding locally-harvested, sustainable seafood'' and supporting ''the local fishing community'' by connecting various stakeholders. This involves managing ''cross-sector complexity'' and building ''aligned outcomes'' among fishermen, markets, and consumers. The 2020 guide to finding local seafood and the expansion of the ''Best Choice Restaurant Program'' in 2026 suggests strategic growth and partnership refinement.',36.97409999999999997,-122.0293000000000063,NULL,'2026-03-26 06:31:35','2026-03-26 06:31:35');
INSERT INTO organizations VALUES(29,'Vancouver Fraser Port Authority','Vancouver, BC','https://www.portvancouver.com/','600','$150M','Stewards the Port of Vancouver, enabling Canada''s trade, protecting the environment, and considering local communities, with a vision to be the world''s most sustainable port.','A major public-private entity with significant ongoing sustainability, environmental, and infrastructure projects, requiring leadership in strategic planning, multi-stakeholder alignment, and community engagement for its ''world''s most sustainable port'' vision.','identified','infra','high','confirmed','Actively pursuing a ''world''s most sustainable port'' vision and extensive sustainability initiatives, involving strategic transitions, environmental protection, and community consideration.',49.2826999999999984,-123.1206999999999994,NULL,'2026-03-26 06:43:06','2026-03-26 06:43:06');
INSERT INTO organizations VALUES(30,'Vancouver Pile Driving Ltd. (VanPile)','North Vancouver, BC','https://www.vanpile.com/','200','$75M','Designs and constructs durable marine facilities, including wharves, docks, and waterfront infrastructure for complex coastal projects across Western Canada.','Engaged in complex, large-scale marine infrastructure projects, likely encountering cross-sector complexity, partnership challenges, and project management bottlenecks during expansion and major project execution.','identified','infra','strong','inferred','Involvement in significant marine construction projects like the Vancouver Airport Fuel Delivery Project and G3 Terminal Marine Structures implies managing complex partnerships and operational scaling.',49.31929999999999837,-123.0763000000000033,NULL,'2026-03-26 06:43:08','2026-03-26 06:43:08');
INSERT INTO organizations VALUES(31,'Cellula Robotics Ltd.','Port Coquitlam, BC','https://cellula.com/','90','$35M','Specializes in the turnkey design and production of subsea robotic systems, including Autonomous Underwater Vehicles (AUVs) for applications in subsea security, mineral, and energy exploration.','A growing marine technology company with international operations, likely navigating hypergrowth, strategic expansion, and continuous innovation in a competitive deep technology space.','identified','sci','high','inferred','Described as a ''world-leading, privately owned company'' with ''over 80 skilled professionals across Canada, US and the UK'', suggesting scaling and global expansion challenges.',49.26299999999999813,-122.7750000000000056,NULL,'2026-03-26 06:43:15','2026-03-26 06:43:15');
INSERT INTO organizations VALUES(32,'Alaska Conservation Foundation','Anchorage, AK','https://alaskaconservation.org/','Medium (9 employees in 2017, but significant grantmaking capacity and network coordination)','Assets $10.4 million (2017). Has awarded over $59 million in grants since 1980. Annual revenues around $2.5 million (2017).','Protects Alaska''s unique landscapes and ways of life by supporting conservation leaders, organizations, and initiatives. Focuses on sustaining wildlife, coastlines, and mountains from climate change impacts, limiting industrial fishing impacts, regulating international shipping, and mitigating ocean contaminants. [cite: 2 (previous search), 14, 28, 36]','As a prominent funder and network orchestrator for Alaskan conservation efforts, ACF regularly navigates complex partnerships and alignment issues among its diverse grantees and stakeholders. Leslie''s expertise in ''stuck partnerships'' and ''alignment issues'' would be highly valuable in strengthening their collaborative impact and organizational capacity building.','identified','cons','high','confirmed','Leadership transition to Michael Barber as President and CEO, who started as a Program Officer in 2013. Actively involved in ''Organizational capacity grants'' to promote leadership within conservation organizations. Hosts ''Conservation Achievement Awards'' (Aug 1, 2025) recognizing leaders.',61.21809999999999974,-149.9002999999999873,NULL,'2026-03-26 06:50:51','2026-03-26 06:50:51');
INSERT INTO organizations VALUES(33,'Don Young Port of Alaska','Anchorage, AK','https://www.muni.org/departments/port','Large (Hundreds of employees across Municipality, significant port operations staff)','Operations budget not explicitly stated, but drives >$14 billion in statewide economic activity annually. Over $104 million in current infrastructure investments.','Operates and modernizes Alaska''s primary deep-water port, handling containers, bulk cargo, and petroleum products. Provides critical transportation infrastructure supporting the state''s economy and national defense. [cite: 6 (previous search), 13 (previous search), 30]','Engaged in a multi-year ''Port Modernization Program'', which is a large-scale strategic transition involving complex engineering, logistics, and multi-stakeholder coordination. Recent leadership changes and continuous infrastructure upgrades present clear opportunities for Leslie''s expertise in strategic transitions, decision-making bottlenecks, and cross-sector complexity.','identified','infra','high','confirmed','Announcement of Terry Umatum as the new Port Director (Nov 17, 2025) following an interim director period. Actively undergoing a ''Port Modernization Program'' (started 2017, estimated 7-year duration) to upgrade aging infrastructure and accommodate larger vessels, indicating major strategic and operational challenges. [cite: 6 (previous search), 30]',61.21809999999999974,-149.9002999999999873,NULL,'2026-03-26 06:50:52','2026-03-26 06:50:52');
