INSERT INTO notes VALUES(1,1,'qualification','The Clearwater-Mi''kmaq partnership is genuinely groundbreaking. $1B acquisition in 2021. Multi-species ocean operations (lobster, scallops, clams, shrimp, crab) at $500M+ revenue. Both parties navigating shared governance across very different organizational cultures — exactly the "stuck partnership" Leslie solves.','2026-03-15 06:16:00');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(2,1,'general','Initial conversation with Ian Smith was promising. He acknowledged that the partnership governance model is "still being figured out" and that external perspective could be valuable. Wants to discuss with the board before committing.','2026-03-21 06:16:00');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(3,1,'call_note','Meeting scheduled for June 2nd with Ian Smith and Chief Terry Paul. Focus: exploring how external leadership advisory could help navigate the Indigenous-corporate governance challenges.','2026-03-22 06:16:00');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(4,2,'qualification','DOT is pivoting from pure hardware (ocean sensors) to a full ocean data platform (SaaS). Revenue growing but team scaling is creating founder-to-CEO transition challenges. $25M annual revenue, 45 people.','2026-03-17 06:16:00');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(5,4,'qualification','Publicly traded (TSX: PNG). Revenue tripled from $25M to $80M+ in 2 years. Multiple acquisitions (PanGeo Subsea, 13th Group). Hypergrowth creating integration challenges across defense, commercial, and environmental business lines. Ocean-wide platform company.','2026-03-18 06:16:00');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(6,4,'general','Karl Kenny (CEO) is a mutual connection through COVE. Known to be receptive to external advisory, especially around scaling culture and integrating acquisitions. The defense-to-commercial balance is a strategic alignment challenge.','2026-03-20 06:16:00');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(7,3,'qualification','Ocean intelligence company using satellite/drone/AI for ocean-wide monitoring. Growing fast through defense and commercial contracts. Founder-led, transitioning to scaled operations. COVE member, connected to Halifax ocean ecosystem.','2026-03-19 06:16:00');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(8,5,'qualification','Crown corporation — ports, monitoring networks, marine construction. $45M revenue, 120 people. Navigating government contracts + private partnerships + community stakeholders simultaneously. Classic cross-sector complexity.','2026-03-20 06:16:00');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(9,6,'qualification','Part of global Oceana network. $25M+ budget. Runs complex ocean policy campaigns requiring coordination across government, industry, and Indigenous stakeholders. Potential leadership advisory need around campaign alignment and stakeholder management.','2026-03-18 06:16:00');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(10,7,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Business\u000aNotes: Strong fit – significant budget, clear strategic direction, confirmed leadership transitions, and focus on long-term sustainability and economic growth. Excellent opportunity for Leslie''s expertise in strategic knots and leadership alignment.\u000aLeadership Signal: Fulvio Fracassi was appointed President and CEO in September 2024, following an international search. Two new executive leaders (VP, Talent and Communications; General Counsel and Corporate Secretary) joined in June/July 2025. The HPA also released a comprehensive 50-Year Plan in June 2022, indicating ongoing strategic development and potential for decision-making bottlenecks and alignment issues as new leadership implements this long-term vision.'),'2026-03-23 07:41:02');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(11,8,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Business\u000aNotes: Exceptional fit. COVE is actively scaling, forming complex partnerships, and dealing with talent challenges. Leslie''s advisory on strategic transitions and scaling culture would be invaluable.\u000aLeadership Signal: In November 2025, COVE was selected to host Canada''s first Maritime Defence Innovation Secure Hub (DISH) with a $29.4M government investment, indicating significant expansion and new strategic initiatives. A partnership with Carbon to Sea Initiative in September 2024 for open-source R&D also highlights cross-sector complexity. The CEO mentioned a ''decade long labour challenge'' in May 2023, implying ongoing scaling culture and talent acquisition issues.'),'2026-03-23 07:41:03');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(12,9,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Business\u000aNotes: Confirmed hypergrowth and strategic initiatives make this a strong lead for Leslie, especially with her background in tech and scaling culture.\u000aLeadership Signal: The company announced a newly redesigned website in March 2026 to reflect its ''innovative and mission ready next gen undersea warfare solutions,'' indicating a strategic refresh. In August 2025, it was reported the firm employs over 250 people and expects to expand to nearly 300 by year-end with major defense contracts, signifying hypergrowth and potential scaling challenges. They also received a £40 Million contract for Sonobuoys in March 2026.'),'2026-03-23 07:41:05');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(13,10,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Business\u000aNotes: Large, established company with continuous, multi-year contracts. Leslie''s experience in ''stuck partnerships'' and ''alignment issues'' would be relevant in managing such complex, long-duration projects.\u000aLeadership Signal: Awarded the Halifax-class Combat Systems in-service support contract valued at $182 million over six years in 2025, ensuring continuous operational readiness. Also undertaking P-3C aircraft upgrades, signaling ongoing large-scale projects and complex program management. Joel Houde, VP and GM, was named ''Defence Executive of the Year 2026,'' indicating strong leadership focus and strategic direction within the company.'),'2026-03-23 07:41:06');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(14,11,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Review\u000aNotes: Strong mission fit and confirmed strategic partnerships. Needs a bit more research to identify a specific senior leader contact.\u000aLeadership Signal: In April 2025, JASCO announced a ''global strategic partnership'' with Blue Ocean Monitoring, combining expertise in underwater acoustics and uncrewed underwater vehicles, indicating a strategic growth initiative and cross-sector collaboration. They also engage in projects with Indigenous fishers and DRDC, highlighting complex stakeholder environments.'),'2026-03-23 07:41:09');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(15,12,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Business\u000aNotes: Exciting growth-stage tech company with a clear ocean health mission. Good for Leslie to support their scaling and partnership strategies.\u000aLeadership Signal: Moved to join The PIER in the Port of Halifax in May 2024 to strengthen connections with local industry and expand global maritime partnerships. The CEO, Mark Wood, stated this move reflects their commitment to ''amplify our impact'' and ''opens up new avenues for expanding our reach''. Also launched ''Lucy II'' software in March 2024.'),'2026-03-23 07:41:10');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(16,13,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Business\u000aNotes: Excellent timing with confirmed governance and board transitions. Leslie''s skills in alignment and cross-sector complexity are a direct match for this non-profit with a crucial role in clean energy.\u000aLeadership Signal: In February 2026, FORCE announced a new independent governance structure and the appointment of two new directors, Dr. Jeffrey Taylor and Ross Jefferson. The executive director, Lindsay Bennett, noted this as a ''foundational shift'' to support responsible deployment and reinforce FORCE''s role as a transparent facilitator.'),'2026-03-23 07:41:12');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(17,14,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Review\u000aNotes: Not a direct ocean organization, but a key enabler and convener for the ocean economy. Leslie could work on broader regional leadership challenges that impact ocean businesses. Confirmed initiative aligns with her problem-solving.\u000aLeadership Signal: Launched ''The Productivity Puzzle'' initiative in April 2025 to address Nova Scotia''s productivity challenges, explicitly involving discussions and research to spark broader conversation and find solutions, which implies tackling ''strategic knots'' and ''decision-making bottlenecks'' at a regional level.'),'2026-03-23 07:41:13');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(18,15,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Business\u000aNotes: Confirmed leadership transition in finance to support hypergrowth is a direct match for Leslie''s expertise. Strong ''blue economy'' connection through the spaceport being in Nova Scotia and defense contracts.\u000aLeadership Signal: On March 20, 2026, the company announced the appointment of an interim finance leadership team to ''support the Company''s next phase of growth'' and ''modernize and streamline existing systems and processes to support disciplined growth and operational readiness.'' This follows a 10-year agreement with the Department of National Defence.'),'2026-03-23 07:41:15');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(19,16,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Review\u000aNotes: Government research arm, so ''leadership challenges'' are more about strategic direction and internal/external alignment than hypergrowth. Good for Leslie if she''s interested in policy and strategic influence within a public sector context.\u000aLeadership Signal: Regular participation in defense conferences (CANSEC 2025) and ongoing collaboration with industry and allies imply continuous strategic development and partnership management. The broader ''unprecedented defence investments'' by the Canadian government (March 2026) suggest an environment of increased mandate and potential for strategic re-prioritization.'),'2026-03-23 07:41:16');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(20,17,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Review\u000aNotes: Excellent, high-level opportunity. While not a single ''company,'' Leslie could advise the OSC on stakeholder alignment, managing complex initiatives, or potentially be placed within one of its member organizations. Strong win-win-win potential due to broad impact.\u000aLeadership Signal: In March 2026, the OSC announced $4.1M for an ''AI-powered Monitoring for Sustainable Wave-powered Desalination Project,'' and in late 2025, it announced $52 million in new, expanded project activity, indicating continuous growth, complex project management, and a need for strong strategic alignment across diverse partners.'),'2026-03-23 07:41:18');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(21,18,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Review\u000aNotes: Strong mission alignment with ''blue food'' and sustainability. Inferred leadership challenges based on company size and global presence. Needs verification on current strategic initiatives and leadership context via direct outreach.\u000aLeadership Signal: As a large, international company focused on innovation and sustainable marine resources, it''s highly likely to be navigating strategic growth and market shifts, implying ongoing leadership challenges related to scaling, market expansion, and maintaining a competitive edge. (No recent specific news of leadership transition found in current search, but their nature implies it).'),'2026-03-23 07:41:19');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(22,19,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Review\u000aNotes: Academic institution, but involved in significant, applied ocean research with commercialization potential. Leslie could advise on strategic partnerships and research translation. Dr. Fennel is a strong potential contact for initial outreach.\u000aLeadership Signal: Ongoing involvement in major research consortia like the Carbon to Sea Initiative''s Ocean Alk-Align (received $11M USD in grants in 2023) indicates complex, multi-stakeholder project management and the need for strategic alignment across diverse research teams.'),'2026-03-23 07:41:22');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(23,20,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Review\u000aNotes: Massive scale and long-term project. Leslie''s advisory on large-scale strategic alignment and complex partnership management is a great fit, even if specific leadership challenges aren''t publicly confirmed with dates. A critical national project.\u000aLeadership Signal: Ongoing steel cutting for River-class destroyers (March 2026) and continuous work on the National Shipbuilding Strategy indicate a sustained period of high-stakes, complex operations. Such a massive, long-term project inherently involves ongoing strategic challenges, partnership management, and potential for decision-making bottlenecks.'),'2026-03-23 07:41:23');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(24,21,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Review\u000aNotes: Part of a major global player, strong ocean tech focus. ''Unknown'' leadership signal tier, but a strong company to investigate for a potential placement given its sector and scale.\u000aLeadership Signal: Insufficient public data to assess leadership challenges. Recommend direct outreach to verify organizational context before pursuing.'),'2026-03-23 07:41:25');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(25,22,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Business\u000aNotes: A very large organization; the placement would likely need to be with a specific regional or project-based leadership team focused on marine/ocean infrastructure.\u000aLeadership Signal: Reported significant net profit growth (3251.61% for Q2 2025) and an outlook revised to positive, with expected free operating cash flow (FOCF) rising to over $500M in 2026. This rapid financial improvement suggests strategic transitions and potential scaling challenges within its various operational units, including those focused on marine infrastructure.'),'2026-03-23 07:44:56');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(26,23,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Review\u000aNotes: Focus on complex partnerships and large-scale environmental solutions. A large organization, so specific local leadership challenges would need to be identified, but the nature of their work suggests a good fit.\u000aLeadership Signal: The Nature Conservancy is actively working with a ''suite of partners'' on complex projects like the Pacific Coast Highway Natural Infrastructure Pilot Project and creating a ''blueprint for nature-based adaptation for Monterey Bay''. This level of multi-stakeholder engagement inherently involves ''stuck partnerships'' and ''alignment issues'' in coordinating diverse interests and goals for regional climate resilience.'),'2026-03-26 06:31:17');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(27,24,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Review\u000aNotes: Multi-university consortium could be a good fit for Leslie''s cross-sector complexity and alignment skills, but specific leadership challenges would need to be confirmed.\u000aLeadership Signal: MLML is a consortium of seven California State Universities, offering a thesis-based master''s degree. The nature of a consortium implies ongoing ''alignment issues'' and ''cross-sector complexity'' in coordinating research, education, and funding across multiple academic institutions. The expansion of the NOAA-relevant STEM disciplines and social sciences via CCME-II program suggests ''scaling culture'' during growth.'),'2026-03-26 06:31:23');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(28,25,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Review\u000aNotes: Federal agency, so a placement might require navigating government bureaucracy, but their broad mandate and ecosystem complexity are a good fit for Leslie''s skills.\u000aLeadership Signal: As a large federal marine protected area, the MBNMS navigates balancing conservation with sustainable use, involving ''multi-stakeholder'' interests (recreational, commercial, research). This inherently creates ''cross-sector complexity'' and potential ''decision-making bottlenecks'' in policy implementation and resource management. Their active programs like ''Following Microplastics from Shore to Sanctuary'' and ''Iconic Kelp Action Plan'' require strong coordination and strategic direction.'),'2026-03-26 06:31:29');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(29,26,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Review\u000aNotes: Academic environment, good for strategic thinking and program development. Might need to pinpoint a specific initiative or growth area for Leslie''s advisory.\u000aLeadership Signal: The department emphasizes ''immersive research, fieldwork, and faculty mentorship'' and states it''s ''being in the field as much as in the classroom''. While not explicitly stating a challenge, this hands-on, expansive approach for students and faculty in a dynamic environment like the Monterey Bay National Marine Sanctuary implies ongoing ''organizational alignment'' needs between academic rigor and practical application, as well as ''scaling culture'' for growing student involvement in research.'),'2026-03-26 06:31:30');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(30,27,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Review\u000aNotes: Good blue economy fit, but Santa Cruz HQ pushes it to the edge of the 15-mile radius if measured from Monterey directly. Their operations are within Monterey Bay, which is key.\u000aLeadership Signal: The trust focuses on ''finding locally-harvested, sustainable seafood'' and supporting ''the local fishing community'' by connecting various stakeholders. This involves managing ''cross-sector complexity'' and building ''aligned outcomes'' among fishermen, markets, and consumers. The 2020 guide to finding local seafood and the expansion of the ''Best Choice Restaurant Program'' in 2026 suggests strategic growth and partnership refinement.'),'2026-03-26 06:31:35');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(32,29,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Business\u000aNotes: Strong fit – large budget, ocean-wide mission, clear strategic direction towards sustainability and community benefits.\u000aLeadership Signal: Actively pursuing a ''world''s most sustainable port'' vision and extensive sustainability initiatives, involving strategic transitions, environmental protection, and community consideration.'),'2026-03-26 06:43:06');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(33,30,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Review\u000aNotes: Key player in marine infrastructure, potential for strategic advisory on project delivery and stakeholder management.\u000aLeadership Signal: Involvement in significant marine construction projects like the Vancouver Airport Fuel Delivery Project and G3 Terminal Marine Structures implies managing complex partnerships and operational scaling.'),'2026-03-26 06:43:08');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(34,31,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Business\u000aNotes: High-tech company, ideal for advisor focused on founder-led scaling and hypergrowth in deep tech.\u000aLeadership Signal: Described as a ''world-leading, privately owned company'' with ''over 80 skilled professionals across Canada, US and the UK'', suggesting scaling and global expansion challenges.'),'2026-03-26 06:43:15');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(35,32,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Business\u000aNotes: Significant influence as a conservation funder. Leslie''s skills in navigating complex stakeholder landscapes would be valuable in enhancing their strategic impact across a network of environmental groups.\u000aLeadership Signal: Leadership transition to Michael Barber as President and CEO, who started as a Program Officer in 2013. Actively involved in ''Organizational capacity grants'' to promote leadership within conservation organizations. Hosts ''Conservation Achievement Awards'' (Aug 1, 2025) recognizing leaders.'),'2026-03-26 06:50:51');
INSERT INTO notes VALUES(36,33,'qualification',unistr('Review Status: Lead for Business\u000aNotes: Very strong fit. Major public infrastructure undergoing significant modernization and leadership transition. High economic impact and complexity align perfectly with Leslie''s advisory focus.\u000aLeadership Signal: Announcement of Terry Umatum as the new Port Director (Nov 17, 2025) following an interim director period. Actively undergoing a ''Port Modernization Program'' (started 2017, estimated 7-year duration) to upgrade aging infrastructure and accommodate larger vessels, indicating major strategic and operational challenges. [cite: 6 (previous search), 30]'),'2026-03-26 06:50:52');
INSERT INTO outreach_drafts VALUES(1,2,3,'A colleague I''d love to introduce — leadership advisory for ocean tech scaling',unistr('Hi James,\u000a\u000aI hope this finds you well. I''ve been following DOT''s evolution from ocean sensors into a full ocean data platform — it''s exactly the kind of bold pivot that reshapes an industry.\u000a\u000aI''m reaching out because I''d love to introduce you to my colleague Leslie, who I think could be a genuinely valuable resource for DOT at this stage of your growth.\u000a\u000aLeslie has spent nearly twenty years helping tech executives navigate the founder-to-CEO transition, create aligned teams, and scale operations without losing the culture that made the company special. She''s now bringing that same discipline to the blue economy, and she''s looking for one ocean company to work with intensively this summer.\u000a\u000aWhat she''s offering is a condensed senior advisory engagement — 6 to 8 weeks, the equivalent of a year-long coaching engagement compressed into the summer. She specializes in exactly the kind of hardware-to-SaaS pivot and team scaling challenges DOT is navigating right now.\u000a\u000aWould you be open to a 30-minute call to explore whether there''s a fit?\u000a\u000aWarm regards,\u000aKarl'),'sent','2026-03-19 06:16:00','2026-03-19 06:16:00','2026-03-23 06:16:00');
INSERT INTO discovery_runs VALUES(1,1,'ocean technology ocean infrastructure blue economy organizations Halifax Nova Scotia','','','[{"name":"Clearwater Seafoods","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia","website":"https://clearwater.ca","estimated_size":"250","estimated_budget":"$500M","mission_focus":"Premium multi-species ocean harvest company with vertically integrated operations across lobster, scallops, clams, shrimp, and crab. Joint ownership with Mi''kmaq coalition. One of North America''s largest ocean product companies.","why_fit":"The Mi''kmaq-Clearwater partnership is a groundbreaking Indigenous-corporate joint venture. Multi-species ocean operations at massive scale, navigating shared governance across very different organizational cultures — exactly the \"stuck partnership\" Leslie solves.","keyword_category":"sector","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed"},{"name":"Dartmouth Ocean Technologies (DOT)","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://dartmouthocean.com","estimated_size":"45","estimated_budget":"$25M","mission_focus":"Ocean technology company developing underwater sensing, ocean monitoring platforms, and ocean data systems for commercial and defense clients worldwide.","why_fit":"DOT is scaling from a niche sensor company into a full ocean data platform. Rapid growth, international expansion, and the pivot from hardware to SaaS creates leadership alignment challenges ideal for Leslie''s advisory.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred"},{"name":"Maerospace (COVE Member)","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia","website":"https://maerospace.com","estimated_size":"35","estimated_budget":"$20M","mission_focus":"Commercial ocean intelligence company using satellite, drone, and AI to provide ocean monitoring, maritime domain awareness, and environmental surveillance across entire ocean basins.","why_fit":"Ocean-wide platform company serving the full marine sector. Growing fast through defense and commercial contracts. Transitioning from founder-led to scaled operations — a classic inflection point where external advisory is most valuable.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred"},{"name":"Kraken Robotics","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://krakenrobotics.com","estimated_size":"300","estimated_budget":"$80M","mission_focus":"Publicly traded ocean technology company providing underwater robotics (AUVs/ROVs), sonar systems, ocean batteries, and subsea sensors for defense, commercial, and environmental applications.","why_fit":"Kraken is in hypergrowth — revenue tripled in 2 years, rapid hiring, multiple acquisitions. A public company navigating the transition from startup culture to institutional operations. Cross-sector complexity (defense + commercial + environmental) creates alignment challenges.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed"},{"name":"Nova Scotia Fisheries & Ocean Infrastructure Corp","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia","website":"https://nsfoi.ca","estimated_size":"120","estimated_budget":"$45M","mission_focus":"Crown corporation operating at intersection of government mandate and commercial fisheries. Port systems, ocean monitoring networks, and marine facility construction across Atlantic Canada.","why_fit":"Building ocean infrastructure at scale requires navigating government contracts, private partnerships, and community stakeholders simultaneously. Classic cross-sector complexity with multiple stuck partnerships that need alignment.","keyword_category":"infra","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred"}]',5,0,'2026-03-13 06:16:00');
INSERT INTO discovery_runs VALUES(2,1,'Default search for Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada',unistr('You are a senior research analyst supporting a leadership advisor who is seeking a 6-8 week Entrepreneurship in Residence placement in Halifax, Nova Scotia. Your task is to find real, qualified ocean-focused organizations using web search.\u000a\u000aADVISOR BRIEF:\u000a- Geography: Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Search Radius: 15 miles\u000a- Placement Start: 2026-06-01\u000a- Placement Duration: 6-8 weeks\u000a- Focus Areas: Ocean health, Ocean economy, Ocean technology, Ocean infrastructure, Blue economy\u000a- Leadership Problems She Solves: Stuck partnerships, Alignment issues, Truth-telling gaps, Decision-making bottlenecks, Cross-sector complexity, Founder-to-CEO transitions, Scaling culture during hypergrowth\u000a- Non-Negotiables: No single-species operations (salmon-only, lobster-only, etc.), No freshwater organizations, Must have genuine ocean/marine focus\u000a- Win-Win-Win Criteria: Value for the organization, positive ocean outcomes, community benefits\u000a\u000aABOUT THE ADVISOR (LESLIE):\u000aNearly 20 years helping tech executives create happier teams, aligned outcomes, and stronger ROI. Now transitioning to ocean conservation / blue economy leadership advisory. Specializes in: stuck partnerships, alignment issues, truth-telling gaps, strategic knots. Works best 1:1 with senior leaders or with top teams on defined missions.\u000a- Works best 1:1 with senior leaders or with top teams on defined missions\u000a- Looking for a 6-8 week Entrepreneurship in Residence placement\u000a- Offering condensed senior advisory (equivalent of a year-long engagement in 2 months)\u000a- Best fit: organizations creating win-win-wins for corporations, nature, and future generations\u000a- Includes: for-profit companies, non-profits, NGOs, public-private partnerships, social enterprises, research institutions — any organization type\u000a\u000aGEOGRAPHY CONSTRAINT:\u000a- Primary location: Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Search radius: within 15 miles of Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Only include organizations headquartered or with major operations within this radius\u000a\u000aSEARCH TASK:\u000aFind ocean-focused organizations within 15 miles of Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada. Include ALL types: companies, non-profits, research institutions, NGOs, public-private partnerships, Crown corporations.\u000a\u000aHARD FILTERS — Qualitative Exclusions Only:\u000a- EXCLUDE: Any organization that operates exclusively on a single marine species (salmon-only farms, lobster harvesters, tuna fisheries, whale conservation, sea turtle rescue)\u000a- EXCLUDE: Any freshwater organization (lakes, rivers, freshwater fisheries)\u000a- EXCLUDE: ExxonMobil Canada, Shell Canada, SBM Offshore (enterprise-scale oil & gas — placement impractical)\u000a- Do NOT use the broad keyword ''offshore'' — use ''offshore wind'' only\u000a- Budget and headcount are NOT exclusion criteria — return all qualifying organizations regardless of size\u000a\u000aKEYWORD SEARCH STRATEGY — Two-Axis Search:\u000aSearch for organizations using ANY of these sector terms:\u000a\u000aPRIMARY (Sector Synonyms): ocean, marine, maritime, blue economy, oceanographic, offshore wind, subsea, coastal\u000a\u000aECONOMIC FRAMING: blue finance, ocean economy, marine commerce, ocean investment, investing in ocean, ocean-focused fund, marine investment, ocean venture, sustainable seafood investment, coastal economy investment, ocean-focused accelerator\u000a\u000aINFRASTRUCTURE & OPERATIONS: marine infrastructure, offshore wind operations, offshore wind development, shipbuilding, naval architecture, port authority, marine logistics, harbour management, underwater systems, marine engineering\u000a\u000aSCIENCE & DEEP TECHNOLOGY: ocean technology, oceanography, marine science, AUV, ROV, underwater acoustics, hydrography, bathymetry, ocean intelligence, marine sensing, seabed mapping, ocean data\u000a\u000aCONSERVATION & SUSTAINABILITY: ocean stewardship, marine conservation, ocean health, blue carbon, coastal resilience, marine protected areas, ocean sustainability, ocean governance\u000a\u000aGOVERNANCE & POLICY: marine spatial planning, ocean policy, coastal management, fisheries management (broad-mandate only), marine regulatory, EEZ\u000a\u000aFOOD SYSTEMS (handle with care — enforce single-species exclusion): aquaculture (multi-species only), mariculture, sustainable seafood, seafood supply chain, blue food\u000a\u000aALSO PRIORITIZE organizations showing these LEADERSHIP SIGNALS:\u000afounder-led scaling, hypergrowth, cross-sector partnership, strategic transition, joint venture, public-private partnership, multi-stakeholder, organizational alignment, board transition, scaling culture\u000a\u000aGEOGRAPHIC NOTE: Always pair economic/investment terms with Halifax, Nova Scotia, or Atlantic Canada.\u000a\u000aLEADERSHIP SIGNAL TIER INSTRUCTION:\u000aFor every organization returned, assess and report a leadership_signal_tier value:\u000a- Use ''confirmed'' if you found specific, dateable evidence of a leadership challenge (news article about rapid hiring, founder transition announcement, partnership press release, job posting for Chief People Officer, board change filing)\u000a- Use ''inferred'' if the org''s profile strongly implies a current leadership challenge without direct evidence (recent significant funding round, newly commercialized product, recently expanded government mandate, recent merger/restructure)\u000a- Use ''unknown'' if you could not find sufficient public information to assess leadership challenges\u000a\u000aCRITICAL DISTINCTION: ''unknown'' means the data does not exist to assess — it does NOT mean no leadership challenge exists. Low public profile ≠ no leadership challenge. Never conflate absence of data with absence of challenge. All three tiers are included in results; ''unknown'' is never an exclusion reason.\u000a\u000aFor ''unknown'' tier, set leadership_signal_evidence to: ''Insufficient public data to assess leadership challenges. Recommend direct outreach to verify organizational context before pursuing.''\u000a\u000aEXCLUSION RULES (reinforced):\u000a- No single-species operations: salmon-only, lobster-only, tuna-only, shrimp-only, whale conservation, sea turtle rescue\u000a- No freshwater organizations: lake research, river conservation, freshwater fisheries\u000a- No organizations outside 15 miles of Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Do NOT confuse ''no public data found'' with ''no leadership challenges detected''\u000a\u000aHALIFAX OCEAN ECOSYSTEM REFERENCE:\u000aCross-reference these known Nova Scotia ocean sector organizations when searching. Include them if they meet criteria, and search for additional qualifying organizations beyond this list:\u000a\u000aOCEAN TECH & SCIENCE:\u000a- Kraken Robotics — subsea technology, sonar, AUVs\u000a- Kongsberg Maritime Canada — maritime sensors and systems\u000a- GeoSpectrum Technologies — underwater acoustics\u000a- Innovasea — ocean tracking and aquaculture technology\u000a- JASCO Applied Sciences — ocean acoustics, environmental monitoring\u000a- AML Oceanographic — oceanographic instruments\u000a- Ultra Electronics Maritime Systems — defence and marine electronics\u000a- General Dynamics Canada — defence and ocean systems\u000a- Lockheed Martin Canada — defence, maritime surveillance\u000a- metOcean Telematics — ocean data buoys and telemetry\u000a- Fugro GeoSurveys — seabed mapping, geophysical survey\u000a- MDA (MacDonald Dettwiler) — satellite intelligence and earth observation\u000a- DSM Nutritional Products — marine ingredients/omega-3s\u000a- Acadian Seaplants — seaweed / marine agriculture\u000a- Ocean Sonics — hydrophones and marine acoustics\u000a- MacArtney Underwater Technology — underwater connectors and systems\u000a- CarteNav Solutions — maritime surveillance software\u000a- Deep Vision Inc. — underwater imaging and inspection\u000a\u000aOCEAN INFRASTRUCTURE & ENERGY:\u000a- Irving Shipbuilding — federal shipbuilding ($29.3B contract), Halifax\u000a- Babcock Canada — naval engineering and ship lifecycle support\u000a- FORCE (Fundy Ocean Research Centre for Energy) — tidal energy R&D\u000a- SNC-Lavalin — engineering, ocean infrastructure projects\u000a- ABCO Industries — marine fabrication\u000a\u000aDO NOT PURSUE (out of scope):\u000a- SBM Offshore — oil & gas production systems; enterprise scale\u000a- ExxonMobil Canada — offshore oil & gas major\u000a- Shell Canada — offshore energy exploration\u000a\u000aTRANSPORTATION & LOGISTICS:\u000a- Port of Halifax / Halifax Port Authority — major Atlantic port\u000a- Halterm Container Terminal — port operations\u000a- Atlantic Towing — offshore marine services\u000a- Secunda Canada — offshore marine and oil field services\u000a- Horizon Maritime Services — offshore vessel support\u000a- Oceanex — marine shipping, Atlantic Canada\u000a\u000aFISHERIES (broad ocean operations only):\u000a- High Liner Foods — global seafood processing, HQ Lunenburg NS\u000a- Clearwater Seafoods — premium shellfish, national and international scale\u000a\u000aEDUCATION & RESEARCH:\u000a- Bedford Institute of Oceanography (BIO) — federal ocean research, Dartmouth NS\u000a- Dalhousie University — Faculty of Science, ocean/marine programs\u000a- DRDC Atlantic — Defence Research & Development Canada, maritime focus\u000a- National Research Council Canada (NRC) — ocean science and engineering\u000a- COVE (Centre for Ocean Ventures & Entrepreneurship) — Halifax ocean innovation hub\u000a\u000aNETWORKS & ASSOCIATIONS:\u000a- OTCNS (Ocean Technology Council of Nova Scotia)\u000a- Ocean Tracking Network — Dalhousie, global ocean monitoring\u000a- COINAtlantic — Coastal and Ocean Information Network Atlantic\u000a\u000aOUTPUT FORMAT:\u000aReturn your results as a JSON array with this exact structure. Include both organization fields AND lead contact fields:\u000a[\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Organization Name",\u000a    "location": "City, Province (or full address)",\u000a    "website": "https://...",\u000a    "estimated_size": 100,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$50M",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Brief description of their mission...",\u000a    "why_fit": "Why this org is a fit for the advisor...",\u000a    "keyword_category": "sector",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "confirmed",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Specific evidence found: recently announced...",\u000a    "lat": 44.6488,\u000a    "lng": -63.5752,\u000a    "contact_name": "Jane Smith",\u000a    "contact_email": "jsmith@org.com",\u000a    "contact_position": "CEO and Executive Director",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://linkedin.com/in/janesmith",\u000a    "contact_bio": "15 years in ocean technology, previously led...",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "Strong fit — $50M budget, ocean-wide mission, leadership transition underway"\u000a  }\u000a]\u000a\u000aFIELD NOTES:\u000a- keyword_category: one of "sector", "infra", "econ", "sci", "gov" — which cluster best describes this org\u000a- signal_strength: one of "high", "strong", "supplemental", "careful" — how strong a lead for Leslie\u000a- leadership_signal_tier: one of "confirmed", "inferred", "unknown" — evidence quality for leadership challenge\u000a- leadership_signal_evidence: 1-3 sentences describing specific evidence or standard ''insufficient data'' note\u000a- lat/lng: approximate coordinates for Halifax-area mapping (decimal degrees)\u000a- review_status: one of "Lead for Business", "Lead for Review", "Pending Review", "Do NOT Contact"\u000a\u000aCOUNT AND QUALITY:\u000aReturn between 10 and 15 results. Prefer verified organizations with web-searchable evidence over speculative results. Do not return fewer than 10 results. Distribute across all three signal tiers — do not exclude unknown-tier orgs to meet a count target. Sort by estimated budget (high to low) with signal tier as tiebreaker.\u000a\u000aReturn ONLY the JSON array, no other text.'),unistr('```json\u000a[\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Kraken Robotics",\u000a    "location": "Dartmouth, Nova Scotia",\u000a    "website": "https://krakenrobotics.com/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 200,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$50M+",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Developing and commercializing advanced sonar, laser, and robotic systems for underwater data acquisition and imaging, primarily for defence, commercial, and scientific applications.",\u000a    "why_fit": "A publicly-traded, rapidly innovating company in ocean technology, likely facing challenges associated with scaling product lines, global market penetration, and managing complex contracts in defence and commercial sectors. Advisor''s expertise in founder-led scaling and cross-sector complexity would be highly valuable.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "sci",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "inferred",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "As a publicly traded company (TSX: PNG) in a high-growth sector, Kraken Robotics would inherently be navigating strategic transitions, investor relations, and scaling challenges. Their recent strategic shifts and product launches imply ongoing organizational development.",\u000a    "lat": 44.6488,\u000a    "lng": -63.5752,\u000a    "contact_name": "Karl Kenny",\u000a    "contact_email": "info@krakenrobotics.com",\u000a    "contact_position": "President & CEO",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/karl-kenny-662287b/",\u000a    "contact_bio": "Veteran entrepreneur and leader in the subsea technology sector, driving Kraken Robotics'' innovation and global expansion.",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "Strong fit for Leslie due to high-tech, global ambition, and publicly traded status which often implies strategic challenges."\u000a  },\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Irving Shipbuilding Inc.",\u000a    "location": "Halifax, Nova Scotia",\u000a    "website": "https://www.irvingshipbuilding.com/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 2500,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$2B+",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Prime contractor for Canada''s National Shipbuilding Strategy, focusing on naval vessel construction, modernization, and maintenance, as well as commercial shipbuilding and repair.",\u000a    "why_fit": "Managing multi-billion dollar federal contracts requires immense cross-sector complexity, strategic alignment across numerous stakeholders (government, suppliers, workforce), and continuous decision-making in a high-stakes environment. Leslie''s expertise in stuck partnerships and alignment issues would be critical.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "infra",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "inferred",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "The ongoing, large-scale nature of the National Shipbuilding Strategy and the inherent complexity of defence procurement projects suggest continuous strategic, operational, and partnership challenges within the organization.",\u000a    "lat": 44.6488,\u000a    "lng": -63.5752,\u000a    "contact_name": "Kevin McCoy",\u000a    "contact_email": "info@irvingshipbuilding.com",\u000a    "contact_position": "President",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/kevin-mccoy-b2b96328/",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "Very large organization with significant public-private partnership challenges and long-term strategic needs."\u000a  },\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Clearwater Seafoods",\u000a    "location": "Bedford, Nova Scotia",\u000a    "website": "https://www.clearwater.ca/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 1500,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$500M+",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Sustainably harvesting, processing, and distributing a diverse range of premium wild-caught shellfish a