scientific programs, including significant ocean and marine research.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Large academic institution, good for community benefit and potential for strategic partnerships in research/commercialization.","budget_tier":"enterprise"},{"name":"Canada''s Ocean Supercluster (OSC)","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia","website":"https://oceansupercluster.ca/","estimated_size":50,"estimated_budget":"$150M+","mission_focus":"A national, industry-led initiative to accelerate innovation and drive sustainable economic growth across Canada''s ocean economy by connecting businesses, researchers, and innovators.","why_fit":"As a major federal innovation fund, OSC deals with complex public-private partnerships, cross-sector complexity in managing diverse projects, and ensuring alignment across a broad ecosystem of stakeholders to achieve national outcomes. Leslie''s expertise in strategic knots and alignment issues would be directly applicable.","keyword_category":"econ","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Established as a national initiative with significant government funding (Canada committed $153 million in 2018), OSC is constantly navigating multi-stakeholder dynamics and strategic project management across diverse ocean sectors. CEO Kendra MacDonald is actively leading this organization.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Kendra MacDonald","contact_email":"info@oceansupercluster.ca","contact_position":"CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/kendramacdonald1/","contact_bio":"Experienced leader in innovation, strategy, and technology, driving collaborative initiatives across the ocean economy.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Excellent fit due to national mandate, large budget, and inherent cross-sector complexity in its mission.","budget_tier":"large"},{"name":"Halifax Port Authority","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia","website":"https://portofhalifax.ca/","estimated_size":250,"estimated_budget":"$100M+","mission_focus":"Facilitating trade and economic growth by managing the Port of Halifax, developing marine infrastructure, and fostering community connections.","why_fit":"As a critical piece of ocean infrastructure and an economic driver, the Port faces ongoing strategic planning, stakeholder alignment (shipping lines, logistics, city, government), and balancing economic growth with environmental sustainability. Leslie''s experience with multi-stakeholder complexity and decision-making bottlenecks would be valuable.","keyword_category":"infra","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"The Port of Halifax is continuously involved in infrastructure development projects and managing relationships with numerous local and international stakeholders, implying ongoing strategic challenges and partnership complexities.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Captain Allan Gray","contact_email":"info@portofhalifax.ca","contact_position":"President & CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/allan-gray-8a56a632/","contact_bio":"An accomplished maritime professional with extensive experience in port operations and leadership.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Important public-private entity with constant strategic and operational challenges related to trade and infrastructure.","budget_tier":"large"},{"name":"Bedford Institute of Oceanography (BIO)","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://www.dfo-mpo.gc.ca/science/facilities-installations/bio-eng.html","estimated_size":600,"estimated_budget":"$75M+","mission_focus":"Canada''s largest centre for oceanographic research, conducting multidisciplinary studies in physical, chemical, and biological oceanography, marine fisheries, and geology.","why_fit":"As a major government research institution, BIO faces challenges in strategic research prioritization, inter-agency collaboration, talent management, and translating scientific findings into policy and innovation. Leslie''s focus on strategic knots and alignment could help optimize research impact.","keyword_category":"oceanographic","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"As a large government research facility, BIO constantly manages multiple scientific programs, inter-departmental collaborations, and adapting research priorities to national needs, implying continuous strategic and operational leadership challenges.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Mary-Lynn Dickson","contact_email":"XMAR-BIOInformation@dfo-mpo.gc.ca","contact_position":"Director General, Gulf Region (BIO is part of DFO Science)","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/mary-lynn-dickson-0a568b20/","contact_bio":"Senior leader within Fisheries and Oceans Canada, overseeing significant scientific research initiatives.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Major research institution, potentially interested in strategic advisory on operational efficiency or knowledge transfer.","budget_tier":"mid"},{"name":"Kraken Robotics","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://krakenrobotics.com/","estimated_size":200,"estimated_budget":"$50M+","mission_focus":"Developing and commercializing advanced sonar, laser, and robotic systems for underwater data acquisition and imaging, primarily for defence, commercial, and scientific applications.","why_fit":"A publicly-traded, rapidly innovating company in ocean technology, likely facing challenges associated with scaling product lines, global market penetration, and managing complex contracts in defence and commercial sectors. Advisor''s expertise in founder-led scaling and cross-sector complexity would be highly valuable.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"As a publicly traded company (TSX: PNG) in a high-growth sector, Kraken Robotics would inherently be navigating strategic transitions, investor relations, and scaling challenges. Their recent strategic shifts and product launches imply ongoing organizational development.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Karl Kenny","contact_email":"info@krakenrobotics.com","contact_position":"President & CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/karl-kenny-662287b/","contact_bio":"Veteran entrepreneur and leader in the subsea technology sector, driving Kraken Robotics'' innovation and global expansion.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Strong fit for Leslie due to high-tech, global ambition, and publicly traded status which often implies strategic challenges.","budget_tier":"mid"},{"name":"JASCO Applied Sciences","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://jasco.com/","estimated_size":100,"estimated_budget":"$20M+","mission_focus":"Global leader in underwater acoustics, providing services and technology for environmental monitoring, defence, marine mammal mitigation, and ocean science.","why_fit":"JASCO is a high-tech company experiencing growth through acquisitions and international collaborations, indicating strategic transitions, potential integration challenges, and the need to scale culture during expansion. Leslie''s expertise in strategic knots and scaling culture would be highly valuable.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Recent news highlights acquisitions (Cryosphere Innovation, Autonomous Marine Systems Inc.), new technical director hires, and significant collaborative projects, all indicative of strategic growth, integration challenges, and leadership evolution.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Ken Collins","contact_email":"info@jasco.com","contact_position":"CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/ken-collins-8b4b7218/","contact_bio":"Leader in ocean acoustics and environmental consulting, steering JASCO''s global scientific and commercial endeavors.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"High-growth tech company with clear signals of strategic transitions and integration needs.","budget_tier":"mid"},{"name":"GeoSpectrum Technologies Inc.","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://geospectrum.ca/","estimated_size":100,"estimated_budget":"$15M+","mission_focus":"Designing and manufacturing advanced underwater acoustic components and systems for maritime surveillance, defence, and ocean exploration.","why_fit":"This fast-growing company has secured significant contracts and is actively hiring, indicating hypergrowth and the need to scale culture, manage strategic partnerships (e.g., with Novacavi for cable solutions), and navigate rapid expansion. Leslie''s insights into leadership problems during growth phases would be beneficial.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Recent news from February 2026 and July 2025 details significant hiring plans, contract wins in Europe, US, and Asia, and company expansion, clearly indicating hypergrowth and strategic scaling challenges.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Paul Yeatman","contact_email":"sales@geospectrum.ca","contact_position":"President","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/paul-yeatman-912a7a10/","contact_bio":"An experienced leader in the defence and ocean technology sectors, driving innovation in underwater acoustics.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Very strong signal of hypergrowth and expansion, ideal for Leslie''s expertise.","budget_tier":"small_mid"},{"name":"COVE (Centre for Ocean Ventures & Entrepreneurship)","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://www.coveocean.com/","estimated_size":70,"estimated_budget":"$10M+","mission_focus":"A global innovation hub for the ocean economy, supporting the commercialization of ocean technology companies through shared infrastructure, programs, and a collaborative ecosystem.","why_fit":"COVE is a nexus for startups, industry, and academia, and is directly involved in fostering hypergrowth and strategic transitions for its member companies. Leslie''s expertise in scaling culture and founder-to-CEO transitions would be highly beneficial to COVE''s portfolio and its own organizational development.","keyword_category":"econ","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"COVE is explicitly focused on accelerating ocean technology companies, implying a constant need for strategic guidance on scaling, commercialization, and fostering strong partnerships. Its role as a hub for ''over 70 organizations'' suggests ongoing complexity in managing diverse stakeholder needs and growth.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Melanie Nadeau","contact_email":"info@coveocean.com","contact_position":"CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/melanie-nadeau-a7346123/","contact_bio":"Accomplished leader with a strong background in economic development and supporting innovation ecosystems.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Excellent strategic fit as an accelerator of ocean-focused hypergrowth organizations.","budget_tier":"small_mid"},{"name":"CarteNav Solutions","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia","website":"https://cartenav.com/","estimated_size":75,"estimated_budget":"$10M+","mission_focus":"Developing ISR (Intelligence, Surveillance, Reconnaissance) mission software for situational awareness in maritime, land, and air environments for defence, security, and commercial clients.","why_fit":"CarteNav, a subsidiary of PAL Aerospace, continually innovates its software and expands its global customer base. Having undergone an acquisition and with a focus on product and training expansion, they likely navigate strategic alignment within a larger corporate structure and scaling development teams. Leslie''s experience with alignment issues and strategic knots would be valuable.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Acquired by PAL Aerospace in 2016. News from 2014 mentions a new CEO appointment and rapid growth. Current news from June 2025 details showcasing advanced mission system solutions at international airshows, emphasizing continuous innovation and market expansion.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Nick Edwards","contact_email":"info@cartenav.com","contact_position":"VP & General Manager","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/nick-edwards-a400a45/","contact_bio":"Executive leader overseeing operations and strategic direction for CarteNav''s mission software solutions.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Tech company with strong growth, acquisitions, and consistent product innovation. Good for strategic alignment and scaling.","budget_tier":"small_mid"},{"name":"Ocean Sonics","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia (Truro HQ with Halifax software office)","website":"https://oceansonics.com/","estimated_size":50,"estimated_budget":"$5M+","mission_focus":"Pioneering smart digital hydrophones and acoustic solutions for real-time ocean sound monitoring, environmental assessment, defence, and energy sectors.","why_fit":"A founder-led company with recent strategic moves, including opening a new Halifax office at The PIER and launching new software. This indicates ongoing scaling, product commercialization challenges, and managing distributed teams. Leslie''s insights on founder-led scaling and strategic transitions would be directly applicable.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Founded by Mark Wood and Desiree Stockermans, the company recently announced an expansion by joining The PIER at the Port of Halifax for their growing software team (May 2024), and launched new software (Lucy II) in March 2024, indicating strategic growth and operational transitions.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Mark Wood","contact_email":"jennifer.aftanas@oceansonics.com (Media contact for CEO)","contact_position":"CEO & Founder","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/mark-wood-03716035/","contact_bio":"Visionary founder driving innovation in underwater acoustic technology with a passion for giving the ocean a voice.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Founder-led, rapidly growing, and strategically expanding into a new location – excellent fit for Leslie.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Ocean Startup Project","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia","website":"https://oceanstartupproject.ca/","estimated_size":15,"estimated_budget":"$5M+","mission_focus":"A pan-Atlantic (now national) initiative that empowers Canadian ocean startups, providing funding, programs, and connections to accelerate the commercialization of sustainable ocean solutions.","why_fit":"As an organization dedicated to fostering startup growth and commercialization, OSP is constantly dealing with founder-led scaling, strategic transitions for numerous ventures, and complex multi-stakeholder engagement (investors, entrepreneurs, government, academia). Leslie''s direct experience with these issues would be a perfect fit to advise OSP''s leadership or its portfolio.","keyword_category":"econ","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Since its launch in 2020, OSP has expanded nationally, supported over 256 startups, distributed significant funds, and created hundreds of jobs. This clearly demonstrates hypergrowth, strategic transitions (national expansion), and managing a complex ecosystem of growing ventures.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Sherry Soanes","contact_email":"info@oceanstartupproject.ca","contact_position":"Executive Director","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/sherry-soanes-2541a017/","contact_bio":"Experienced professional in innovation and entrepreneurship, leading initiatives to foster growth in the ocean sector.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Directly supports hypergrowth and founder transitions, making it an excellent match for Leslie''s advisory skills.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"OceanSync","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia","website":"https://oceansync.io/","estimated_size":25,"estimated_budget":"$1M-$5M","mission_focus":"Building marine data infrastructure for continuous ocean observation, providing real-time vessel data, edge computing, and advanced analytics for marine transportation, defence, and port operations.","why_fit":"Founded in 2020 by serial entrepreneurs, OceanSync is a growing startup in the crucial marine data sector. They are likely facing challenges typical of founder-led scaling, securing partnerships, and rapid product development during hypergrowth. Leslie''s experience would be highly relevant to their early growth phase.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Founded in 2020 by a team with entrepreneurial backgrounds, including a serial entrepreneur. Their rapid development of marine data infrastructure and securing leading shipping companies as clients point to founder-led scaling and hypergrowth.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Sebastiaan van der Par","contact_email":"info@oceansync.io","contact_position":"Co-Founder & CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/sebastiaanvanderpar/","contact_bio":"Serial entrepreneur with extensive experience in tech and big-data, now leading OceanSync in marine data solutions.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Early-stage, founder-led company in a hot sector, likely grappling with scaling and partnerships.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Marine Thinking","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia","website":"https://marinethinking.com/","estimated_size":30,"estimated_budget":"$1M-$5M","mission_focus":"Developing Uncrewed Surface Vessel (USV) solutions for hydrographic surveys, environmental monitoring, search and recovery, and marine technology automation.","why_fit":"As a growing company involved in cutting-edge USV technology, Marine Thinking is experiencing significant attention, including from government defence initiatives and high-level meetings. This signals hypergrowth, strategic partnerships, and challenges in scaling production and operations. Leslie''s expertise in scaling culture and cross-sector complexity (defence partnerships) would be highly relevant.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Recent news (February 2026) highlights their inclusion in a Government of Canada Defence Investment Initiative and meeting with the Prime Minister (March 2025), indicating strong government partnerships and rapid growth.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"WenWen Pei","contact_email":"info@marinethinking.com","contact_position":"CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/wenwen-pei-73a111166/","contact_bio":"Leader in marine autonomous systems, driving innovation for ocean data collection and applications.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"High-tech startup with significant government interest, indicating rapid growth and strategic partnership challenges.","budget_tier":"small"}]',15,0,'2026-03-23 07:16:35');
INSERT INTO discovery_runs VALUES(3,1,'Default search for Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada',unistr('You are a senior research analyst supporting a leadership advisor who is seeking a 6-8 week Entrepreneurship in Residence placement in Halifax, Nova Scotia. Your task is to find real, qualified ocean-focused organizations using web search.\u000a\u000aADVISOR BRIEF:\u000a- Geography: Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Search Radius: 15 miles\u000a- Placement Start: 2026-06-01\u000a- Placement Duration: 6-8 weeks\u000a- Focus Areas: Ocean health, Ocean economy, Ocean technology, Ocean infrastructure, Blue economy\u000a- Leadership Problems She Solves: Stuck partnerships, Alignment issues, Truth-telling gaps, Decision-making bottlenecks, Cross-sector complexity, Founder-to-CEO transitions, Scaling culture during hypergrowth\u000a- Non-Negotiables: No single-species operations (salmon-only, lobster-only, etc.), No freshwater organizations, Must have genuine ocean/marine focus\u000a- Win-Win-Win Criteria: Value for the organization, positive ocean outcomes, community benefits\u000a\u000aABOUT THE ADVISOR (LESLIE):\u000aNearly 20 years helping tech executives create happier teams, aligned outcomes, and stronger ROI. Now transitioning to ocean conservation / blue economy leadership advisory. Specializes in: stuck partnerships, alignment issues, truth-telling gaps, strategic knots. Works best 1:1 with senior leaders or with top teams on defined missions.\u000a- Works best 1:1 with senior leaders or with top teams on defined missions\u000a- Looking for a 6-8 week Entrepreneurship in Residence placement\u000a- Offering condensed senior advisory (equivalent of a year-long engagement in 2 months)\u000a- Best fit: organizations creating win-win-wins for corporations, nature, and future generations\u000a- Includes: for-profit companies, non-profits, NGOs, public-private partnerships, social enterprises, research institutions — any organization type\u000a\u000aGEOGRAPHY CONSTRAINT:\u000a- Primary location: Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Search radius: within 30 miles of Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Only include organizations headquartered or with major operations within this radius\u000a\u000aSEARCH TASK:\u000aFind ocean-focused organizations within 30 miles of Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada. Include ALL types: companies, non-profits, research institutions, NGOs, public-private partnerships, Crown corporations.\u000a\u000aHARD FILTERS — Qualitative Exclusions Only:\u000a- EXCLUDE: Any organization that operates exclusively on a single marine species (salmon-only farms, lobster harvesters, tuna fisheries, whale conservation, sea turtle rescue)\u000a- EXCLUDE: Any freshwater organization (lakes, rivers, freshwater fisheries)\u000a- EXCLUDE: ExxonMobil Canada, Shell Canada, SBM Offshore (enterprise-scale oil & gas — placement impractical)\u000a- Do NOT use the broad keyword ''offshore'' — use ''offshore wind'' only\u000a- Budget and headcount are NOT exclusion criteria — return all qualifying organizations regardless of size\u000a\u000aKEYWORD SEARCH STRATEGY — Two-Axis Search:\u000aSearch for organizations using ANY of these sector terms:\u000a\u000aPRIMARY (Sector Synonyms): ocean, marine, maritime, blue economy, oceanographic, offshore wind, subsea, coastal\u000a\u000aECONOMIC FRAMING: blue finance, ocean economy, marine commerce, ocean investment, investing in ocean, ocean-focused fund, marine investment, ocean venture, sustainable seafood investment, coastal economy investment, ocean-focused accelerator\u000a\u000aINFRASTRUCTURE & OPERATIONS: marine infrastructure, offshore wind operations, offshore wind development, shipbuilding, naval architecture, port authority, marine logistics, harbour management, underwater systems, marine engineering\u000a\u000aSCIENCE & DEEP TECHNOLOGY: ocean technology, oceanography, marine science, AUV, ROV, underwater acoustics, hydrography, bathymetry, ocean intelligence, marine sensing, seabed mapping, ocean data\u000a\u000aCONSERVATION & SUSTAINABILITY: ocean stewardship, marine conservation, ocean health, blue carbon, coastal resilience, marine protected areas, ocean sustainability, ocean governance\u000a\u000aGOVERNANCE & POLICY: marine spatial planning, ocean policy, coastal management, fisheries management (broad-mandate only), marine regulatory, EEZ\u000a\u000aFOOD SYSTEMS (handle with care — enforce single-species exclusion): aquaculture (multi-species only), mariculture, sustainable seafood, seafood supply chain, blue food\u000a\u000aALSO PRIORITIZE organizations showing these LEADERSHIP SIGNALS:\u000afounder-led scaling, hypergrowth, cross-sector partnership, strategic transition, joint venture, public-private partnership, multi-stakeholder, organizational alignment, board transition, scaling culture\u000a\u000aGEOGRAPHIC NOTE: Always pair economic/investment terms with Halifax, Nova Scotia, or Atlantic Canada.\u000a\u000aLEADERSHIP SIGNAL TIER INSTRUCTION:\u000aFor every organization returned, assess and report a leadership_signal_tier value:\u000a- Use ''confirmed'' if you found specific, dateable evidence of a leadership challenge (news article about rapid hiring, founder transition announcement, partnership press release, job posting for Chief People Officer, board change filing)\u000a- Use ''inferred'' if the org''s profile strongly implies a current leadership challenge without direct evidence (recent significant funding round, newly commercialized product, recently expanded government mandate, recent merger/restructure)\u000a- Use ''unknown'' if you could not find sufficient public information to assess leadership challenges\u000a\u000aCRITICAL DISTINCTION: ''unknown'' means the data does not exist to assess — it does NOT mean no leadership challenge exists. Low public profile ≠ no leadership challenge. Never conflate absence of data with absence of challenge. All three tiers are included in results; ''unknown'' is never an exclusion reason.\u000a\u000aFor ''unknown'' tier, set leadership_signal_evidence to: ''Insufficient public data to assess leadership challenges. Recommend direct outreach to verify organizational context before pursuing.''\u000a\u000aEXCLUSION RULES (reinforced):\u000a- No single-species operations: salmon-only, lobster-only, tuna-only, shrimp-only, whale conservation, sea turtle rescue\u000a- No freshwater organizations: lake research, river conservation, freshwater fisheries\u000a- No organizations outside 30 miles of Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Do NOT confuse ''no public data found'' with ''no leadership challenges detected''\u000a\u000aHALIFAX OCEAN ECOSYSTEM REFERENCE:\u000aCross-reference these known Nova Scotia ocean sector organizations when searching. Include them if they meet criteria, and search for additional qualifying organizations beyond this list:\u000a\u000aOCEAN TECH & SCIENCE:\u000a- Kraken Robotics — subsea technology, sonar, AUVs\u000a- Kongsberg Maritime Canada — maritime sensors and systems\u000a- GeoSpectrum Technologies — underwater acoustics\u000a- Innovasea — ocean tracking and aquaculture technology\u000a- JASCO Applied Sciences — ocean acoustics, environmental monitoring\u000a- AML Oceanographic — oceanographic instruments\u000a- Ultra Electronics Maritime Systems — defence and marine electronics\u000a- General Dynamics Canada — defence and ocean systems\u000a- Lockheed Martin Canada — defence, maritime surveillance\u000a- metOcean Telematics — ocean data buoys and telemetry\u000a- Fugro GeoSurveys — seabed mapping, geophysical survey\u000a- MDA (MacDonald Dettwiler) — satellite intelligence and earth observation\u000a- DSM Nutritional Products — marine ingredients/omega-3s\u000a- Acadian Seaplants — seaweed / marine agriculture\u000a- Ocean Sonics — hydrophones and marine acoustics\u000a- MacArtney Underwater Technology — underwater connectors and systems\u000a- CarteNav Solutions — maritime surveillance software\u000a- Deep Vision Inc. — underwater im