_budget":"$29.3B+ (federal contract)","mission_focus":"Design, construction, and maintenance of naval and Coast Guard vessels for the Canadian government, central to Canada''s National Shipbuilding Strategy.","why_fit":"Leslie''s expertise in scaling culture during hypergrowth and cross-sector complexity is highly relevant given Irving''s massive federal contracts, continuous modernization, and need to integrate diverse supply chains and a growing workforce. Their recent investment in a new shiplift and focus on future naval combatants implies ongoing strategic transitions.","keyword_category":"infra","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Significant investment of over $400 million in facilities modernization, ongoing construction of Arctic and Offshore Patrol Ships, and design for Canadian Surface Combatants indicates continuous large-scale project management and workforce scaling challenges. Also, a recent four-year, $789,000 initiative with Techsploration to support young women in skilled trades and STEM indicates a focus on workforce development and culture.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Kevin McCoy","contact_email":"info@irvingshipbuilding.com","contact_position":"President","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/irving-shipbuilding/","contact_bio":"Leads Canada''s largest shipbuilder responsible for major federal contracts.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Massive scale, confirmed hypergrowth/scaling challenges due to NSS contracts. Excellent fit for Leslie''s expertise in large-scale organizational alignment and cross-sector complexity.","budget_tier":"enterprise"},{"name":"Halifax Port Authority","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia","website":"https://www.portofhalifax.ca/","estimated_size":100,"estimated_budget":"$2B+ (economic impact annually)","mission_focus":"Manages and develops port facilities in Halifax Harbour, facilitating global trade, cargo, and cruise activity, and driving economic benefits for the region.","why_fit":"As a Crown corporation managing significant assets and driving substantial economic impact, the HPA faces ongoing challenges in strategic transitions (e.g., digitalization), multi-stakeholder engagement (global shipping lines, local community, government), and optimizing complex logistics. Leslie''s experience with stuck partnerships and decision-making bottlenecks would be valuable.","keyword_category":"infra","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Actively working to transform into a ''digital organization'' to handle industry changes, indicating strategic transition and technology integration challenges. Manages the PortControl digital operating system for port users. The port also recorded a significant container throughput increase in 2022.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Fulvio Fracassi","contact_email":"info@portofhalifax.ca","contact_position":"President & CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/halifax-port-authority/","contact_bio":"Leads the management and development of Canada''s major Atlantic port.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Crown corp, high economic impact, explicit digital transformation, and multi-stakeholder environment. Good fit for strategic transitions and complex partnerships.","budget_tier":"enterprise"},{"name":"Canada''s Ocean Supercluster (OSC)","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia","website":"https://oceansupercluster.ca/","estimated_size":"Small core team, supports hundreds of companies","estimated_budget":"$34.5M (in recent project announcements)","mission_focus":"Accelerating innovation and driving sustainable economic growth in Canada''s ocean economy by bringing together businesses, researchers, and innovators across various ocean sectors.","why_fit":"As a national, industry-led initiative aiming for 5X growth by 2035, OSC is inherently focused on scaling, cross-sector partnerships, and alignment across a vast network of stakeholders. Leslie''s expertise in scaling culture, strategic knots, and fostering win-win-wins is directly applicable to OSC''s mission of transforming the ocean economy.","keyword_category":"econ","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Announced $34.5 million in five new ocean innovation projects in December 2025. This significant investment and project pipeline demonstrates rapid growth and continuous need for strategic alignment and project management across diverse initiatives.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Kendra MacDonald","contact_email":"info@oceansupercluster.ca","contact_position":"CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/kendra-macdonald-p-eng-0b44b41/","contact_bio":"Leads Canada''s national ocean cluster, driving innovation and economic growth.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Highly relevant for scaling, cross-sector work, and strategic transitions. A core player in the blue economy. CEO is a clear target.","budget_tier":"mid"},{"name":"Innovasea","location":"Bedford, Nova Scotia","website":"https://innovasea.com/","estimated_size":100,"estimated_budget":"$4.8M+ (recent project funding)","mission_focus":"Providing aquaculture and ocean tracking solutions, including fish tracking, environmental monitoring, and AI-powered fish species identification for sustainable aquatic management.","why_fit":"Innovasea''s focus on innovative, AI-powered solutions for sustainable aquaculture and fish tracking indicates potential for rapid scaling and cross-sector partnerships (e.g., with energy companies for hydropower monitoring). Leslie''s skills in founder-to-CEO transitions (if applicable), strategic knots, and ensuring positive ocean outcomes are relevant for a tech company growing in a sensitive environmental sector.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Led the $4.8 million ''Species Aware Ocean AI Project'' announced in December 2025, in partnership with Canada''s Ocean Supercluster. This project involves expanding AI capabilities for automated fish species identification, demonstrating active innovation, growth, and complex project leadership.","lat":44.7167,"lng":-63.6264,"contact_name":"David Kelly","contact_email":"info@innovasea.com","contact_position":"CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/innovasea/","contact_bio":"Leads a global company in aquaculture and ocean tracking technology.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Confirmed large project funding, strong AI and sustainable ocean focus. Direct relevance for strategic transitions and scaling impact.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Marine Thinking","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia","website":"https://www.marinesense.com/","estimated_size":50,"estimated_budget":"$4.74M (recent project funding)","mission_focus":"Developing advanced AI-powered robotic platforms and vessel automation toolkits to revolutionize ship inspections and marine operations for efficiency and sustainability.","why_fit":"As a startup leading two significant projects supported by Canada''s Ocean Supercluster, Marine Thinking is likely in a hypergrowth phase, facing challenges related to founder-led scaling, cross-sector partnerships (e.g., with shipping and offshore energy), and strategic transitions from R&D to commercialization. Leslie''s expertise in these areas would be highly beneficial.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Leading the $940K ''Amphibian UWILD Remote Robotic Platform Project'' and the $3.8M ''AI-Powered Vessel Automation Toolkit Project,'' both supported by Canada''s Ocean Supercluster and announced in January 2025. This clearly indicates significant funding, rapid project development, and complex partnerships.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Unknown","contact_email":"info@marinesense.com","contact_position":"CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/marine-thinking/","contact_bio":"Focuses on developing AI and robotic solutions for marine operations.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Excellent example of founder-led scaling and hypergrowth in a deep tech ocean space. Strong leadership signal.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"COVE (Centre for Ocean Ventures & Entrepreneurship)","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://coveocean.com/","estimated_size":70,"estimated_budget":"Unknown (receives government funding, attracts private investment)","mission_focus":"A world-class hub for ocean technology innovation, fostering collaboration among startups, industry leaders, and researchers, and providing infrastructure for marine technology development and commercialization.","why_fit":"As an innovation hub experiencing rapid growth and hosting over 70 organizations, COVE is likely to face founder-to-CEO transitions as startups scale, alignment issues among diverse members, and challenges in scaling its own ''ecosystem culture'' during hypergrowth. Leslie''s experience in accelerators and fostering win-win-win scenarios for corporations and nature would be highly valuable here.","keyword_category":"econ","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Designated Canada''s first Defence Innovation Secure Hub (DISH) and leading new at-sea testing capabilities, indicating rapid expansion and strategic transitions. Hosts accelerator programs (Innovate UK Global Incubator Programme) and Demo Days, implying active support for scaling companies and associated leadership challenges.","lat":44.6644,"lng":-63.5583,"contact_name":"Melanie Nadeau","contact_email":"info@coveocean.com","contact_position":"CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/melanie-nadeau-84954714/","contact_bio":"Leads COVE, a global innovation centre for ocean technology, fostering entrepreneurship and industry collaboration.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Explicitly focused on innovation, startups, and scaling, making it a direct fit for founder challenges and hypergrowth culture. High visibility and active programs.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Bedford Institute of Oceanography (BIO)","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://www.dfo-mpo.gc.ca/science/facilities/bio-eng.html","estimated_size":600,"estimated_budget":"Unknown (Federal government funding)","mission_focus":"Canada''s largest federal center for multidisciplinary ocean research, focusing on aquatic, seafloor, and subsurface natural resources, environmental protection, and sustainable resource use.","why_fit":"As a large, multi-departmental government research facility, BIO likely deals with significant cross-sector complexity, alignment issues between different federal mandates (DFO, NRCan, Environment Canada, DND), and the challenge of translating scientific ''truth-telling'' into actionable policy and resource management. Leslie''s advisory skills would be highly relevant in enhancing inter-departmental collaboration and decision-making.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Ongoing multidisciplinary research across four federal departments (DFO, NRCan, EC, DND) and responding to complex issues like climate change and environmental emergencies implies continuous need for alignment and strategic direction across diverse teams. Research on the spread of radioactivity and impacts of ocean warming also indicates critical, complex problem-solving.","lat":44.6811,"lng":-63.5858,"contact_name":"F. David Zemeck","contact_email":"info@dfo-mpo.gc.ca","contact_position":"Director General (DFO Maritimes Region)","contact_linkedin":"N/A (Government)","contact_bio":"Leads a major federal ocean research institution with broad scientific mandates.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Government research institution, large staff, multidisciplinary. Strong fit for alignment, truth-telling, and cross-sector complexity. Official government contacts often generic.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Dalhousie University (Ocean Programs)","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia","website":"https://www.dal.ca/faculty/science/oceanography.html","estimated_size":"Large (university-wide, hundreds in ocean sector)","estimated_budget":"Unknown (part of university budget, external grants)","mission_focus":"Leading research and education in ocean science, technology, and governance through various institutes like the Ocean Frontier Institute (OFI) and the Ocean Tracking Network, contributing to a sustainable ocean economy.","why_fit":"Dalhousie''s role as a major research institution and host to multiple ocean-focused initiatives implies ongoing needs for strategic alignment across diverse projects, managing complex multi-stakeholder partnerships (e.g., with industry, government), and addressing truth-telling gaps in communicating scientific outcomes to policy. Leslie could help optimize these cross-sector collaborations and research-to-impact pathways.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Hosts the CDL-Atlantic Oceans Stream, supporting early-stage ocean companies, and is a key partner in Canada''s Ocean Supercluster, indicating active engagement in scaling innovation and managing a growing ecosystem.","lat":44.6366,"lng":-63.5925,"contact_name":"Chris Moore","contact_email":"chris.moore@dal.ca","contact_position":"Dean of Science","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/school/dalhousie-university/","contact_bio":"Oversees scientific research and education, including significant ocean programs.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Excellent academic research hub, involved in commercialization through CDL. Strong for cross-sector complexity, but contact might be more academic initially.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Kraken Robotics","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://krakenrobotics.com/","estimated_size":100,"estimated_budget":"Unknown (public company, multi-million revenue)","mission_focus":"Developing and commercializing advanced subsea technologies, including sonar, sensors, and autonomous underwater vehicles (AUVs) for various marine applications.","why_fit":"As a technology company operating in a rapidly evolving field, Kraken Robotics likely faces challenges associated with hypergrowth, new product commercialization, and potentially founder-to-CEO transitions or scaling internal culture. Leslie''s background in tech executive advisory and strategic knots would be highly valuable in optimizing their growth trajectory and market positioning.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Known for developing cutting-edge technologies like SeaVision® laser scanner and AquaPix® synthetic aperture sonar, implying continuous R&D and commercialization efforts. Frequently features in ocean tech news for new deployments and partnerships, suggesting ongoing scaling and integration challenges.","lat":44.6853,"lng":-63.5657,"contact_name":"Karl Kenny","contact_email":"info@krakenrobotics.com","contact_position":"President & CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/karlkenny/","contact_bio":"Veteran entrepreneur in ocean technology, leading Kraken Robotics'' growth and innovation.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Tech company with strong growth potential, active in innovation. Good fit for scaling culture and product commercialization.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"JASCO Applied Sciences","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://www.jasco.com/","estimated_size":50,"estimated_budget":"Unknown","mission_focus":"Specializes in underwater acoustics, providing services and systems for environmental monitoring, noise management, and marine mammal mitigation.","why_fit":"As an organization focused on highly technical and environmentally sensitive areas, JASCO likely navigates complex regulatory environments and cross-sector demands (e.g., oil & gas, defense, conservation). Leslie''s ability to solve ''truth-telling gaps'' and ''cross-sector complexity'' would be beneficial in translating scientific findings into clear advice and fostering effective partnerships for positive ocean outcomes.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Known for significant work in environmental impact assessments for marine projects and developing innovative acoustic monitoring systems, suggesting ongoing complex project management and the need for strategic growth in a niche market.","lat":44.6853,"lng":-63.5657,"contact_name":"Ken Collins","contact_email":"info@jasco.com","contact_position":"President","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/jasco-applied-sciences/","contact_bio":"Leads a global provider of underwater acoustic solutions and services.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Highly specialized technical company in a sensitive area. Good for truth-telling and cross-sector complexity.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"metOcean Telematics","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://metocean.com/","estimated_size":100,"estimated_budget":"Unknown","mission_focus":"Designs and manufactures state-of-the-art data acquisition and telemetry systems, including ocean data buoys, for global remote monitoring and tracking applications.","why_fit":"Operating in the cutting-edge field of ocean data and telemetry, metOcean Telematics likely experiences rapid product development cycles, scaling challenges with global deployments, and the need for strategic partnerships. Leslie''s experience with tech executives and strategic knots would be highly relevant in optimizing their market penetration and operational efficiencies.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Continuously developing and deploying new generations of ocean data buoys and Iridium-based telemetry systems for global clients, indicating ongoing R&D, manufacturing scaling, and international market expansion.","lat":44.6853,"lng":-63.5657,"contact_name":"Tony Healey","contact_email":"info@metocean.com","contact_position":"President & CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/metocean-telematics/","contact_bio":"Leads a company at the forefront of remote global communication and tracking solutions.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Tech company with global reach in a critical ocean data space. Good for scaling, strategic knots, and potentially founder-to-CEO aspects.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Ocean Technology Council of Nova Scotia (OTCNS)","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://otcns.ca/","estimated_size":"Small (association staff), Represents many companies","estimated_budget":"Unknown","mission_focus":"An industry association representing and advancing economic opportunities for Nova Scotia''s ocean technology sector, including SMEs delivering world-class advanced technologies and services.","why_fit":"As an industry association, OTCNS plays a crucial role in fostering alignment among its diverse member companies, advocating for the sector, and managing cross-sector complexity. Leslie''s experience in building happier teams and aligned outcomes across a collective of organizations would be highly valuable in enhancing the council''s strategic impact and member engagement.","keyword_category":"econ","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Actively involved in workforce development, supplier development events, and trade missions for its member SMEs. Partnerships with organizations like Discovery Centre for youth camps also show efforts in ecosystem building and future talent pipeline, indicating a broad mandate with ongoing strategic coordination challenges.","lat":44.6853,"lng":-63.5657,"contact_name":"Unknown","contact_email":"info@otcns.ca","contact_position":"Executive Director","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/ocean-technology-council-of-nova-scotia/","contact_bio":"Represents and promotes the ocean technology sector in Nova Scotia.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Industry association, good for understanding the broader ecosystem challenges and applying alignment skills to a network of companies.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"COINAtlantic (Coastal and Ocean Information Network Atlantic)","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia","website":"https://www.coinatlantic.ca/","estimated_size":10,"estimated_budget":"Unknown (NGO, project-based funding)","mission_focus":"A non-governmental organization dedicated to supporting coastal and marine spatial planning and decision-making through open data management and information sharing in Atlantic Canada.","why_fit":"COINAtlantic''s mission focuses on integrated ocean networks, open information exchange, and coastal & ocean collaborations, inherently involving ''truth-telling gaps'' and ''cross-sector complexity'' across diverse stakeholders. Leslie''s expertise in strategic knots and fostering alignment for positive ocean outcomes would be a strong match for enhancing their impact on sustainable ocean management and policy.","keyword_category":"gov","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Working across sectors for over 25 years to promote open data and information sharing, and involved in projects like ''Clean Coasts'' to understand blue carbon, indicating continuous efforts in complex, multi-stakeholder initiatives and the need for improved decision-making based on shared data.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Unknown","contact_email":"coinatlantic@dal.ca","contact_position":"Executive Director","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/coinatlantic/","contact_bio":"Leads an NGO focused on ocean data sharing and marine spatial planning.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"NGO with a clear mission in ocean governance and data. Strong for truth-telling, alignment, and community benefits. Might have a smaller budget/team.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Ultra Electronics Maritime Systems","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://www.ultra.group/our-businesses/maritime-systems/","estimated_size":500,"estimated_budget":"Unknown (multi-national corporation, significant contracts)","mission_focus":"Develops advanced maritime systems for surveillance, acoustic processing, and underwater warfare, primarily for defense and security applications.","why_fit":"As part of a large multi-national defense contractor, the Halifax-based Maritime Systems division likely deals with complex program management, strategic transitions (e.g., adapting to new defense contracts or technological shifts), and potential ''alignment issues'' within a large organizational structure. Leslie''s experience with senior leaders in tech and strategic knots would be valuable in optimizing their operational excellence and innovation pipeline.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"supplemental","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"As a major player in maritime defense and security, they are continuously involved in large-scale government contracts and R&D for advanced systems. Their presence in Nova Scotia''s defense cluster implies ongoing strategic importance and potential for growth/restructuring within that context.","lat":44.6853,"lng":-63.5657,"contact_name":"Unknown","contact_email":"info@ultra.group","contact_position":"Managing Director (Canada)","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/ultra-electronics-maritime-systems/","contact_bio":"Leads a defense contractor specializing in maritime systems.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Large, established company in defense tech. Less direct ''blue economy'' but highly relevant for ocean tech and complex programs. Potential for internal leadership challenges.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Horizon Maritime Services","location":"St. John''s, NL (with significant operations/presence in Halifax, NS)","website":"https://horizonmaritime.com/","estimated_size":200,"estimated_budget":"Unknown","mission_focus":"Provides offshore marine services, including vessel management, crew services, and offshore support for various industries.","why_fit":"Horizon Maritime, as an offshore marine services provider, operates in a demanding environment that requires strong operational alignment, effective decision-making, and potentially navigating ''stuck partnerships'' with clients or suppliers. Leslie''s focus on team alignment and decision-making bottlenecks would be valuable in enhancing their operational efficiency and strategic client engagements.","keyword_category":"infra","signal_strength":"supplemental","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"A growing player in offshore marine services, often involved in supporting diverse offshore projects. Their continuous expansion and involvement in new offshore contracts (e.g., wind, rather than just O&G) would indicate ongoing operational scaling and strategic management challenges.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Sean Leet","contact_email":"info@horizonmaritime.com","contact_position":"CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/horizon-maritime-services-ltd/","contact_bio":"Experienced leader in the offshore marine and energy sectors.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Important maritime services player. Good for operational alignment and decision-making in a complex industry. Ensure ocean focus is broad, not just O&G.","budget_tier":"small"}]',15,0,'2026-03-23 07:25:58');
INSERT INTO discovery_runs VALUES(5,1,'Default search for Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada',unistr('You are a senior research analyst supporting a leadership advisor who is seeking a 6-8 week Entrepreneurship in Residence placement in Halifax, Nova Scotia. Your task is to find real, qualified ocean-focused organizations using web search.\u000a\u000aADVISOR BRIEF:\u000a- Geography: Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Search Radius: 15 miles\u000a- Placement Start: 2026-06-01\u000a- Placement Duration: 6-8 weeks\u000a- Focus Areas: Ocean health, Ocean economy, Ocean technology, Ocean infrastructure, Blue economy\u000a- Leadership Problems She Solves: Stuck partnerships, Alignment issues, Truth-telling gaps, Decision-making bottlenecks, Cross-sector complexity, Founder-to-CEO transitions, Scaling culture during hypergrowth\u000a- Non-Negotiables: No single-species operations (salmon-only, lobster-only, etc.), No freshwater organizations, Must have genuine ocean/marine focus\u000a- Win-Win-Win Criteria: Value for the organization, positive ocean outcomes, community benefits\u000a\u000aABOUT THE ADVISOR (LESLIE):\u000aNearly 20 years helping tech executives create happier teams, aligned outcomes, and stronger ROI. Now transitioning to ocean conservation / blue economy leadership advisory. Specializes in: stuck partnerships, alignment issues, truth-telling gaps, strategic knots. Works best 1:1 with senior leaders or with top teams on defined missions.\u000a- Works best 1:1 with senior leaders or with top teams on defined missions\u000a- Looking for a 6-8 week Entrepreneurship in Residence placement\u000a- Offering condensed senior advisory (equivalent of a year-long engagement in 2 months)\u000a- Best fit: organizations creating win-win-wins for corporations, nature, and future generations\u000a- Includes: for-profit companies, non-profits, NGOs, public-private partnerships, social enterprises, research institutions — any organization type\u000a\u000aGEOGRAPHY CONSTRAINT:\u000a- Primary location: Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Search radius: within 15 miles of Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Only include organizations headquartered or with major operations within this radius\u000a\u000aSEARCH TASK:\u000aFind ocean-focused organizations within 15 miles of Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada. Include ALL types: companies, non-profits, research institutions, NGOs, public-private partnerships, Crown corporations.\u000a\u000aHARD FILTERS — Qualitative Exclusions Only:\u000a- EXCLUDE: Any organization that operates exclusively on a single marine species (salmon-only farms, lobster harvesters, tuna fisheries, whale conservation, sea turtle rescue)\u000a- EXCLUDE: Any freshwater organization (lakes, rivers, freshwater fisheries)\u000a- EXCLUDE: ExxonMobil Canada, Shell Canada, SBM Offshore (enterprise-scale oil & gas — placement impractical)\u000a- Do NOT use the broad keyword ''offshore'' — use ''offshore wind'' only\u000a- Budget and headcount are NOT exclusion criteria — return all qualifying organizations regardless of size\u000a\u000aKEYWORD SEARCH STRATEGY — Two-Axis Search:\u000aSearch for organizations using ANY of these sector terms:\u000a\u000aPRIMARY (Sector Synonyms): ocean, marine, maritime, blue economy, oceanographic, offshore wind, subsea, coastal\u000a\u000aECONOMIC FRAMING: blue finance, ocean economy, marine commerce, ocean investment, investing in ocean, ocean-focused fund, marine investment, ocean venture, sustainable seafood investment, coastal economy investment, ocean-focused accelerator\u000a\u000aINFRASTRUCTURE & OPERATIONS: marine infrastructure, offshore wind operations, offshore wind development, shipbuilding, naval architecture, port authority, marine logistics, harbour management, underwater systems, marine engineering\u000a\u000aSCIENCE & DEEP TECHNOLOGY: ocean technology, oceanography, marine science, AUV, ROV, underwater acoustics, hydrography, bathymetry, ocean intelligence, marine sensing, seabed mapping, ocean data\u000a\u000aCONSERVATION & SUSTAINABILITY: ocean stewardship, marine conservation, ocean health, blue carbon, coastal resilience, marine protected areas, ocean sustainability, ocean governance\u000a\u000aGOVERNANCE & POLICY: marine spatial planning, ocean policy, coastal management, fisheries management (broad-mandate only), marine regulatory, EEZ\u000a\u000aFOOD SYSTEMS (handle with care — enforce single-species exclusion): aquaculture (multi-species only), mariculture, sustainable seafood, seafood supply chain, blue food\u000a\u000aALSO PRIORITIZE organizations showing these LEADERSHIP SIGNALS:\u000afounder-led scaling, hypergrowth, cross-sector partnership, strategic transition, joint venture, public-private partnership, multi-stakeholder, organizational alignment, board transition, scaling culture\u000a\u000aGEOGRAPHIC NOTE: Always pair economic/investment terms with Halifax, Nova Scotia, or Atlantic Canada.\u000a\u000aLEADERSHIP SIGNAL TIER INSTRUCTION:\u000aFor every organization returned, assess and report a leadership_signal_tier value:\u000a- Use ''confirmed'' if you found specific, dateable evidence of a leadership challenge (news article about rapid hiring, founder transition announcement, partnership press release, job posting for Chief People Officer, board change filing)\u000a- Use ''inferred'' if the org''s profile strongly implies a current leadership challenge without direct evidence (recent significant funding round, newly commercialized product, recently expanded government mandate, recent merger/restructure)\u000a- Use ''unknown'' if you could not find sufficient public information to assess leadership challenges\u000a\u000aCRITICAL DISTINCTION: ''unknown'' means the data does not exist to assess — it does NOT mean no leadership challenge exists. Low public profile ≠ no leadership challenge. Never conflate absence of data with absence of challenge. All three tiers are included in results; ''unknown'' is never an exclusion reason.\u000a\u000aFor ''unknown'' tier, set leadership_signal_evidence to: ''Insufficient public data to assess leadership challenges. Recommend direct outreach to verify organizational context before pursuing.''\u000a\u000aEXCLUSION RULES (reinforced):\u000a- No single-species operations: salmon-only, lobster-only, tuna-only, shrimp-only, whale conservation, sea turtle rescue\u000a- No freshwater organizations: lake research, river conservation, freshwater fisheries\u000a- No organizations outside 15 miles of Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Do NOT confuse ''no public data found'' with ''no leadership challenges detected''\u000a\u000aHALIFAX OCEAN ECOSYSTEM REFERENCE:\u000aCross-reference these known Nova Scotia ocean sector organizations when searching. Include them if they meet criteria, and search for additional qualifying organizations beyond this list:\u000a\u000aOCEAN TECH & SCIENCE:\u000a- Kraken Robotics — subsea technology, sonar, AUVs\u000a- Kongsberg Maritime Canada — maritime sensors and systems\u000a- GeoSpectrum Technologies — underwater acoustics\u000a- Innovasea — ocean tracking and aquaculture technology\u000a- JASCO Applied Sciences — ocean acoustics, environmental monitoring\u000a- AML Oceanographic — oceanographic instruments\u000a- Ultra Electronics Maritime Systems — defence and marine electronics\u000a- General Dynamics Canada — defence and ocean systems\u000a- Lockheed Martin Canada — defence, maritime surveillance\u000a- metOcean Telematics — ocean data buoys and telemetry\u000a- Fugro GeoSurveys — seabed mapping, geophysical survey\u000a- MDA (MacDonald Dettwiler) — satellite intelligence and earth observation\u000a- DSM Nutritional Products — marine ingredients/omega-3s\u000a- Acadian Seaplants — seaweed / marine agriculture\u000a- Ocean Sonics — hydrophones and marine acoustics\u000a- MacArtney Underwater Technology — underwater connectors and systems\u000a- CarteNav Solutions — maritime surveillance software\u000a- Deep Vision Inc. — underwater imaging and inspection\u000a\u000aOCEAN INFRASTRUCTURE & ENERGY:\u000a- Irving Shipbuilding — federal shipbuilding ($29.3B contract), Halifax\u000a- Babcock Canada — naval engineering and ship lifecycle support\u000a- FORCE (Fundy Ocean Research Centre for Energy) — tidal energy R&D\u000a- SNC-Lavalin — engineering, ocean infrastructure projects\u000a- ABCO Industries — marine fabrication\u000a\u000aDO NOT PURSUE (out of scope):\u000a- SBM Offshore — oil & gas production systems; enterprise scale\u000a- ExxonMobil Canada — offshore oil & gas major\u000a- Shell Canada — offshore energy exploration\u000a\u000aTRANSPORTATION & LOGISTICS:\u000a- Port of Halifax / Halifax Port Authority — major Atlantic port\u000a- Halterm Container Terminal — port operations\u000a- Atlantic Towing — offshore marine services\u000a- Secunda Canada — offshore marine and oil field services\u000a- Horizon Maritime Services — offshore vessel support\u000a- Oceanex — marine shipping, Atlantic Canada\u000a\u000aFISHERIES (broad ocean operations only):\u000a- High Liner Foods — global seafood processing, HQ Lunenburg NS\u000a- Clearwater Seafoods — premium shellfish, national and international scale\u000a\u000aEDUCATION & RESEARCH:\u000a- Bedford Institute of Oceanography (BIO) — federal ocean research, Dartmouth NS\u000a- Dalhousie University — Faculty of Science, ocean/marine programs\u000a- DRDC Atlantic — Defence Research & Development Canada, maritime focus\u000a- National Research Council Canada (NRC) — ocean science and engineering\u000a- COVE (Centre for Ocean Ventures & Entrepreneurship) — Halifax ocean innovation hub\u000a\u000aNETWORKS & ASSOCIATIONS:\u000a- OTCNS (Ocean Technology Council of Nova Scotia)\u000a- Ocean Tracking Network — Dalhousie, global ocean monitoring\u000a- COINAtlantic — Coastal and Ocean Information Network Atlantic\u000a\u000aOUTPUT FORMAT:\u000aReturn your results as a JSON array with this exact structure. Include both organization fields AND lead contact fields:\u000a[\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Organization Name",\u000a    "location": "City, Province (or full address)",\u000a    "website": "https://...",\u000a    "estimated_size": 100,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$50M",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Brief description of their mission...",\u000a    "why_fit": "Why this org is a fit for the advisor...",\u000a    "keyword_category": "sector",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "confirmed",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Specific evidence found: recently announced...",\u000a    "lat": 44.6488,\u000a    "lng": -63.5752,\u000a    "contact_name": "Jane Smith",\u000a    "contact_email": "jsmith@org.com",\u000a    "contact_position": "CEO and Executive Director",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://linkedin.com/in/janesmith",\u000a    "contact_bio": "15 years in ocean technology, previously led...",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "Strong fit — $50M budget, ocean-wide mission, leadership transition underway"\u000a  }\u000a]\u000a\u000aFIELD NOTES:\u000a- keyword_category: one of "sector", "infra", "econ", "sci", "gov" — which cluster best describes this org\u000a- signal_strength: one of "high", "strong", "supplemental", "careful" — how strong a lead for Leslie\u000a- leadership_signal_tier: one of "confirmed", "inferred", "unknown" — evidence quality for leadership challenge\u000a- leadership_signal_evidence: 1-3 sentences describing specific evidence or standard ''insufficient data'' note\u000a- lat/lng: approximate coordinates for Halifax-area mapping (decimal degrees)\u000a- review_status: one of "Lead for Business", "Lead for Review", "Pending Review", "Do NOT Contact"\u000a\u000aCOUNT AND QUALITY:\u000aReturn between 10 and 15 results. Prefer verified organizations with web-searchable evidence over speculative results. Do not return fewer than 10 results. Distribute across all three signal tiers — do not exclude unknown-tier orgs to meet a count target. Sort by estimated budget (high to low) with signal tier as tiebreaker.\u000a\u000aReturn ONLY the JSON array, no other text.'),unistr('[\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Irving Shipbuilding",\u000a    "location": "Halifax, Nova Scotia",\u000a    "website": "https://www.irvingshipbuilding.com/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 2800,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$1.15B (2023 revenue)",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Irving Shipbuilding is the operator of Halifax Shipyard, a multi-billion dollar shipbuilding facility responsible for constructing Canada''s future naval combatant fleet under the National Shipbuilding Strategy.",\u000a    "why_fit": "Leslie''s expertise in strategic knots, decision-making bottlenecks, cross-sector complexity, and alignment issues would be invaluable for managing the immense scale and complexity of federal shipbuilding contracts, stakeholder engagement (government, suppliers, unions), and long-term project execution. The significant federal investment and ongoing projects indicate substantial leadership challenges in scaling and strategic execution.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "infra",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "inferred",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "The company is engaged in multi-billion dollar, multi-decade federal contracts (National Shipbuilding Strategy) which inherently involve complex project management, large-scale workforce scaling, intricate stakeholder alignment, and ongoing strategic adjustments. Recent governmental ''investments'' in facility modernization also point to ongoing strategic challenges and transitions.",\u000a    "lat": 44.6488,\u000a    "lng": -63.5752,\u000a    "contact_name": "Kevin McCoy",\u000a    "contact_email": "info@irvingshipbuilding.com",\u000a    "contact_position": "President",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/kevinmccoyirving/",\u000a    "contact_bio": "President of Irving Shipbuilding, leading Canada''s National Shipbuilding Strategy projects, with extensive experience in defense and naval operations.",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "Massive government contracts present continuous leadership challenges in project management, stakeholder alignment, and scaling. High potential for Leslie''s expertise."\u000a  },\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Kraken Robotics",\u000a    "location": "Dartmouth, Nova Scotia",\u000a    "website": "https://krakenrobotics.com/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 150,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$91.3M (2024 revenue)",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Kraken Robotics specializes in cutting-edge subsea technology, including sonar systems, marine robotics (AUVs), and subsea batteries, for defense, commercial, and scientific applications.",\u000a    "why_fit": "Kraken''s rapid growth, global expansion, and focus on acquiring new technologies (like PanGeo Subsea) suggest ongoing challenges in scaling culture, integrating partnerships, and managing hypergrowth. Leslie''s expertise in founder-led scaling and cross-sector complexity would be highly relevant.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "sci",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "confirmed",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Reported 70% revenue increase in 2023 over 2022, with a strong outlook for 2024 projecting revenue between $90M-$100M. The company''s sales pipeline exceeds $900M, indicating hypergrowth and the need for scaling and strategic execution. Recent acquisitions further confirm integration challenges.",\u000a    "lat": 44.6738,\u000a    "lng": -63.5413,\u000a    "contact_name": "Greg Reid",\u000a    "contact_email": "info@krakenrobotics.com",\u000a    "contact_position": "President and CEO",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/gregreidkrakenrobotics/",\u000a    "contact_bio": "Greg Reid leads Kraken Robotics, driving innovation and growth in subsea technology. He has a strong background in tech leadership and business development.",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "High growth tech company with confirmed acquisitions and significant contracts; excellent fit for scaling culture and integration advisory."\u000a  },\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Dalhousie University - Ocean Frontier Institute (OFI)",\u000a    "location": "Halifax, Nova Scotia",\u000a    "website": "https://oceanfrontierinstitute.com/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 500,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$400M+ (total activated funding for current initiative)",\u000a    "mission_focus": "The Ocean Frontier Institute (OFI) is a collaborative research institute focused on understanding and sustaining the North Atlantic Ocean, addressing global challenges like climate change, ocean health, and sustainable ocean resource management.",\u000a    "why_fit": "OFI, as a multi-institutional and international collaboration, inherently faces complex cross-sector partnerships, alignment issues among diverse stakeholders (academia, government, industry, Indigenous communities), and strategic knots in driving large-scale research initiatives. Leslie''s skills would directly apply to optimizing these collaborations and scaling impact.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "sci",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "confirmed",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Received a $154M Canada First Research Excellence Fund (CFREF) grant in April 2023, activating nearly $400M in total funding for the ''Transforming Climate Action'' initiative. This massive investment indicates a significant strategic transition and expansion, requiring complex multi-stakeholder and cross-sector alignment.",\u000a    "lat": 44.6366,\u000a    "lng": -63.5902,\u000a    "contact_name": "Dr. Anya Waite",\u000a    "contact_email": "ofi@dal.ca",\u000a    "contact_position": "Scientific Director and CEO",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/anyawaite/",\u000a    "contact_bio": "Dr. Waite is a globally recognized oceanographer and leader in ocean science, guiding OFI''s strategic direction and fostering international collaborations.",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "Massive new funding and a highly collaborative structure indicate confirmed leadership challenges in alignment, partnerships, and strategic scaling."\u000a  },\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Clearwater Seafoods",\u000a    "location": "Bedford, Nova Scotia",\u000a    "website": "https://www.clearwater.ca/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 1900,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$500M+ (estimated annual revenue)",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Clearwater Seafoods is a leading producer of wild-caught, premium seafood, committed to sustainable harvesting and processing of various shellfish species for global markets.",\u000a    "why_fit": "The recent acquisition by a First Nation coalition and Premium Brands Holdings Corporation in 2021 marks a significant strategic transition and ownership change. This would present considerable leadership challenges in post-acquisition integration, cultural alignment, and managing new governance structures, all areas where Leslie excels.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "blue food",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "confirmed",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Acquired by a partnership between Premium Brands Holdings Corporation and a Mi''kmaq First Nation coalition in January 2021. This substantial ownership change and integration would require significant leadership in managing strategic transition and cultural alignment.",\u000a    "lat": 44.7171,\u000a    "lng": -63.6396,\u000a    "contact_name": "Ian D. Smith",\u000a    "contact_email": "info@clearwater.ca",\u000a    "contact_position": "Chief Executive Officer",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/iansmithclearwater/",\u000a    "contact_bio": "Ian D. Smith leads Clearwater Seafoods, guiding its operations and strategic direction as a global leader in premium, wild-caught seafood.",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "Recent major acquisition creates confirmed challenges in integration, strategic alignment, and culture, fitting Leslie''s expertise perfectly."\u000a  },\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "COVE (Centre for Ocean Ventures & Entrepreneurship)",\u000a    "location": "Dartmouth, Nova Scotia",\u000a    "website": "https://www.coveocean.com/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 100,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$10M+ (annual operating budget/funding)",\u000a    "mission_focus": "COVE is an ocean technology innovation hub that supports the commercialization of ocean technologies and the growth of the blue economy by fostering collaboration between industry, academia, and government.",\u000a    "why_fit": "As a hub for startups and growing companies, COVE continuously deals with founder-to-CEO transitions, scaling culture, and forging cross-sector partnerships. Leslie''s advisory on strategic knots and alignment issues would directly benefit COVE and its member organizations.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "econ",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "inferred",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "As an innovation hub, COVE''s core mission involves supporting rapid growth, scaling startups, and fostering complex public-private-academic partnerships, inherently implying ongoing leadership challenges related to hypergrowth and cross-sector complexity. The investment by Irving Shipbuilding in COVE further underscores its role in industry growth.",\u000a    "lat": 44.6738,\u000a    "lng": -63.5413,\u000a    "contact_name": "Melanie Nadeau",\u000a    "contact_email": "info@coveocean.com",\u000a    "contact_position": "CEO",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/melanienadeau/",\u000a    "contact_bio": "Melanie Nadeau leads COVE, driving the growth of the ocean technology sector in Nova Scotia and fostering innovation and entrepreneurship.",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "Excellent opportunity to impact multiple founder-led ventures and address systemic scaling challenges within the ocean tech ecosystem."\u000a  },\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "MetOcean Telematics",\u000a    "location": "Dartmouth, Nova Scotia",\u000a    "website": "https://www.metocean.com/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 100,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$25M+ (estimated annual revenue)",\u000a    "mission_focus": "MetOcean Telematics designs and manufactures state-of-the-art data acquisition and end-to-end telematics solutions, with a focus on niche MetOcean solutions and custom Defence and Security products.",\u000a    "why_fit": "MetOcean''s history of strategic acquisitions and continuous innovation in satellite communications and ocean data solutions indicates ongoing strategic transitions, integration challenges, and the need for scaling culture. Leslie''s expertise in strategic knots and alignment issues would be very valuable.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "sci",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "confirmed",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Acquired the Nautics Group in September 2022 and OmniCom vessel management systems in July 2021, and was itself acquired by OTS in 2024. These frequent acquisitions and its own acquisition confirm significant strategic transition, integration, and potential alignment challenges.",\u000a    "lat": 44.6738,\u000a    "lng": -63.5413,\u000a    "contact_name": "Tony Chedrawy",\u000a    "contact_email": "sales@metocean.com",\u000a    "contact_position": "CEO",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/tony-chedrawy-7132a41a/",\u000a    "contact_bio": "Tony Chedrawy leads MetOcean Telematics, driving innovation in satellite communications and ocean technology through strategic growth and acquisitions.",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "Confirmed M&A activity means ongoing strategic transitions and integration challenges, an ideal fit for Leslie''s skills."\u000a  },\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Halifax Port Authority",\u000a    "location": "Halifax, Nova Scotia",\u000a    "website": "https://portofhalifax.ca/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 100,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$70M+ (annual revenue)",\u000a    "mission_focus": "The Port of Halifax is a major international gateway and economic engine for Atlantic Canada, facilitating global trade, cruise operations, and responsible stewardship of Halifax Harbour.",\u000a    "why_fit": "As a Crown corporation managing significant infrastructure, the Port faces ongoing challenges in strategic alignment with various stakeholders (government, shipping lines, local community), managing large capital projects (expansion, modernization), and navigating cross-sector complexity (logistics, environment, tourism). Leslie''s expertise in decision-making bottlenecks and multi-stakeholder engagement would be highly valuable.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "infra",\u000a    "signal_strength": "strong",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "inferred",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Continuous large-scale infrastructure projects (e.g., expansion plans to handle increased cargo and cruise traffic by 2070) and ongoing digital transformation initiatives, as detailed in their annual reports, imply significant strategic transitions and the need for complex multi-stakeholder coordination and decision-making.",\u000a    "lat": 44.6406,\u000a    "lng": -63.5683,\u000a    "contact_name": "Captain Allan Gray",\u000a    "contact_email": "info@portofhalifax.ca",\u000a    "contact_position": "President and CEO",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/captainallangray/",\u000a    "contact_bio": "Captain Allan Gray leads the Halifax Port Authority, overseeing strategic