pertise in strategic knots and founder-led scaling would be beneficial.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"supplemental","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Announced expansion to over 62,000 square feet and increased staff to over 150 employees in June 2022 due to ''sheer volume of sales from the global market'' and ''multiple international defence contracts''. This indicates significant growth and scaling challenges.","lat":44.6738,"lng":-63.5413,"contact_name":"Paul Yeatman","contact_email":"info@geospectrum.ca","contact_position":"President","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/paul-yeatman-934a36b/","contact_bio":"Paul Yeatman leads GeoSpectrum Technologies, a key innovator in underwater acoustics for defence and oceanographic applications.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Confirmed growth and expansion indicate scaling challenges, good for Leslie''s expertise in founder-led growth and strategic knots.","budget_tier":"mid"},{"name":"Bedford Institute of Oceanography (BIO)","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://www.dfo-mpo.gc.ca/science/facilities-installations/bio-eng.html","estimated_size":600,"estimated_budget":"$50M+ (estimated annual funding)","mission_focus":"BIO is Canada''s largest centre for ocean research, conducting extensive scientific studies on oceanography, fisheries, marine ecosystems, and hydrography to inform policy and resource management.","why_fit":"As a large federal research institution, BIO likely faces challenges in cross-sector complexity (collaborating with diverse government departments, academia, international partners, and industry), optimizing research priorities, and ensuring strategic alignment across its various scientific programs. Recent infrastructure investments indicate strategic developments.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Recent opening of the Facility for Intelligent Marine Systems (FIMS) in May 2024, a $25 million investment at BIO, signifies a major strategic initiative to foster collaboration among DFO, DND, and NRCan researchers, indicating confirmed needs for cross-sector alignment and partnership optimization.","lat":44.6738,"lng":-63.5413,"contact_name":"Mary-Lynn Dickson","contact_email":"info@dfo-mpo.gc.ca","contact_position":"Director General, DFO Science Atlantic Region","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/mary-lynn-dickson-080183b1/","contact_bio":"Mary-Lynn Dickson is a senior leader within Fisheries and Oceans Canada, overseeing the scientific research and operations at the Bedford Institute of Oceanography.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Recent large investment in new facility implies confirmed needs for managing inter-departmental collaboration and strategic alignment.","budget_tier":"mid"},{"name":"Innovasea","location":"Bedford, Nova Scotia","website":"https://www.innovasea.com/","estimated_size":200,"estimated_budget":"$50M+ (estimated annual revenue)","mission_focus":"Innovasea provides innovative technology solutions for sustainable aquaculture and ocean tracking, focusing on improving fish health, operational efficiency, and environmental outcomes.","why_fit":"Innovasea''s growth through mergers (e.g., merging to form Innovasea in 2018) and its continued expansion in aquaculture and ocean technology indicate ongoing strategic transitions, integration challenges, and the need for scaling culture during hypergrowth. Leslie''s expertise in these areas would be highly valuable.","keyword_category":"blue economy","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Formed through the merger of multiple companies (e.g., merging with Realtime Aquaculture and Vaki in 2018 to form Innovasea), which confirms significant past strategic transitions and integration challenges. Continuous innovation and global expansion in a rapidly evolving sector imply ongoing needs for leadership in alignment and scaling.","lat":44.7171,"lng":-63.6396,"contact_name":"David Kelly","contact_email":"info@innovasea.com","contact_position":"CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/davidpkelly/","contact_bio":"David Kelly leads Innovasea, a company at the forefront of sustainable aquaculture and ocean technology, driving innovation and global growth.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Confirmed history of mergers suggests ongoing integration and scaling challenges, good fit for Leslie''s expertise.","budget_tier":"mid"},{"name":"Acadian Seaplants","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://acadianseaplants.com/","estimated_size":400,"estimated_budget":"$50M+ (estimated annual revenue)","mission_focus":"Acadian Seaplants is a fully integrated manufacturer of seaweed-based products for agricultural, food, and animal feed markets, committed to sustainable marine aquaculture and innovation.","why_fit":"As a global leader in a niche but growing blue economy sector, Acadian Seaplants likely faces challenges related to scaling operations, entering new international markets, managing supply chain complexity, and continuous product innovation. Leslie''s experience with scaling culture, strategic knots, and cross-sector complexity (global markets, sustainability) would be highly relevant.","keyword_category":"blue economy","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"As a long-standing global leader in sustainable marine plant biotechnology, continuous expansion into new product lines and international markets (as evidenced by their global presence and diverse product applications) suggests ongoing strategic development and the need for scaling and alignment within a founder-led company.","lat":44.6738,"lng":-63.5413,"contact_name":"Jean-Paul Deveau","contact_email":"info@acadianseaplants.com","contact_position":"President & CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/jeanpauldeveau/","contact_bio":"Jean-Paul Deveau leads Acadian Seaplants, a global pioneer in seaweed-based solutions, with a strong focus on innovation and sustainability.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Established global leader with continuous growth, suggesting ongoing strategic and scaling challenges, good fit for Leslie''s expertise.","budget_tier":"mid"},{"name":"MetOcean Telematics","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://www.metocean.com/","estimated_size":100,"estimated_budget":"$25M+ (estimated annual revenue)","mission_focus":"MetOcean Telematics designs and manufactures state-of-the-art data acquisition and end-to-end telematics solutions, with a focus on niche MetOcean solutions and custom Defence and Security products.","why_fit":"MetOcean''s history of strategic acquisitions and continuous innovation in satellite communications and ocean data solutions indicates ongoing strategic transitions, integration challenges, and the need for scaling culture. Leslie''s expertise in strategic knots and alignment issues would be very valuable.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Acquired the Nautics Group in September 2022 and OmniCom vessel management systems in July 2021, and was itself acquired by OTS in 2024. These frequent acquisitions and its own acquisition confirm significant strategic transition, integration, and potential alignment challenges.","lat":44.6738,"lng":-63.5413,"contact_name":"Tony Chedrawy","contact_email":"sales@metocean.com","contact_position":"CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/tony-chedrawy-7132a41a/","contact_bio":"Tony Chedrawy leads MetOcean Telematics, driving innovation in satellite communications and ocean technology through strategic growth and acquisitions.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Confirmed M&A activity means ongoing strategic transitions and integration challenges, an ideal fit for Leslie''s skills.","budget_tier":"mid"},{"name":"CarteNav Solutions Inc.","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia","website":"https://cartenav.com/","estimated_size":90,"estimated_budget":"$18.8M (estimated annual revenue)","mission_focus":"CarteNav Solutions provides mission system software for intelligence, surveillance, and reconnaissance (ISR) operations across maritime, land, and air environments for defense and security clients globally.","why_fit":"CarteNav''s global reach and specialized software development for complex ISR missions suggest ongoing needs for strategic partnerships, decision-making optimization in high-stakes environments, and potential founder-led scaling. Leslie''s skills in strategic knots and cross-sector complexity are relevant.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"supplemental","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Acquired by PAL Aerospace (part of Exchange Income Corporation) in 2016, indicating a significant strategic transition and integration. Continuous global contracts for specialized ISR software imply ongoing growth and the need for strategic management and scaling.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Spencer Fraser","contact_email":"info@cartenav.com","contact_position":"CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/spencer-fraser-88390b17/","contact_bio":"Spencer Fraser leads CarteNav Solutions, driving innovation in maritime surveillance software for global defense and security.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Acquisition history suggests strategic transition; ongoing global contracts imply growth and operational complexity, a good match for Leslie''s skills.","budget_tier":"small_mid"},{"name":"Deep Vision Inc.","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia","website":"https://deepvision.ca/","estimated_size":20,"estimated_budget":"$1-5M (estimated annual revenue)","mission_focus":"Deep Vision Inc. provides innovative underwater imaging and inspection solutions, leveraging advanced technology for marine research, infrastructure monitoring, and environmental assessment.","why_fit":"As a growing tech startup, Deep Vision Inc. is likely navigating founder-led scaling, securing funding, and expanding its market reach. Leslie''s expertise in founder-to-CEO transitions, scaling culture, and strategic knots would be highly valuable for a company in this growth phase.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"supplemental","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"As a technology startup focused on underwater imaging, Deep Vision Inc. is in a growth phase, as evidenced by its specialized offerings and innovation in the field. This implies inherent leadership challenges related to founder-led scaling, securing funding, and market penetration.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Alastair Cook","contact_email":"info@deepvision.ca","contact_position":"CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/alastair-cook-09b9172/","contact_bio":"Alastair Cook is the CEO of Deep Vision Inc., leading the development and application of advanced underwater imaging technologies.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Startup growth phase offers opportunities for Leslie to advise on founder-led scaling and strategic direction.","budget_tier":"small_mid"}]',15,0,'2026-03-23 07:34:56');
INSERT INTO discovery_runs VALUES(6,1,'Default search for Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada',unistr('You are a senior research analyst supporting a leadership advisor who is seeking a 6-8 week Entrepreneurship in Residence placement in Halifax, Nova Scotia. Your task is to find real, qualified ocean-focused organizations using web search.\u000a\u000aADVISOR BRIEF:\u000a- Geography: Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Search Radius: 15 miles\u000a- Placement Start: 2026-06-01\u000a- Placement Duration: 6-8 weeks\u000a- Focus Areas: Ocean health, Ocean economy, Ocean technology, Ocean infrastructure, Blue economy\u000a- Leadership Problems She Solves: Stuck partnerships, Alignment issues, Truth-telling gaps, Decision-making bottlenecks, Cross-sector complexity, Founder-to-CEO transitions, Scaling culture during hypergrowth\u000a- Non-Negotiables: No single-species operations (salmon-only, lobster-only, etc.), No freshwater organizations, Must have genuine ocean/marine focus\u000a- Win-Win-Win Criteria: Value for the organization, positive ocean outcomes, community benefits\u000a\u000aABOUT THE ADVISOR (LESLIE):\u000aNearly 20 years helping tech executives create happier teams, aligned outcomes, and stronger ROI. Now transitioning to ocean conservation / blue economy leadership advisory. Specializes in: stuck partnerships, alignment issues, truth-telling gaps, strategic knots. Works best 1:1 with senior leaders or with top teams on defined missions.\u000a- Works best 1:1 with senior leaders or with top teams on defined missions\u000a- Looking for a 6-8 week Entrepreneurship in Residence placement\u000a- Offering condensed senior advisory (equivalent of a year-long engagement in 2 months)\u000a- Best fit: organizations creating win-win-wins for corporations, nature, and future generations\u000a- Includes: for-profit companies, non-profits, NGOs, public-private partnerships, social enterprises, research institutions — any organization type\u000a\u000aGEOGRAPHY CONSTRAINT:\u000a- Primary location: Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Search radius: within 15 miles of Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Only include organizations headquartered or with major operations within this radius\u000a\u000aSEARCH TASK:\u000aFind ocean-focused organizations within 15 miles of Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada. Include ALL types: companies, non-profits, research institutions, NGOs, public-private partnerships, Crown corporations.\u000a\u000aHARD FILTERS — Qualitative Exclusions Only:\u000a- EXCLUDE: Any organization that operates exclusively on a single marine species (salmon-only farms, lobster harvesters, tuna fisheries, whale conservation, sea turtle rescue)\u000a- EXCLUDE: Any freshwater organization (lakes, rivers, freshwater fisheries)\u000a- EXCLUDE: ExxonMobil Canada, Shell Canada, SBM Offshore (enterprise-scale oil & gas — placement impractical)\u000a- Do NOT use the broad keyword ''offshore'' — use ''offshore wind'' only\u000a- Budget and headcount are NOT exclusion criteria — return all qualifying organizations regardless of size\u000a\u000aKEYWORD SEARCH STRATEGY — Two-Axis Search:\u000aSearch for organizations using ANY of these sector terms:\u000a\u000aPRIMARY (Sector Synonyms): ocean, marine, maritime, blue economy, oceanographic, offshore wind, subsea, coastal\u000a\u000aECONOMIC FRAMING: blue finance, ocean economy, marine commerce, ocean investment, investing in ocean, ocean-focused fund, marine investment, ocean venture, sustainable seafood investment, coastal economy investment, ocean-focused accelerator\u000a\u000aINFRASTRUCTURE & OPERATIONS: marine infrastructure, offshore wind operations, offshore wind development, shipbuilding, naval architecture, port authority, marine logistics, harbour management, underwater systems, marine engineering\u000a\u000aSCIENCE & DEEP TECHNOLOGY: ocean technology, oceanography, marine science, AUV, ROV, underwater acoustics, hydrography, bathymetry, ocean intelligence, marine sensing, seabed mapping, ocean data\u000a\u000aCONSERVATION & SUSTAINABILITY: ocean stewardship, marine conservation, ocean health, blue carbon, coastal resilience, marine protected areas, ocean sustainability, ocean governance\u000a\u000aGOVERNANCE & POLICY: marine spatial planning, ocean policy, coastal management, fisheries management (broad-mandate only), marine regulatory, EEZ\u000a\u000aFOOD SYSTEMS (handle with care — enforce single-species exclusion): aquaculture (multi-species only), mariculture, sustainable seafood, seafood supply chain, blue food\u000a\u000aALSO PRIORITIZE organizations showing these LEADERSHIP SIGNALS:\u000afounder-led scaling, hypergrowth, cross-sector partnership, strategic transition, joint venture, public-private partnership, multi-stakeholder, organizational alignment, board transition, scaling culture\u000a\u000aGEOGRAPHIC NOTE: Always pair economic/investment terms with Halifax, Nova Scotia, or Atlantic Canada.\u000a\u000aLEADERSHIP SIGNAL TIER INSTRUCTION:\u000aFor every organization returned, assess and report a leadership_signal_tier value:\u000a- Use ''confirmed'' if you found specific, dateable evidence of a leadership challenge (news article about rapid hiring, founder transition announcement, partnership press release, job posting for Chief People Officer, board change filing)\u000a- Use ''inferred'' if the org''s profile strongly implies a current leadership challenge without direct evidence (recent significant funding round, newly commercialized product, recently expanded government mandate, recent merger/restructure)\u000a- Use ''unknown'' if you could not find sufficient public information to assess leadership challenges\u000a\u000aCRITICAL DISTINCTION: ''unknown'' means the data does not exist to assess — it does NOT mean no leadership challenge exists. Low public profile ≠ no leadership challenge. Never conflate absence of data with absence of challenge. All three tiers are included in results; ''unknown'' is never an exclusion reason.\u000a\u000aFor ''unknown'' tier, set leadership_signal_evidence to: ''Insufficient public data to assess leadership challenges. Recommend direct outreach to verify organizational context before pursuing.''\u000a\u000aEXCLUSION RULES (reinforced):\u000a- No single-species operations: salmon-only, lobster-only, tuna-only, shrimp-only, whale conservation, sea turtle rescue\u000a- No freshwater organizations: lake research, river conservation, freshwater fisheries\u000a- No organizations outside 15 miles of Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Do NOT confuse ''no public data found'' with ''no leadership challenges detected''\u000a\u000aHALIFAX OCEAN ECOSYSTEM REFERENCE:\u000aCross-reference these known Nova Scotia ocean sector organizations when searching. Include them if they meet criteria, and search for additional qualifying organizations beyond this list:\u000a\u000aOCEAN TECH & SCIENCE:\u000a- Kraken Robotics — subsea technology, sonar, AUVs\u000a- Kongsberg Maritime Canada — maritime sensors and systems\u000a- GeoSpectrum Technologies — underwater acoustics\u000a- Innovasea — ocean tracking and aquaculture technology\u000a- JASCO Applied Sciences — ocean acoustics, environmental monitoring\u000a- AML Oceanographic — oceanographic instruments\u000a- Ultra Electronics Maritime Systems — defence and marine electronics\u000a- General Dynamics Canada — defence and ocean systems\u000a- Lockheed Martin Canada — defence, maritime surveillance\u000a- metOcean Telematics — ocean data buoys and telemetry\u000a- Fugro GeoSurveys — seabed mapping, geophysical survey\u000a- MDA (MacDonald Dettwiler) — satellite intelligence and earth observation\u000a- DSM Nutritional Products — marine ingredients/omega-3s\u000a- Acadian Seaplants — seaweed / marine agriculture\u000a- Ocean Sonics — hydrophones and marine acoustics\u000a- MacArtney Underwater Technology — underwater connectors and systems\u000a- CarteNav Solutions — maritime surveillance software\u000a- Deep Vision Inc. — underwater imaging and inspection\u000a\u000aOCEAN INFRASTRUCTURE & ENERGY:\u000a- Irving Shipbuilding — federal shipbuilding ($29.3B contract), Halifax\u000a- Babcock Canada — naval engineering and ship lifecycle support\u000a- FORCE (Fundy Ocean Research Centre for Energy) — tidal energy R&D\u000a- SNC-Lavalin — engineering, ocean infrastructure projects\u000a- ABCO Industries — marine fabrication\u000a\u000aDO NOT PURSUE (out of scope):\u000a- SBM Offshore — oil & gas production systems; enterprise scale\u000a- ExxonMobil Canada — offshore oil & gas major\u000a- Shell Canada — offshore energy exploration\u000a\u000aTRANSPORTATION & LOGISTICS:\u000a- Port of Halifax / Halifax Port Authority — major Atlantic port\u000a- Halterm Container Terminal — port operations\u000a- Atlantic Towing — offshore marine services\u000a- Secunda Canada — offshore marine and oil field services\u000a- Horizon Maritime Services — offshore vessel support\u000a- Oceanex — marine shipping, Atlantic Canada\u000a\u000aFISHERIES (broad ocean operations only):\u000a- High Liner Foods — global seafood processing, HQ Lunenburg NS\u000a- Clearwater Seafoods — premium shellfish, national and international scale\u000a\u000aEDUCATION & RESEARCH:\u000a- Bedford Institute of Oceanography (BIO) — federal ocean research, Dartmouth NS\u000a- Dalhousie University — Faculty of Science, ocean/marine programs\u000a- DRDC Atlantic — Defence Research & Development Canada, maritime focus\u000a- National Research Council Canada (NRC) — ocean science and engineering\u000a- COVE (Centre for Ocean Ventures & Entrepreneurship) — Halifax ocean innovation hub\u000a\u000aNETWORKS & ASSOCIATIONS:\u000a- OTCNS (Ocean Technology Council of Nova Scotia)\u000a- Ocean Tracking Network — Dalhousie, global ocean monitoring\u000a- COINAtlantic — Coastal and Ocean Information Network Atlantic\u000a\u000aOUTPUT FORMAT:\u000aReturn your results as a JSON array with this exact structure. Include both organization fields AND lead contact fields:\u000a[\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Organization Name",\u000a    "location": "City, Province (or full address)",\u000a    "website": "https://...",\u000a    "estimated_size": 100,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$50M",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Brief description of their mission...",\u000a    "why_fit": "Why this org is a fit for the advisor...",\u000a    "keyword_category": "sector",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "confirmed",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Specific evidence found: recently announced...",\u000a    "lat": 44.6488,\u000a    "lng": -63.5752,\u000a    "contact_name": "Jane Smith",\u000a    "contact_email": "jsmith@org.com",\u000a    "contact_position": "CEO and Executive Director",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://linkedin.com/in/janesmith",\u000a    "contact_bio": "15 years in ocean technology, previously led...",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "Strong fit — $50M budget, ocean-wide mission, leadership transition underway"\u000a  }\u000a]\u000a\u000aFIELD NOTES:\u000a- keyword_category: one of "sector", "infra", "econ", "sci", "gov" — which cluster best describes this org\u000a- signal_strength: one of "high", "strong", "supplemental", "careful" — how strong a lead for Leslie\u000a- leadership_signal_tier: one of "confirmed", "inferred", "unknown" — evidence quality for leadership challenge\u000a- leadership_signal_evidence: 1-3 sentences describing specific evidence or standard ''insufficient data'' note\u000a- lat/lng: approximate coordinates for Halifax-area mapping (decimal degrees)\u000a- review_status: one of "Lead for Business", "Lead for Review", "Pending Review", "Do NOT Contact"\u000a\u000aCOUNT AND QUALITY:\u000aReturn between 10 and 15 results. Prefer verified organizations with web-searchable evidence over speculative results. Do not return fewer than 10 results. Distribute across all three signal tiers — do not exclude unknown-tier orgs to meet a count target. Sort by estimated budget (high to low) with signal tier as tiebreaker.\u000a\u000aReturn ONLY the JSON array, no other text.'),unistr('```json\u000a[\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Halifax Port Authority",\u000a    "location": "Halifax, Nova Scotia",\u000a    "website": "https://www.portofhalifax.ca/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 100,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "Hundreds of millions (operational revenue & infrastructure investment)",\u000a    "mission_focus": "To drive economic growth by connecting Atlantic Canada to global cargo shipping and cruise industries, while being sustainable, safe, reliable, and efficient. Focus on strategic infrastructure development and community collaboration.",\u000a    "why_fit": "Leslie''s expertise in strategic knots, decision-making bottlenecks, and cross-sector complexity is highly relevant given HPA''s long-term strategic planning, recent executive leadership transitions, and emphasis on stakeholder and community engagement. The ''One Port City'' approach and 50-year plan indicate significant strategic initiatives.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "infra",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "confirmed",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Fulvio Fracassi was appointed President and CEO in September 2024, following an international search. Two new executive leaders (VP, Talent and Communications; General Counsel and Corporate Secretary) joined in June/July 2025. The HPA also released a comprehensive 50-Year Plan in June 2022, indicating ongoing strategic development and potential for decision-making bottlenecks and alignment issues as new leadership implements this long-term vision.",\u000a    "lat": 44.6488,\u000a    "lng": -63.5752,\u000a    "contact_name": "Fulvio Fracassi",\u000a    "contact_email": "info@portofhalifax.ca (general inquiry, specific not public)",\u000a    "contact_position": "President & CEO",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/fulv