ocation":"Halifax, Nova Scotia","website":"https://www.marinethinking.com/","estimated_size":"11-50","estimated_budget":"$4M+ (recent federal investment)","mission_focus":"Develops uncrewed surface vessels (USVs) and advanced marine technology for hydrographic surveys, environmental monitoring, and marine research.","why_fit":"Received significant federal investment (February 2026) for scaling operations, adopting advanced technologies, and expanding its workforce. This signals hypergrowth and strategic transitions, making it an ideal candidate for advisory on founder-led scaling and decision-making bottlenecks.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Received federal investment of over $4 million in February 2026 under the Regional Defence Investment Initiative (RDII) to scale up operations, develop technologies, and expand its workforce. This is strong evidence of hypergrowth and strategic transitions.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Xueming Sheng","contact_email":"info@marinethinking.com","contact_position":"Chief Executive Officer","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/marine-thinking","contact_bio":"Leads Marine Thinking in developing cutting-edge autonomous marine solutions for diverse applications.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Fast-growing startup with confirmed recent funding and a clear growth mandate, offering significant advisory opportunities in scaling and strategic execution.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Global Spatial Technology Solutions (GSTS)","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://gsts.ca/","estimated_size":"51-200","estimated_budget":"Multi-millions (recent federal investment)","mission_focus":"Provides AI-powered marine intelligence and maritime surveillance solutions to enhance safety, security, and operational efficiency in the maritime domain.","why_fit":"Received federal investment (March 2026) to expand operations and workforce, indicating a period of significant growth and strategic scaling. As a leader in AI-driven solutions, they likely face challenges in rapid technology integration, market penetration, and organizational alignment during hypergrowth.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Received federal investment in March 2026 to scale up operations, boost production capacity, and expand its workforce, explicitly signaling hypergrowth and strategic transitions as it responds to growing market demand for its AI-powered solutions.","lat":44.6853,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Richard W. Myers","contact_email":"info@gsts.ca","contact_position":"Chief Executive Officer","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/richardwmyers","contact_bio":"Leads GSTS in delivering advanced marine intelligence solutions leveraging AI and big data.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"AI-focused tech company with recent confirmed funding for growth, creating a clear opportunity for advisory on scaling and market strategy.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Maritime Launch Services Inc.","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia (corporate office)","website":"https://maritimelaunch.com/","estimated_size":"50-100","estimated_budget":"Publicly Traded (significant capital raised)","mission_focus":"Developing Spaceport Nova Scotia as a launch site for commercial and government satellites, offering orbital launch services to the global space economy.","why_fit":"Announced an interim finance leadership team in March 2026 to support its ''next phase of growth'' and ''modernize and streamline existing systems and processes to support disciplined growth and operational readiness.'' This signals a clear strategic transition and scaling challenge within a high-growth, founder-led environment.","keyword_category":"infra","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Announced the appointment of an interim finance leadership team in March 2026 to support the company''s ''next phase of growth'' and ''modernize and streamline existing systems and processes.'' This explicitly indicates a strategic transition, scaling challenges, and a focus on operational readiness for a rapidly developing company.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Stephen Matier","contact_email":"info@maritimelaunch.com","contact_position":"President & CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/stephen-matier-886008b","contact_bio":"Founder and leader driving the development of Canada''s first commercial spaceport.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"High-growth, founder-led company with clear, recent leadership transitions and scaling needs, offering a unique intersection of space and blue economy.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Dalhousie University (Ocean/Marine Programs)","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia","website":"https://www.dal.ca/faculty/science/ocean-sciences.html","estimated_size":"2,000+ (faculty/staff in relevant departments)","estimated_budget":"Multi-millions (research grants)","mission_focus":"A leading academic institution with extensive research and educational programs in oceanography, marine science, marine biology, and ocean technology, fostering innovation and conservation.","why_fit":"Engages in complex multi-stakeholder partnerships (e.g., Ocean Frontier Institute, Ocean Tracking Network, CDL-Atlantic Oceans Stream) and continuous strategic planning for research funding, talent development, and industry collaboration. Ideal for addressing alignment issues and cross-sector complexity in a research-heavy environment.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"As a major research institution, Dalhousie continually forms new cross-sector partnerships with industry and government (e.g., in defence, ocean tech) and manages numerous complex, multi-stakeholder initiatives like the Ocean Tracking Network. This environment inherently presents challenges in organizational alignment and strategic decision-making.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Dr. Alice Aiken","contact_email":"vpr@dal.ca","contact_position":"Vice President Research","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/alice-aiken","contact_bio":"Oversees the university''s research portfolio, including significant ocean-related initiatives and partnerships.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"A large, complex academic setting with constant multi-stakeholder projects, offering rich ground for advisory on collaboration and strategic alignment.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Bedford Institute of Oceanography (BIO)","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia","website":"https://www.dfo-mpo.gc.ca/science/facilities-installations/bio-eng.html","estimated_size":"600+ (scientists, engineers, technicians)","estimated_budget":"Hundreds of millions (federal research budget)","mission_focus":"Canada''s largest centre for ocean research, housing federal departments conducting research in oceanography, hydrography, fisheries, and marine geosciences.","why_fit":"As a large federal scientific institution, BIO constantly navigates evolving research priorities, inter-departmental alignment, resource allocation, and external partnerships. The scale and breadth of its mandate imply ongoing strategic, alignment, and decision-making challenges for leadership.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"As a vast federal research institution, BIO operates with complex mandates across multiple government departments (Fisheries and Oceans Canada, Natural Resources Canada), requiring continuous strategic alignment, resource management, and negotiation of diverse research priorities. This infers ongoing leadership challenges related to internal coordination and external partnerships.","lat":44.6997,"lng":-63.5684,"contact_name":"Mary-Anne Gough","contact_email":"mary-anne.gough@dfo-mpo.gc.ca","contact_position":"Regional Director of Science (Maritimes Region)","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/mary-anne-gough-47754316","contact_bio":"Responsible for scientific activities and programs within DFO''s Maritimes Region, including research conducted at BIO.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"A major federal research hub; advisory could focus on inter-agency alignment, strategic science communication, or optimizing research outcomes.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Horizon Maritime Services Ltd.","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia (operations)","website":"https://horizonmaritime.com/","estimated_size":"200-500","estimated_budget":"Multi-millions","mission_focus":"Provides diverse marine services, including offshore vessels, crewing, tugs, barges, vessel management, and logistics, operating in challenging environments globally.","why_fit":"Engaged in joint ventures with First Nations (e.g., Miawpukek Horizon Maritime Services) and other partnerships (e.g., Genoa Design International), indicating complex cross-sector and multi-stakeholder dynamics. Their continuous expansion and diversification into various marine sectors present ongoing scaling and alignment challenges.","keyword_category":"infra","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Horizon Maritime is actively engaged in strategic joint ventures with First Nations (e.g., Miawpukek Horizon Maritime Services) and has recently entered a new partnership with Membertou First Nation and Horizon Naval Engineering Partnership (January 2026), indicating ongoing cross-sector complexity and strategic transitions.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Sean Leet","contact_email":"info@horizonmaritime.com","contact_position":"Chief Executive Officer","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/sean-leet-5858088","contact_bio":"Co-founder and CEO, leading a rapidly growing marine services company with a focus on partnerships and diversification.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Strong potential for advisory on partnership management, cultural integration in JVs, and scaling operational complexity.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Acadian Seaplants Limited","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia (R&D/operations)","website":"https://acadianseaplants.com/","estimated_size":"500-1000","estimated_budget":"Multi-millions","mission_focus":"A fully integrated manufacturer of seaweed-based products for food, animal feed, and agricultural applications, committed to sustainable harvesting and innovation in marine biotechnology.","why_fit":"A founder-led company with global operations, continuously innovating and expanding into new markets. Likely faces challenges in scaling culture, managing international partnerships, and navigating strategic transitions as it grows and diversifies its product lines.","keyword_category":"food","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"As a global, founder-led company, Acadian Seaplants is continuously engaged in innovation, product diversification, and international market expansion, inferring ongoing leadership challenges related to scaling global operations, managing complex supply chains, and fostering an innovative culture.","lat":44.6853,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Jean-Paul Deveau","contact_email":"info@acadianseaplants.com","contact_position":"President & CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/jeanpauldeveau","contact_bio":"Second-generation leader of a global marine plant biotechnology company, focused on sustainability and innovation.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Founder-led, global company with a sustainability focus. Potential for advising on global scaling, innovation management, and internal alignment.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Innovasea","location":"Bedford, Nova Scotia","website":"https://innovasea.com/","estimated_size":"200-500","estimated_budget":"Multi-millions","mission_focus":"Provides innovative aquaculture technology and ocean tracking solutions to advance sustainable seafood production and marine research.","why_fit":"As a global leader in aquaculture technology, Innovasea is constantly pushing for innovation and sustainable practices. This implies ongoing strategic challenges in product development, market expansion, and maintaining alignment in a rapidly evolving sector with high demands for environmental responsibility. Their focus on multi-species aquaculture aligns with the advisor''s non-negotiables.","keyword_category":"food","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Innovasea is a global technology company operating in a rapidly evolving sector (sustainable aquaculture) which requires continuous innovation, market adaptation, and strategic partnerships. This infers ongoing leadership challenges related to driving new product commercialization, global expansion, and maintaining organizational agility in a competitive, environmentally sensitive industry.","lat":44.7162,"lng":-63.6805,"contact_name":"David Kelly","contact_email":"info@innovasea.com","contact_position":"Chief Executive Officer","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/david-kelly-innovasea","contact_bio":"Leads Innovasea in delivering cutting-edge technology for sustainable aquaculture and ocean intelligence.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Strong fit in sustainable aquaculture, a growing sector with constant innovation and market challenges, providing ample advisory opportunities.","budget_tier":"small"}]',15,0,'2026-03-23 07:42:59');
INSERT INTO discovery_runs VALUES(8,1,'Default search for Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada',unistr('You are a senior research analyst supporting a leadership advisor who is seeking a 6-8 week Entrepreneurship in Residence placement in Halifax, Nova Scotia. Your task is to find real, qualified ocean-focused organizations using web search.\u000a\u000aADVISOR BRIEF:\u000a- Geography: Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Search Radius: 15 miles\u000a- Placement Start: 2026-06-01\u000a- Placement Duration: 6-8 weeks\u000a- Focus Areas: Ocean health, Ocean economy, Ocean technology, Ocean infrastructure, Blue economy\u000a- Leadership Problems She Solves: Stuck partnerships, Alignment issues, Truth-telling gaps, Decision-making bottlenecks, Cross-sector complexity, Founder-to-CEO transitions, Scaling culture during hypergrowth\u000a- Non-Negotiables: No single-species operations (salmon-only, lobster-only, etc.), No freshwater organizations, Must have genuine ocean/marine focus\u000a- Win-Win-Win Criteria: Value for the organization, positive ocean outcomes, community benefits\u000a\u000aABOUT THE ADVISOR (LESLIE):\u000aNearly 20 years helping tech executives create happier teams, aligned outcomes, and stronger ROI. Now transitioning to ocean conservation / blue economy leadership advisory. Specializes in: stuck partnerships, alignment issues, truth-telling gaps, strategic knots. Works best 1:1 with senior leaders or with top teams on defined missions.\u000a- Works best 1:1 with senior leaders or with top teams on defined missions\u000a- Looking for a 6-8 week Entrepreneurship in Residence placement\u000a- Offering condensed senior advisory (equivalent of a year-long engagement in 2 months)\u000a- Best fit: organizations creating win-win-wins for corporations, nature, and future generations\u000a- Includes: for-profit companies, non-profits, NGOs, public-private partnerships, social enterprises, research institutions — any organization type\u000a\u000aGEOGRAPHY CONSTRAINT:\u000a- Primary location: Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Search radius: within 15 miles of Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Only include organizations headquartered or with major operations within this radius\u000a\u000aSEARCH TASK:\u000aFind ocean-focused organizations within 15 miles of Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada. Include ALL types: companies, non-profits, research institutions, NGOs, public-private partnerships, Crown corporations.\u000a\u000aHARD FILTERS — Qualitative Exclusions Only:\u000a- EXCLUDE: Any organization that operates exclusively on a single marine species (salmon-only farms, lobster harvesters, tuna fisheries, whale conservation, sea turtle rescue)\u000a- EXCLUDE: Any freshwater organization (lakes, rivers, freshwater fisheries)\u000a- EXCLUDE: ExxonMobil Canada, Shell Canada, SBM Offshore (enterprise-scale oil & gas — placement impractical)\u000a- Do NOT use the broad keyword ''offshore'' — use ''offshore wind'' only\u000a- Budget and headcount are NOT exclusion criteria — return all qualifying organizations regardless of size\u000a\u000aKEYWORD SEARCH STRATEGY — Two-Axis Search:\u000aSearch for organizations using ANY of these sector terms:\u000a\u000aPRIMARY (Sector Synonyms): ocean, marine, maritime, blue economy, oceanographic, offshore wind, subsea, coastal\u000a\u000aECONOMIC FRAMING: blue finance, ocean economy, marine commerce, ocean investment, investing in ocean, ocean-focused fund, marine investment, ocean venture, sustainable seafood investment, coastal economy investment, ocean-focused accelerator\u000a\u000aINFRASTRUCTURE & OPERATIONS: marine infrastructure, offshore wind operations, offshore wind development, shipbuilding, naval architecture, port authority, marine logistics, harbour management, underwater systems, marine engineering\u000a\u000aSCIENCE & DEEP TECHNOLOGY: ocean technology, oceanography, marine science, AUV, ROV, underwater acoustics, hydrography, bathymetry, ocean intelligence, marine sensing, seabed mapping, ocean data\u000a\u000aCONSERVATION & SUSTAINABILITY: ocean stewardship, marine conservation, ocean health, blue carbon, coastal resilience, marine protected areas, ocean sustainability, ocean governance\u000a\u000aGOVERNANCE & POLICY: marine spatial planning, ocean policy, coastal management, fisheries management (broad-mandate only), marine regulatory, EEZ\u000a\u000aFOOD SYSTEMS (handle with care — enforce single-species exclusion): aquaculture (multi-species only), mariculture, sustainable seafood, seafood supply chain, blue food\u000a\u000aALSO PRIORITIZE organizations showing these LEADERSHIP SIGNALS:\u000afounder-led scaling, hypergrowth, cross-sector partnership, strategic transition, joint venture, public-private partnership, multi-stakeholder, organizational alignment, board transition, scaling culture\u000a\u000aGEOGRAPHIC NOTE: Always pair economic/investment terms with Halifax, Nova Scotia, or Atlantic Canada.\u000a\u000aLEADERSHIP SIGNAL TIER INSTRUCTION:\u000aFor every organization returned, assess and report a leadership_signal_tier value:\u000a- Use ''confirmed'' if you found specific, dateable evidence of a leadership challenge (news article about rapid hiring, founder transition announcement, partnership press release, job posting for Chief People Officer, board change filing)\u000a- Use ''inferred'' if the org''s profile strongly implies a current leadership challenge without direct evidence (recent significant funding round, newly commercialized product, recently expanded government mandate, recent merger/restructure)\u000a- Use ''unknown'' if you could not find sufficient public information to assess leadership challenges\u000a\u000aCRITICAL DISTINCTION: ''unknown'' means the data does not exist to assess — it does NOT mean no leadership challenge exists. Low public profile ≠ no leadership challenge. Never conflate absence of data with absence of challenge. All three tiers are included in results; ''unknown'' is never an exclusion reason.\u000a\u000aFor ''unknown'' tier, set leadership_signal_evidence to: ''Insufficient public data to assess leadership challenges. Recommend direct outreach to verify organizational context before pursuing.''\u000a\u000aEXCLUSION RULES (reinforced):\u000a- No single-species operations: salmon-only, lobster-only, tuna-only, shrimp-only, whale conservation, sea turtle rescue\u000a- No freshwater organizations: lake research, river conservation, freshwater fisheries\u000a- No organizations outside 15 miles of Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada\u000a- Do NOT confuse ''no public data found'' with ''no leadership challenges detected''\u000a\u000aHALIFAX OCEAN ECOSYSTEM REFERENCE:\u000aCross-reference these known Nova Scotia ocean sector organizations when searching. Include them if they meet criteria, and search for additional qualifying organizations beyond this list:\u000a\u000aOCEAN TECH & SCIENCE:\u000a- Kraken Robotics — subsea technology, sonar, AUVs\u000a- Kongsberg Maritime Canada — maritime sensors and systems\u000a- GeoSpectrum Technologies — underwater acoustics\u000a- Innovasea — ocean tracking and aquaculture technology\u000a- JASCO Applied Sciences — ocean acoustics, environmental monitoring\u000a- AML Oceanographic — oceanographic instruments\u000a- Ultra Electronics Maritime Systems — defence and marine electronics\u000a- General Dynamics Canada — defence and ocean systems\u000a- Lockheed Martin Canada — defence, maritime surveillance\u000a- metOcean Telematics — ocean data buoys and telemetry\u000a- Fugro GeoSurveys — seabed mapping, geophysical survey\u000a- MDA (MacDonald Dettwiler) — satellite intelligence and earth observation\u000a- DSM Nutritional Products — marine ingredients/omega-3s\u000a- Acadian Seaplants — seaweed / marine agriculture\u000a- Ocean Sonics — hydrophones and marine acoustics\u000a- MacArtney Underwater Technology — underwater connectors and systems\u000a- CarteNav Solutions — maritime surveillance software\u000a- Deep Vision Inc. — underwater imaging and inspection\u000a\u000aOCEAN INFRASTRUCTURE & ENERGY:\u000a- Irving Shipbuilding — federal shipbuilding ($29.3B contract), Halifax\u000a- Babcock Canada — naval engineering and ship lifecycle support\u000a- FORCE (Fundy Ocean Research Centre for Energy) — tidal energy R&D\u000a- SNC-Lavalin — engineering, ocean infrastructure projects\u000a- ABCO Industries — marine fabrication\u000a\u000aDO NOT PURSUE (out of scope):\u000a- SBM Offshore — oil & gas production systems; enterprise scale\u000a- ExxonMobil Canada — offshore oil & gas major\u000a- Shell Canada — offshore energy exploration\u000a\u000aTRANSPORTATION & LOGISTICS:\u000a- Port of Halifax / Halifax Port Authority — major Atlantic port\u000a- Halterm Container Terminal — port operations\u000a- Atlantic Towing — offshore marine services\u000a- Secunda Canada — offshore marine and oil field services\u000a- Horizon Maritime Services — offshore vessel support\u000a- Oceanex — marine shipping, Atlantic Canada\u000a\u000aFISHERIES (broad ocean operations only):\u000a- High Liner Foods — global seafood processing, HQ Lunenburg NS\u000a- Clearwater Seafoods — premium shellfish, national and international scale\u000a\u000aEDUCATION & RESEARCH:\u000a- Bedford Institute of Oceanography (BIO) — federal ocean research, Dartmouth NS\u000a- Dalhousie University — Faculty of Science, ocean/marine programs\u000a- DRDC Atlantic — Defence Research & Development Canada, maritime focus\u000a- National Research Council Canada (NRC) — ocean science and engineering\u000a- COVE (Centre for Ocean Ventures & Entrepreneurship) — Halifax ocean innovation hub\u000a\u000aNETWORKS & ASSOCIATIONS:\u000a- OTCNS (Ocean Technology Council of Nova Scotia)\u000a- Ocean Tracking Network — Dalhousie, global ocean monitoring\u000a- COINAtlantic — Coastal and Ocean Information Network Atlantic\u000a\u000aOUTPUT FORMAT:\u000aReturn your results as a JSON array with this exact structure. Include both organization fields AND lead contact fields