 meet a count target. Sort by estimated budget (high to low) with signal tier as tiebreaker.\u000a\u000aReturn ONLY the JSON array, no other text.'),unistr('```json\u000a[\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Kraken Robotics Inc.",\u000a    "location": "Dartmouth, Nova Scotia, Canada",\u000a    "website": "https://krakenrobotics.com/",\u000a    "estimated_size": "Large (300+ employees)",\u000a    "estimated_budget": "Multi-million CAD (2025 estimated combined revenue $351M-$379M)",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Transforming subsea intelligence through 3D imaging sensors, power solutions, and robotic systems for defense, offshore energy, and scientific exploration.",\u000a    "why_fit": "Experiencing hypergrowth and strategic expansion, evidenced by recent large defence orders, strategic acquisitions, and the launch of a new Nova Scotia manufacturing facility. These dynamics often lead to challenges in scaling culture, integrating new entities, and managing cross-sector complexity.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "sci",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "confirmed",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Announced strategic acquisition of Covelya Group Limited in March 2026, expected to close Q2 2026. Recent additions to leadership team include Bernard Mills as EVP Defence and Terra Penrose as Chief People Officer. A new Nova Scotia manufacturing facility is coming online in the next month (March/April 2026).",\u000a    "lat": 44.6859,\u000a    "lng": -63.5714,\u000a    "contact_name": "Greg Reid",\u000a    "contact_email": "greg.reid@krakenrobotics.com",\u000a    "contact_position": "President and CEO",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/gregreidkraken/",\u000a    "contact_bio": "N/A",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "Very strong fit with recent acquisition, leadership changes, and facility expansion, indicating significant organizational challenges."\u000a  },\u000a  {\u00