":"Large (300+ employees)","estimated_budget":"Multi-million CAD (2025 estimated combined revenue $351M-$379M)","mission_focus":"Transforming subsea intelligence through 3D imaging sensors, power solutions, and robotic systems for defense, offshore energy, and scientific exploration.","why_fit":"Experiencing hypergrowth and strategic expansion, evidenced by recent large defence orders, strategic acquisitions, and the launch of a new Nova Scotia manufacturing facility. These dynamics often lead to challenges in scaling culture, integrating new entities, and managing cross-sector complexity.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Announced strategic acquisition of Covelya Group Limited in March 2026, expected to close Q2 2026. Recent additions to leadership team include Bernard Mills as EVP Defence and Terra Penrose as Chief People Officer. A new Nova Scotia manufacturing facility is coming online in the next month (March/April 2026).","lat":44.6859,"lng":-63.5714,"contact_name":"Greg Reid","contact_email":"greg.reid@krakenrobotics.com","contact_position":"President and CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/gregreidkraken/","contact_bio":"N/A","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Very strong fit with recent acquisition, leadership changes, and facility expansion, indicating significant organizational challenges.","budget_tier":"enterprise"},{"name":"Halifax Port Authority","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada","website":"https://www.portofhalifax.ca/","estimated_size":"Large (100-500 employees)","estimated_budget":"Multi-million CAD (annual economic impact $2 billion)","mission_focus":"Manages and operates the Port of Halifax, facilitating trade, promoting economic development, and ensuring efficient and sustainable marine transportation.","why_fit":"Experienced significant leadership transitions with a new President and CEO appointed in September 2024, followed by two new executive leaders in June 2025. This indicates an organization undergoing strategic change, likely facing alignment issues and decision-making bottlenecks related to its future direction, digital transformation, and decarbonization goals.","keyword_category":"infra","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Fulvio Fracassi assumed the role of President and CEO in September 2024. Leanne Dixon joined as Vice President, Talent and Communications, and Heidi Schedler as General Counsel & Corporate Secretary in June 2025. These are clear, dateable leadership transitions.","lat":44.636,"lng":-63.551,"contact_name":"Fulvio Fracassi","contact_email":"fulvio.fracassi@portofhalifax.ca","contact_position":"President and CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/fulvio-fracassi/","contact_bio":"Seasoned CEO and senior executive with extensive experience in the marine industry and public sector.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Multiple recent leadership changes and ongoing strategic initiatives make this a very strong lead for addressing organizational alignment and strategic transition.","budget_tier":"enterprise"},{"name":"Innovasea","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada","website":"https://www.innovasea.com/","estimated_size":"Medium to Large (250+ employees globally)","estimated_budget":"Multi-million USD","mission_focus":"Provides complete end-to-end solutions for sustainable open-ocean aquaculture and fish tracking, including advanced sensor technology, fish-tracking systems, and farm management software.","why_fit":"Underwent a major rebranding and formalized an expanded leadership team in March 2026, indicating a strategic transition and potential for alignment issues during growth. Their growth, often through acquisition, also presents integration challenges.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Unveiled updated brand and formalized expanded senior leadership team in March 2026. Mark Jollymore was named permanent CEO in November 2025, replacing an interim CEO. Amy Brookman was promoted to General Manager of Fish Tracking in January 2026, and Marc Turano was appointed GM of Aquaculture Systems in 2025.","lat":44.6488,"lng":-63.5752,"contact_name":"Mark Jollymore","contact_email":"mark.jollymore@innovasea.com","contact_position":"CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/mark-jollymore-3b5a1b32/","contact_bio":"Joined Innovasea in 2017 following the acquisition of Amirix Systems, served as President of Fish Tracking Operations before becoming CEO.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Excellent fit with recent leadership changes, rebranding, and ongoing growth, directly aligning with Leslie''s expertise in transitions and alignment.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"JASCO Applied Sciences (Canada) Ltd.","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia, Canada","website":"https://www.jasco.com/","estimated_size":"Medium (50-200 employees)","estimated_budget":"Multi-million CAD","mission_focus":"Provides ocean acoustics, environmental monitoring, and marine mammal detection solutions through passive acoustic monitoring systems, modeling, and data analysis.","why_fit":"Demonstrates strategic growth through recent acquisitions, indicating potential integration challenges. Active participation in international defense and environmental projects highlights cross-sector complexity and multi-stakeholder coordination needs.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Acquired Cryosphere Innovation and Autonomous Marine Systems Inc. in 2024. Actively involved in NATO''s Robotic Experimentation and Prototyping with Maritime Unmanned Systems (REPMUS) exercise in 2025. Scott Carr is CEO.","lat":44.6859,"lng":-63.5714,"contact_name":"Scott Carr","contact_email":"scott.carr@jasco.com","contact_position":"CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/scott-carr-jasco/","contact_bio":"N/A","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Multiple acquisitions and involvement in major international projects present clear leadership challenges related to integration and cross-sector complexity.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"PSA Halifax","location":"Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada","website":"https://www.psahalifax.ca/","estimated_size":"Medium (50-200 employees)","estimated_budget":"Multi-million CAD (part of global PSA International)","mission_focus":"Operates Eastern Canada''s largest container terminal, handling mega-container vessels and facilitating global trade through the Port of Halifax.","why_fit":"Underwent a strategic transition and rebranding in 2019 after being acquired by PSA International. Continues to expand its berth capacity, indicating ongoing operational scaling and potential for decision-making bottlenecks or alignment issues in large infrastructure projects.","keyword_category":"infra","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Acquired by PSA International and rebranded from Halterm Container Terminal to PSA Halifax in late 2019. The terminal is undergoing further berth expansion for mega-container vessels. Hector Macleod is current General Manager.","lat":44.6291,"lng":-63.5658,"contact_name":"Hector Macleod","contact_email":"hector.macleod@globalpsa.com","contact_position":"General Manager","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/hector-macleod-1b931b26/","contact_bio":"N/A","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Recent acquisition and ongoing infrastructure projects indicate clear strategic and operational challenges related to growth and integration.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"COVE (Centre for Ocean Ventures & Entrepreneurship)","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia, Canada","website":"https://coveocean.com/","estimated_size":"Small to Medium (20-50 employees for core team; hosts many startups)","estimated_budget":"Multi-million CAD (grant and partnership funded)","mission_focus":"An ocean technology park that fosters collaboration, innovation, and commercialization among ocean sector companies, researchers, and startups.","why_fit":"As an innovation hub, COVE is inherently involved in supporting numerous organizations through founder-led scaling, strategic transitions, and cross-sector partnerships. Its role in nurturing startups means it constantly navigates decision-making bottlenecks and alignment issues within a multi-stakeholder ecosystem.","keyword_category":"econ","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"As a hub for ocean technology startups and innovation, COVE''s mandate directly involves supporting organizations through founder-to-CEO transitions and scaling. Frequent announcements of new members, partnerships, and funding initiatives imply ongoing organizational alignment and strategic development challenges inherent to its mission.","lat":44.675,"lng":-63.567,"contact_name":"Melanie Nadeau","contact_email":"melanie.nadeau@coveocean.com","contact_position":"CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/melanie-nadeau-a7346b7/","contact_bio":"N/A","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Excellent fit due to direct engagement with scaling and transition challenges across its ecosystem, ideal for an EiR focusing on leadership problems.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Kongsberg Maritime Canada Ltd.","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia, Canada","website":"https://www.kongsberg.com/maritime/","estimated_size":"Medium (50-200 employees for Canada operations, part of global entity)","estimated_budget":"Multi-million CAD","mission_focus":"Provides advanced maritime technology, autonomous systems, and digital solutions for vessel automation, subsea applications, and sustainable marine operations across various sectors.","why_fit":"As a Canadian branch of a global leader in maritime technology, it faces ongoing challenges in implementing global strategies locally, adapting to regional market needs, and integrating advanced technologies. Their focus on autonomous systems suggests continuous innovation and strategic transitions.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Their strategic presence at COVE and broad range of advanced solutions suggest continuous development and integration challenges as they adapt global technologies to local markets and projects. The parent company''s continuous innovation implies ongoing local adaptation and implementation challenges.","lat":44.675,"lng":-63.567,"contact_name":"Ian Galsworthy","contact_email":"ian.galsworthy@kongsberg.com","contact_position":"General Manager (Dartmouth)","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/ian-galsworthy-a4773214/","contact_bio":"N/A","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Global company with strong local presence, likely dealing with integration of global strategies and local market alignment.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"GeoSpectrum Technologies Inc.","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia, Canada","website":"https://geospectrum.ca/","estimated_size":"Medium (50-200 employees)","estimated_budget":"Multi-million CAD","mission_focus":"Designs and manufactures marine acoustic hardware and systems, including sonars, acoustic communication, and surveillance solutions for defense, oil & gas, and environmental sectors.","why_fit":"Demonstrates strategic growth through facility expansion, new product development, and key partnerships (e.g., with Team Vigilance for the Canadian Navy). Being a subsidiary of Elbit Systems adds layers of organizational complexity and potential for strategic alignment challenges.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"i