sed funding)","mission_focus":"A global research, conservation, and management initiative deploying aquatic telemetry to track marine animals and understand their movements and habitats.","why_fit":"As a global research network, OTN deals with inherent multi-stakeholder collaboration challenges (researchers, governments, NGOs), complex international data management, and the continuous need to secure funding and build diverse partnerships. These aspects directly relate to Leslie''s expertise in alignment issues, truth-telling gaps (data interpretation), and cross-sector complexity.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Ongoing management of a complex global network of researchers and data, requiring continuous alignment, partnership management, and strategic funding efforts across diverse international stakeholders.","lat":44.6366,"lng":-63.5937,"contact_name":"Dr. Fred Whoriskey","contact_email":"fred.whoriskey@dal.ca","contact_position":"Scientific Director","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/fred-whoriskey-4a942a12/","contact_bio":"N/A","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Complex global research initiative with strong multi-stakeholder coordination and data management needs, fitting Leslie''s expertise.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"metOcean Telematics","location":"Dartmouth, Nova Scotia, Canada","website":"https://www.metocean.com/","estimated_size":"Medium (50-200 employees)","estimated_budget":"Multi-million CAD","mission_focus":"Designs and manufactures data acquisition and telemetry systems, including oceanographic buoys, satellite communication solutions, and tracking devices for defense, environmental monitoring, and commercial applications.","why_fit":"Continuously innovating in ocean data collection and communication technologies, implying challenges in R&D, commercialization strategies, and scaling for diverse global markets. Serving defense, environmental, and commercial clients also presents significant cross-sector complexity and potential for strategic knots.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"supplemental","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Continuous product development and application across defense, environmental, and commercial sectors suggest ongoing scaling and strategic challenges in a competitive global market, requiring constant organizational adaptation and leadership focus.","lat":44.6859,"lng":-63.5714,"contact_name":"Tony Chedrawy","contact_email":"tony.chedrawy@metocean.com","contact_position":"President and CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/tony-chedrawy-7901042/","contact_bio":"N/A","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Key player in ocean data and telemetry, likely undergoing continuous strategic development and market expansion challenges.","budget_tier":"small"}]',15,0,'2026-03-23 07:50:44');
INSERT INTO discovery_runs VALUES(9,1,'ocean technology within 15 miles',unistr('You are a senior research analyst supporting a leadership advisor who is seeking a 6-8 week Entrepreneurship in Residence placement in Halifax, Nova Scotia. Your task is to find real, qualified ocean-focused organizations using web search.\u000a\u000aADVISOR BRIEF:\u000a- Geography: vancouver, bc\u000a- Search Radius: 15 miles\u000a- Placement Start: 2026-06-01\u000a- Placement Duration: 6-8 weeks\u000a- Focus Areas: Ocean health, Ocean economy, Ocean technology, Ocean infrastructure, Blue economy\u000a- Leadership Problems She Solves: Stuck partnerships, Alignment issues, Truth-telling gaps, Decision-making bottlenecks, Cross-sector complexity, Founder-to-CEO transitions, Scaling culture during hypergrowth\u000a- Non-Negotiables: No single-species operations (salmon-only, lobster-only, etc.), No freshwater organizations, Must have genuine ocean/marine focus\u000a- Win-Win-Win Criteria: Value for the organization, positive ocean outcomes, community benefits\u000a\u000aABOUT THE ADVISOR (LESLIE):\u000aNearly 20 years helping tech executives create happier teams, aligned outcomes, and stronger ROI. Now transitioning to ocean conservation / blue economy leadership advisory. Specializes in: stuck partnerships, alignment issues, truth-telling gaps, strategic knots. Works best 1:1 with senior leaders or with top teams on defined missions.\u000a- Works best 1:1 with senior leaders or with top teams on defined missions\u000a- Looking for a 6-8 week Entrepreneurship in Residence placement\u000a- Offering condensed senior advisory (equivalent of a year-long engagement in 2 months)\u000a- Best fit: organizations creating win-win-wins for corporations, nature, and future generations\u000a- Includes: for-profit companies, non-profits, NGOs, public-private partnerships, social enterprises, research institutions — any organization type\u000a\u000aGEOGRAPHY CONSTRAINT:\u000a- Primary location: vancouver, bc\u000a- Search radius: within 15 miles of vancouver, bc\u000a- Only include organizations headquartered or with major operations within this radius\u000a\u000aSEARCH TASK:\u000aSearch for: "ocean technology within 15 miles"\u000a\u000aHARD FILTERS — Qualitative Exclusions Only:\u000a- EXCLUDE: Any organization that operates exclusively on a single marine species (salmon-only farms, lobster harvesters, tuna fisheries, whale conservation, sea turtle rescue)\u000a- EXCLUDE: Any freshwater organization (lakes, rivers, freshwater fisheries)\u000a- EXCLUDE: ExxonMobil Canada, Shell Canada, SBM Offshore (enterprise-scale oil & gas — placement impractical)\u000a- Do NOT use the broad keyword ''offshore'' — use ''offshore wind'' only\u000a- Budget and headcount are NOT exclusion criteria — return all qualifying organizations regardless of size\u000a\u000aKEYWORD SEARCH STRATEGY — Two-Axis Search:\u000aSearch for organizations using ANY of these sector terms:\u000a\u000aPRIMARY (Sector Synonyms): ocean, marine, maritime, blue economy, oceanographic, offshore wind, subsea, coastal\u000a\u000aECONOMIC FRAMING: blue finance, ocean economy, marine commerce, ocean investment, investing in ocean, ocean-focused fund, marine investment, ocean venture, sustainable seafood investment, coastal economy investment, ocean-focused accelerator\u000a\u000aINFRASTRUCTURE & OPERATIONS: marine infrastructure, offshore wind operations, offshore wind development, shipbuilding, naval architecture, port authority, marine logistics, harbour management, underwater systems, marine engineering\u000a\u000aSCIENCE & DEEP TECHNOLOGY: ocean technology, oceanography, marine science, AUV, ROV, underwater acoustics, hydrography, bathymetry, ocean intelligence, marine sensing, seabed mapping, ocean data\u000a\u000aCONSERVATION & SUSTAINABILITY: ocean stewardship, marine conservation, ocean health, blue carbon, coastal resilience, marine protected areas, ocean sustainability, ocean governance\u000a\u000aGOVERNANCE & POLICY: marine spatial planning, ocean policy, coastal management, fisheries management (broad-mandate only), marine regulatory, EEZ\u000a\u000aFOOD SYSTEMS (handle with care — enforce single-species exclusion): aquaculture (multi-species only), mariculture, sustainable seafood, seafood supply chain, blue food\u000a\u000aALSO PRIORITIZE organizations showing these LEADERSHIP SIGNALS:\u000afounder-led scaling, hypergrowth, cross-sector partnership, strategic transition, joint venture, public-private partnership, multi-stakeholder, organizational alignment, board transition, scaling culture\u000a\u000aGEOGRAPHIC NOTE: Always pair economic/investment terms with Halifax, Nova Scotia, or Atlantic Canada.\u000a\u000aLEADERSHIP SIGNAL TIER INSTRUCTION:\u000aFor every organization returned, assess and report a leadership_signal_tier value:\u000a- Use ''confirmed'' if you found specific, dateable evidence of a leadership challenge (news article about rapid hiring, founder transition announcement, partnership press release, job posting for Chief People Officer, board change filing)\u000a- Use ''inferred'' if the org''s profile strongly implies a current leadership challenge without direct evidence (recent significant funding round, newly commercialized product, recently expanded government mandate, recent merger/restructure)\u000a- Use ''unknown'' if you could not find sufficient public information to assess leadership challenges\u000a\u000aCRITICAL DISTINCTION: ''unknown'' means the data does not exist to assess — it does NOT mean no leadership challenge exists. Low public profile ≠ no leadership challenge. Never conflate absence of data with absence of challenge. All three tiers are included in results; ''unknown'' is never an exclusion reason.\u000a\u000aFor ''unknown'' tier, set leadership_signal_evidence to: ''Insufficient public data to assess leadership challenges. Recommend direct outreach to verify organizational context before pursuing.''\u000a\u000aEXCLUSION RULES (reinforced):\u000a- No single-species operations: salmon-only, lobster-only, tuna-only, shrimp-only, whale conservation, sea turtle rescue\u000a- No freshwater organizations: lake research, river conservation, freshwater fisheries\u000a- No organizations outside 15 miles of vancouver, bc\u000a- Do NOT confuse ''no public data found'' with ''no leadership challenges detected''\u000a\u000aHALIFAX OCEAN ECOSYSTEM REFERENCE:\u000aCross-reference these known Nova Scotia ocean sector organizations when searching. Include them if they meet criteria, and search for additional qualifying organizations beyond this list:\u000a\u000aOCEAN TECH & SCIENCE:\u000a- Kraken Robotics — subsea technology, sonar, AUVs\u000a- Kongsberg Maritime Canada — maritime sensors and systems\u000a- GeoSpectrum Technologies — underwater acoustics\u000a- Innovasea — ocean tracking and aquaculture technology\u000a- JASCO Applied Sciences — ocean acoustics, environmental monitoring\u000a- AML Oceanographic — oceanographic instruments\u000a- Ultra Electronics Maritime Systems — defence and marine electronics\u000a- General Dynamics Canada — defence and ocean systems\u000a- Lockheed Martin Canada — defence, maritime surveillance\u000a- metOcean Telematics — ocean data buoys and telemetry\u000a- Fugro GeoSurveys — seabed mapping, geophysical survey\u000a- MDA (MacDonald Dettwiler) — satellite intelligence and earth observation\u000a- DSM Nutritional Products — marine ingredients/omega-3s\u000a- Acadian Seaplants — seaweed / marine agriculture\u000a- Ocean Sonics — hydrophones and marine acoustics\u000a- MacArtney Underwater Technology — underwater connectors and systems\u000a- CarteNav Solutions — maritime surveillance software\u000a- Deep Vision Inc. — underwater imaging and inspection\u000a\u000aOCEAN INFRASTRUCTURE & ENERGY:\u000a- Irving Shipbuilding — federal shipbuilding ($29.3B contract), Halifax\u000a- Babcock Canada — naval engineering and ship lifecycle support\u000a- FORCE (Fundy Ocean Research Centre for Energy) — tidal energy R&D\u000a- SNC-Lavalin — engineering, ocean infrastructure projects\u000a- ABCO Industries — marine fabrication\u000a\u000aDO NOT PURSUE (out of scope):\u000a- SBM Offshore — oil & gas production systems; enterprise scale\u000a- ExxonMobil Canada — offshore oil & gas major\u000a- Shell Canada — offshore energy exploration\u000a\u000aTRANSPORTATION & LOGISTICS:\u000a- Port of Halifax / Halifax Port Authority — major Atlantic port\u000a- Halterm Container Terminal — port operations\u000a- Atlantic Towing — offshore marine services\u000a- Secunda Canada — offshore marine and oil field services\u000a- Horizon Maritime Services — offshore vessel support\u000a- Oceanex — marine shipping, Atlantic Canada\u000a\u000aFISHERIES (broad ocean operations only):\u000a- High Liner Foods — global seafood processing, HQ Lunenburg NS\u000a- Clearwater Seafoods — premium shellfish, national and international scale\u000a\u000aEDUCATION & RESEARCH:\u000a- Bedford Institute of Oceanography (BIO) — federal ocean research, Dartmouth NS\u000a- Dalhousie University — Faculty of Science, ocean/marine programs\u000a- DRDC Atlantic — Defence Research & Development Canada, maritime focus\u000a- National Research Council Canada (NRC) — ocean science and engineering\u000a- COVE (Centre for Ocean Ventures & Entrepreneurship) — Halifax ocean innovation hub\u000a\u000aNETWORKS & ASSOCIATIONS:\u000a- OTCNS (Ocean Technology Council of Nova Scotia)\u000a- Ocean Tracking Network — Dalhousie, global ocean monitoring\u000a- COINAtlantic — Coastal and Ocean Information Network Atlantic\u000a\u000aOUTPUT FORMAT:\u000aReturn your results as a JSON array with this exact structure. Include both organization fields AND lead contact fields:\u000a[\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Organization Name",\u000a    "location": "City, Province (or full address)",\u000a    "website": "https://...",\u000a    "estimated_size": 100,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$50M",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Brief description of their mission...",\u000a    "why_fit": "Why this org is a fit for the advisor...",\u000a    "keyword_category": "sector",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "confirmed",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Specific evidence found: recently announced...",\u000a    "lat": 44.6488,\u000a    "lng": -63.5752,\u000a    "contact_name": "Jane Smith",\u000a    "contact_email": "jsmith@org.com",\u000a    "contact_position": "CEO and Executive Director",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://linkedin.com/in/janesmith",\u000a    "contact_bio": "15 years in ocean technology, previously led...",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "Strong fit — $50M budget, ocean-wide mission, leadership transition underway"\u000a  }\u000a]\u000a\u000aFIELD NOTES:\u000a- keyword_category: one of "sector", "infra", "econ", "sci", "gov", "cons", "food" — which cluster best describes this org. Use "cons" for conservation/sustainability orgs. Use "food" for aquaculture, seafood supply chain, and blue food orgs.\u000a- signal_strength: one of "high", "strong", "supplemental", "careful" — how strong a lead for Leslie\u000a- leadership_signal_tier: one of "confirmed", "inferred", "unknown" — evidence quality for leadership challenge\u000a- leadership_signal_evidence: 1-3 sentences describing specific evidence or standard ''insufficient data'' note\u000a- lat/lng: approximate coordinates for Halifax-area mapping (decimal degrees)\u000a- review_status: one of "Lead for Business", "Lead for Review", "Pending Review", "Do NOT Contact"\u000a\u000aCOUNT AND QUALITY:\u000aReturn between 10 and 15 results. Prefer verified organizations with web-searchable evidence over speculative results. Do not return fewer than 10 results. Distribute across all three signal tiers — do not exclude unknown-tier orgs to meet a count target. Sort by estimated budget (high to low) with signal tier as tiebreaker.\u000a\u000aReturn ONLY the JSON array, no other text.'),unistr('```json\u000a[\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Seaspan Shipyards",\u000a    "location": "Vancouver, British Columbia",\u000a    "website": "https://www.seaspan.com/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 2800,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$29.3B+",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Seaspan Shipyards is a leader in shipbuilding, repair, and maintenance of naval, research, and commercial vessels, committed to investing in the B.C. business community and clean technology.",\u000a    "why_fit": "This organization aligns with Leslie''s focus on ocean infrastructure and technology, offering opportunities to solve ''scaling culture during hypergrowth'' and ''cross-sector complexity'' as they re-invest in the community and engage in major collaborations. Their large-scale operations and strategic initiatives around clean technology and digital transformation present significant leadership challenges.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "infra",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "confirmed",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Regularly re-invests in the B.C. business community, collaborates with BC Tech for a Digital Lift Internship, and was a finalist in Technology Impact awards, indicating strategic transitions and partnerships. Actively involved in clean technology initiatives at the Port of Vancouver.",\u000a    "lat": 49.2974,\u000a    "lng": -123.1166,\u000a    "contact_name": "Not publicly available",\u000a    "contact_email": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_position": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_bio": "N/A",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "Very large enterprise with confirmed strategic initiatives and partnerships, ideal for addressing scaling culture, cross-sector complexity, and strategic transitions."\u000a  },\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Vancouver Fraser Port Authority (Port of Vancouver)",\u000a    "location": "Vancouver, British Columbia",\u000a    "website": "https://www.portvancouver.com/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 125,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "Multi-million CAD",\u000a    "mission_focus": "As Canada''s largest port, the Port of Vancouver manages trade, land, and marine operations with a strong focus on efficiency, innovation, sustainability, and accelerating the adoption of clean technologies.",\u000a    "why_fit": "The Port Authority is actively pursuing large-scale clean technology initiatives and partnerships, presenting significant challenges in ''strategic transition,'' ''cross-sector complexity,'' and ''organizational alignment'' as they work towards phasing out port-related emissions by 2050.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "gov",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "confirmed",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Launched the ''Clean Technology Initiative'' to fund and accelerate the adoption of low and zero-emission fuels and technologies, and partnered with businesses like Seaspan Ferries for pilot projects. Ronan Chester is cited as Director of Climate Action and Sustainability Leadership.",\u000a    "lat": 49.2827,\u000a    "lng": -123.1207,\u000a    "contact_name": "Ronan Chester",\u000a    "contact_email": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_position": "Director of Climate Action and Sustainability Leadership (as of 2021)",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_bio": "N/A",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "A major public-private entity with clear, ambitious goals requiring significant strategic and operational leadership to achieve decarbonization and innovation targets."\u000a  },\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "UBC Institute for the Oceans and Fisheries (IOF)",\u000a    "location": "Vancouver Campus, The University of British Columbia",\u000a    "website": "https://oceans.ubc.ca/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 100,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "Multi-million CAD",\u000a    "mission_focus": "The IOF contributes to sustainable oceans, coastal ecosystems, and fisheries through research and education, addressing global climate and ocean changes, human impacts, and policy.",\u000a    "why_fit": "As a leading research institution, IOF continually faces challenges in securing funding, managing complex interdisciplinary projects, and translating scientific findings into actionable policy and practice, aligning with ''cross-sector complexity'' and ''strategic knots.''",\u000a    "keyword_category": "sci",\u000a    "signal_strength": "strong",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "inferred",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "As a major research institution, it continuously undertakes ''challenging new research in response to emerging issues'' and collaborates ''with policy-makers at all levels,'' implying ongoing needs for strategic leadership in managing complex partnerships and transitions.",\u000a    "lat": 49.2606,\u000a    "lng": -123.2460,\u000a    "contact_name": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_email": "info@oceans.ubc.ca",\u000a    "contact_position": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_bio": "N/A",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Review",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "A prominent academic and research body, ideal for an advisor focusing on impact translation, organizational alignment within a complex research ecosystem, and strategic planning for ocean outcomes."\u000a  },\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Cellula Robotics",\u000a    "location": "Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada",\u000a    "website": "https://www.cellula.com/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 80,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "Estimated $10M - $50M+",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Cellula Robotics specializes in the turnkey design and production of advanced subsea robotic systems (AUVs) for applications including subsea security, mineral exploration, energy exploration, and science, with a commitment to sustainable solutions.",\u000a    "why_fit": "As a leading marine technology company with over 80 professionals and international operations, Cellula Robotics is likely experiencing ''hypergrowth'' and ''cross-sector complexity'' as they innovate and expand into new applications globally. They could benefit from advisory on scaling culture and strategic partnerships.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "sci",\u000a    "signal_strength": "strong",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "confirmed",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Described as a ''world-leading engineering solutions'' provider with ''over 80 skilled professionals across Canada, US and the UK'', indicating significant growth and international expansion.",\u000a    "lat": 49.2577,\u000a    "lng": -123.0039,\u000a    "contact_name": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_email": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_position": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_bio": "N/A",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "A high-growth ocean technology company with global reach, offering a strong opportunity for an advisor to support scaling, strategic development, and cross-sector engagements."\u000a  },\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "International Submarine Engineering Ltd. (ISE)",\u000a    "location": "Port Coquitlam, British Columbia, Canada",\u000a    "website": "https://www.ise.bc.ca/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 50,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "Estimated $10M - $50M",\u000a    "mission_focus": "ISE designs and delivers subsea robotics, including AUVs, ROVs, and manipulators, for a wide range of marine, land, and space applications, drawing on over four decades of engineering expertise.",\u000a    "why_fit": "As a long-standing leader in advanced robotics, ISE likely faces challenges in ''strategic transition'' to new markets, R&D management for continuous innovation, and maintaining ''organizational alignment'' in a competitive high-tech sector.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "sci",\u000a    "signal_strength": "strong",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "inferred",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "The company has ''4+ decades of subsea marine and robotics engineering'' and ''continues to develop this capability to meet the requirements for future applications,'' suggesting ongoing strategic challenges related to innovation, market positioning, and potentially founder-to-CEO transitions in a legacy tech firm.",\u000a    "lat": 49.2638,\u000a    "lng": -122.7719,\u000a    "contact_name": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_email": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_position": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_bio": "N/A",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Review",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "An established tech firm with deep expertise, suitable for advising on long-term strategic evolution, market diversification, and fostering a culture of continuous innovation."\u000a  },\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Robert Allan Ltd.",\u000a    "location": "Vancouver, British Columbia",\u000a    "website": "https://ral.ca/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 100,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "Estimated $10M - $50M",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Robert Allan Ltd. is an internationally recognized firm of naval architects and marine engineers, renowned for innovative designs across various vessel types, including tugs, ferries, and sophisticated research vessels.",\u000a    "why_fit": "With a history dating back to 1928, this firm likely encounters ''strategic knots'' in evolving design methodologies, adapting to new environmental regulations, and ''scaling culture'' while maintaining its reputation for innovation in a traditional industry.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "infra",\u000a    "signal_strength": "strong",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "inferred",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "A firm ''since 1928,'' known for ''innovative designs.'' Long-standing companies often face leadership challenges related to succession planning, maintaining innovation momentum, and adapting to new industry demands.",\u000a    "lat": 49.2827,\u000a    "lng": -123.1207,\u000a    "contact_name": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_email": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_position": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_bio": "N/A",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Review",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "A well-respected, traditional engineering firm that could benefit from Leslie''s expertise in strategic alignment and navigating industry transformations."\u000a  },\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Vard Marine Inc.",\u000a    "location": "Vancouver, British Columbia (Headquarters)",\u000a    "website": "https://www.vardmarine.com/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 50,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "Estimated $5M - $20M",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Vard Marine is a consulting naval architecture and marine engineering company providing professional ship design, engineering, and shipbuilding technology services for advanced offshore and specialized vessels.",\u000a    "why_fit": "As a consulting firm with an international presence, Vard Marine may face ''alignment issues'' across its global operations and ''strategic knots'' in delivering cutting-edge solutions in a rapidly evolving marine sector, making Leslie''s expertise valuable.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "infra",\u000a    "signal_strength": "strong",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "inferred",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "A ''consulting naval architecture and marine engineering company with our headquarters located in Vancouver, BC. Our satellite offices are located in Ottawa, ON; Houston, TX; Vũng Tàu, Vietnam; and Gdańsk, Poland.'' This suggests potential for ''alignment issues'' across multiple international offices.",\u000a    "lat": 49.2827,\u000a    "lng": -123.1207,\u000a    "contact_name": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_email": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_position": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "N/A",\u000a    "contact_bio": "N/A",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Revie