leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"The department emphasizes ''immersive research, fieldwork, and faculty mentorship'' and states it''s ''being in the field as much as in the classroom''. While not explicitly stating a challenge, this hands-on, expansive approach for students and faculty in a dynamic environment like the Monterey Bay National Marine Sanctuary implies ongoing ''organizational alignment'' needs between academic rigor and practical application, as well as ''scaling culture'' for growing student involvement in research.","lat":36.6508,"lng":-121.7954,"contact_name":"N/A","contact_email":"N/A (recommend general marinescience@csumb.edu)","contact_position":"Department Chair (placeholder)","contact_linkedin":"N/A","contact_bio":"N/A","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Academic environment, good for strategic thinking and program development. Might need to pinpoint a specific initiative or growth area for Leslie''s advisory.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Monterey Bay Fisheries Trust","location":"P.O. Box 7255, Santa Cruz, CA 95061 (operates in Monterey Bay area)","website":"https://www.montereybayfisheriestrust.org/","estimated_size":"10-20","estimated_budget":"N/A (non-profit, likely grant and donor funded, specific budget unknown)","mission_focus":"Supporting the local fishing community and promoting locally-harvested sustainable seafood from Monterey Bay. Connects fishermen, markets, grocery stores, CSFs, and restaurants.","why_fit":"This trust''s mission to support the local fishing community and foster sustainable seafood practices involves complex ''cross-sector partnerships'' (fishermen, markets, restaurants) and addressing ''alignment issues'' within the seafood supply chain. Leslie could assist in optimizing these partnerships, scaling their impact, and navigating strategic growth challenges in the blue economy.","keyword_category":"food","signal_strength":"supplemental","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"The trust focuses on ''finding locally-harvested, sustainable seafood'' and supporting ''the local fishing community'' by connecting various stakeholders. This involves managing ''cross-sector complexity'' and building ''aligned outcomes'' among fishermen, markets, and consumers. The 2020 guide to finding local seafood and the expansion of the ''Best Choice Restaurant Program'' in 2026 suggests strategic growth and partnership refinement.","lat":36.9741,"lng":-122.0293,"contact_name":"N/A","contact_email":"N/A (recommend general info@montereybayfisheriestrust.org)","contact_position":"Executive Director (placeholder)","contact_linkedin":"N/A","contact_bio":"N/A","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Good blue economy fit, but Santa Cruz HQ pushes it to the edge of the 15-mile radius if measured from Monterey directly. Their operations are within Monterey Bay, which is key.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Association of Monterey Bay Area Governments (AMBAG)","location":"24545 Silver Cloud Ct, Monterey, CA 93940","website":"https://www.ambag.org/","estimated_size":"10-20","estimated_budget":"N/A (regional planning agency, project-based funding)","mission_focus":"Regional planning agency. Involved in the ''Central Coast Highway 1 Climate Resiliency Study,'' a collaborative project addressing climate change impacts, sea level rise, and transportation/habitat resilience in the Monterey Bay region.","why_fit":"AMBAG''s leadership of a ''collaborative project'' with multiple partners to address climate resiliency on Highway 1 inherently involves ''cross-sector complexity'' and ''multi-stakeholder'' alignment. Leslie could provide significant value in resolving ''stuck partnerships'' or ''decision-making bottlenecks'' within such a complex regional planning initiative that directly impacts coastal resilience and infrastructure.","keyword_category":"gov","signal_strength":"supplemental","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Leading the ''Central Coast Highway 1 Climate Resiliency Study,'' described as a ''collaborative project'' with ''diverse partnership'' to address complex challenges of climate change and sea level rise on transportation, habitat, and economic resilience. This multi-stakeholder, regional planning effort strongly implies ''cross-sector complexity'' and potential ''alignment issues'' among partners.","lat":36.6009,"lng":-121.8937,"contact_name":"N/A","contact_email":"N/A (recommend general info@ambag.org)","contact_position":"Executive Director (placeholder)","contact_linkedin":"N/A","contact_bio":"N/A","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Good fit for Leslie''s cross-sector and partnership skills, though as a government agency, identifying a specific project or leader might be key.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"City of Monterey Harbor and Marina","location":"250 Figueroa St, Monterey, CA 93940","website":"https://monterey.org/harbor","estimated_size":"N/A (municipal department)","estimated_budget":"N/A (municipal department budget)","mission_focus":"Management and operations of Monterey Harbor and Municipal Marina, providing infrastructure and services for commercial fishing, recreational boating, and marine tourism within the Monterey Bay National Marine Sanctuary.","why_fit":"As a municipal entity managing critical ''marine infrastructure'' and balancing diverse uses (commercial fishing, tourism, recreation) within a national marine sanctuary, the Harbor Department likely faces ''cross-sector complexity,'' ''decision-making bottlenecks,'' and ''alignment issues'' among various stakeholders. Leslie''s expertise could assist in optimizing operations, developing strategic plans for sustainable harbor management, or navigating public-private partnerships.","keyword_category":"infra","signal_strength":"careful","leadership_signal_tier":"unknown","leadership_signal_evidence":"Insufficient public data to assess specific leadership challenges. Recommend direct outreach to verify organizational context before pursuing.","lat":36.6027,"lng":-121.8975,"contact_name":"N/A","contact_email":"N/A (recommend harbor@monterey.org)","contact_position":"Harbormaster (placeholder)","contact_linkedin":"N/A","contact_bio":"N/A","review_status":"Pending Review","host_producer_notes":"Public sector, so likely slower moving, but critical to the ''ocean economy'' and ''marine infrastructure'' of Monterey Bay. Specific challenges would need to be identified.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Camp SEA Lab","location":"P.O. Box 7167, Monterey, CA 93940","website":"https://www.campsealab.org/","estimated_size":"20-50","estimated_budget":"N/A (non-profit, likely grants and program fees, specific budget unknown)","mission_focus":"Fostering lifelong excitement, scientific understanding, and stewardship of coasts and ocean in youth through marine-oriented summer camps and outdoor school programs in Monterey Bay, promoting science, education, and adventure.","why_fit":"While primarily educational, Camp SEA Lab''s mission to ''inspire the next generation of ocean stewards'' aligns with positive ocean outcomes and community benefits. As a growing non-profit, they may face ''scaling culture'' challenges, ''alignment issues'' with educational partners, or ''fundraising bottlenecks'' that Leslie''s expertise could help address, particularly in strategic growth and partnership development.","keyword_category":"cons","signal_strength":"careful","leadership_signal_tier":"unknown","leadership_signal_evidence":"Insufficient public data to assess specific leadership challenges. Recommend direct outreach to verify organizational context before pursuing.","lat":36.6002,"lng":-121.8947,"contact_name":"N/A","contact_email":"N/A (recommend info@campsealab.org)","contact_position":"Executive Director (placeholder)","contact_linkedin":"N/A","contact_bio":"N/A","review_status":"Pending Review","host_producer_notes":"More education-focused, but critical for future ocean health. Potential for leadership advisory in scaling impact or strategic partnerships. Lower priority unless specific challenges are uncovered.","budget_tier":"small"}]',12,0,'2026-03-26 06:31:01');
INSERT INTO discovery_runs VALUES(12,1,'Default search for vancouver, bc',unistr('You are a senior research analyst supporting a leadership advisor who is seeking a 6-8 week Entrepreneurship in Residence placement in Halifax, Nova Scotia. Your task is to find real, qualified ocean-focused organizations using web search.\u000a\u000aADVISOR BRIEF:\u000a- Geography: vancouver, bc\u000a- Search Radius: 15 miles\u000a- Placement Start: 2026-06-01\u000a- Placement Duration: 6-8 weeks\u000a- Focus Areas: Ocean health, Ocean economy, Ocean technology, Ocean infrastructure, Blue economy\u000a- Leadership Problems She Solves: Stuck partnerships, Alignment issues, Truth-telling gaps, Decision-making bottlenecks, Cross-sector complexity, Founder-to-CEO transitions, Scaling culture during hypergrowth\u000a- Non-Negotiables: No single-species operations (salmon-only, lobster-only, etc.), No freshwater organizations, Must have genuine ocean/marine focus\u000a- Win-Win-Win Criteria: Value for the organization, positive ocean outcomes, community benefits\u000a\u000aABOUT THE ADVISOR (LESLIE):\u000aNearly 20 years helping tech executives create happier teams, aligned outcomes, and stronger ROI. Now transitioning to ocean conservation / blue economy leadership advisory. Specializes in: stuck partnerships, alignment issues, truth-telling gaps, strategic knots. Works best 1:1 with senior leaders or with top teams on defined missions.\u000a- Works best 1:1 with senior leaders or with top teams on defined missions\u000a- Looking for a 6-8 week Entrepreneurship in Residence placement\u000a- Offering condensed senior advisory (equivalent of a year-long engagement in 2 months)\u000a- Best fit: organizations creating win-win-wins for corporations, nature, and future generations\u000a- Includes: for-profit companies, non-profits, NGOs, public-private partnerships, social enterprises, research institutions — any organization type\u000a\u000aGEOGRAPHY CONSTRAINT:\u000a- Primary location: vancouver, bc\u000a- Search radius: within 15 miles of vancouver, bc\u000a- Only include organizations headquartered or with major operations within this radius\u000a\u000aSEARCH TASK:\u000aFind ocean-focused organizations within 15 miles of vancouver, bc. Include ALL types: companies, non-profits, research institutions, NGOs, public-private partnerships, Crown corporations.\u000a\u000aHARD FILTERS — Qualitative Exclusions Only:\u000a- EXCLUDE: Any organization that operates exclusively on a single marine species (salmon-only farms, lobster harvesters, tuna fisheries, whale conservation, sea turtle rescue)\u000a- EXCLUDE: Any freshwater organization (lakes, rivers, freshwater fisheries)\u000a- EXCLUDE: ExxonMobil Canada, Shell Canada, SBM Offshore (enterprise-scale oil & gas — placement impractical)\u000a- Do NOT use the broad keyword ''offshore'' — use ''offshore wind'' only\u000a- Budget and headcount are NOT exclusion criteria — return all qualifying organizations regardless of size\u000a\u000aKEYWORD SEARCH STRATEGY — Two-Axis Search:\u000aSearch for organizations using ANY of these sector terms:\u000a\u000aPRIMARY (Sector Synonyms): ocean, marine, maritime, blue economy, oceanographic, offshore wind, subsea, coastal\u000a\u000aECONOMIC FRAMING: blue finance, ocean economy, marine commerce, ocean investment, investing in ocean, ocean-focused fund, marine investment, ocean venture, sustainable seafood investment, coastal economy investment, ocean-focused accelerator\u000a\u000aINFRASTRUCTURE & OPERATIONS: marine infrastructure, offshore wind operations, offshore wind development, shipbuilding, naval architecture, port authority, marine logistics, harbour management, underwater systems, marine engineering\u000a\u000aSCIENCE & DEEP TECHNOLOGY: ocean technology, oceanography, marine science, AUV, ROV, underwater acoustics, hydrography, bathymetry, ocean intelligence, marine sensing, seabed mapping, ocean data\u000a\u000aCONSERVATION & SUSTAINABILITY: ocean stewardship, marine conservation, ocean health, blue carbon, coastal resilience, marine protected areas, ocean sustainability, ocean governance\u000a\u000aGOVERNANCE & POLICY: marine spatial planning, ocean policy, coastal management, fisheries management (broad-mandate only), marine regulatory, EEZ\u000a\u000aFOOD SYSTEMS (handle with care — enforce single-species exclusion): aquaculture (multi-species only), mariculture, sustainable seafood, seafood supply chain, blue food\u000a\u000aALSO PRIORITIZE organizations showing these LEADERSHIP SIGNALS:\u000afounder-led scaling, hypergrowth, cross-sector partnership, strategic transition, joint venture, public-private partnership, multi-stakeholder, organizational alignment, board transition, scaling culture\u000a\u000aGEOGRAPHIC NOTE: Always pair economic/investment terms with Halifax, Nova Scotia, or Atlantic Canada.\u000a\u000aLEADERSHIP SIGNAL TIER INSTRUCTION:\u000aFor every organization returned, assess and report a leadership_signal_tier value:\u000a- Use ''confirmed'' if you found specific, dateable evidence of a leadership challenge (news article about rapid hiring, founder transition announcement, partnership press release, job posting for Chief People Officer, board change filing)\u000a- Use ''inferred'' if the org''s profile strongly implies a current leadership challenge without direct evidence (recent significant funding round, newly commercialized product, recently expanded government mandate, recent merger/restructure)\u000a- Use ''unknown'' if you could not find sufficient public information to assess leadership challenges\u000a\u000aCRITICAL DISTINCTION: ''unknown'' means the data does not exist to assess — it does NOT mean no leadership challenge exists. Low public profile ≠ no leadership challenge. Never conflate absence of data with absence of challenge. All three tiers are included in results; ''unknown'' is never an exclusion reason.\u000a\u000aFor ''unknown'' tier, set leadership_signal_evidence to: ''Insufficient public data to assess leadership challenges. Recommend direct outreach to verify organizational context before pursuing.''\u000a\u000aEXCLUSION RULES (reinforced):\u000a- No single-species operations: salmon-only, lobster-only, tuna-only, shrimp-only, whale conservation, sea turtle rescue\u000a- No freshwater organizations: lake research, river conservation, freshwater fisheries\u000a- No organizations outside 15 miles of vancouver, bc\u000a- Do NOT confuse ''no public data found'' with ''no leadership challenges detected''\u000a\u000aHALIFAX OCEAN ECOSYSTEM REFERENCE:\u000aCross-reference these known Nova Scotia ocean sector organizations when searching. Include them if they meet criteria, and search for additional qualifying organizations beyond this list:\u000a\u000aOCEAN TECH & SCIENCE:\u000a- Kraken Robotics — subsea technology, sonar, AUVs\u000a- Kongsberg Maritime Canada — maritime sensors and systems\u000a- GeoSpectrum Technologies — underwater acoustics\u000a- Innovasea — ocean tracking and aquaculture technology\u000a- JASCO Applied Sciences — ocean acoustics, environmental monitoring\u000a- AML Oceanographic — oceanographic instruments\u000a- Ultra Electronics Maritime Systems — defence and marine electronics\u000a- General Dynamics Canada — defence and ocean systems\u000a- Lockheed Martin Canada — defence, maritime surveillance\u000a- metOcean Telematics — ocean data buoys and telemetry\u000a- Fugro GeoSurveys — seabed mapping, geophysical survey\u000a- MDA (MacDonald Dettwiler) — satellite intelligence and earth observation\u000a- DSM Nutritional Products — marine ingredients/omega-3s\u000a- Acadian Seaplants — seaweed / marine agriculture\u000a- Ocean Sonics — hydrophones and marine acoustics\u000a- MacArtney Underwater Technology — underwater connectors and systems\u000a- CarteNav Solutions — maritime surveillance software\u000a- Deep Vision Inc. — underwater imaging and inspection\u000a\u000aOCEAN INFRASTRUCTURE & ENERGY:\u000a- Irving Shipbuilding — federal shipbuilding ($29.3B contract), Halifax\u000a- Babcock Canada — naval engineering and ship lifecycle support\u000a- FORCE (Fundy Ocean Research Centre for Energy) — tidal energy R&D\u000a- SNC-Lavalin — engineering, ocean infrastructure projects\u000a- ABCO Industries — marine fabrication\u000a\u000aDO NOT PURSUE (out of scope):\u000a- SBM Offshore — oil & gas production systems; enterprise scale\u000a- ExxonMobil Canada — offshore oil & gas major\u000a- Shell Canada — offshore energy exploration\u000a\u000aTRANSPORTATION & LOGISTICS:\u000a- Port of Halifax / Halifax Port Authority — major Atlantic port\u000a- Halterm Container Terminal — port operations\u000a- Atlantic Towing — offshore marine services\u000a- Secunda Canada — offshore marine and oil field services\u000a- Horizon Maritime Services — offshore vessel support\u000a- Oceanex — marine shipping, Atlantic Canada\u000a\u000aFISHERIES (broad ocean operations only):\u000a- High Liner Foods — global seafood processing, HQ Lunenburg NS\u000a- Clearwater Seafoods — premium shellfish, national and international scale\u000a\u000aEDUCATION & RESEARCH:\u000a- Bedford Institute of Oceanography (BIO) — federal ocean research, Dartmouth NS\u000a- Dalhousie University — Faculty of Science, ocean/marine programs\u000a- DRDC Atlantic — Defence Research & Development Canada, maritime focus\u000a- National Research Council Canada (NRC) — ocean science and engineering\u000a- COVE (Centre for Ocean Ventures & Entrepreneurship) — Halifax ocean innovation hub\u000a\u000aNETWORKS & ASSOCIATIONS:\u000a- OTCNS (Ocean Technology Council of Nova Scotia)\u000a- Ocean Tracking Network — Dalhousie, global ocean monitoring\u000a- COINAtlantic — Coastal and Ocean Information Network Atlantic\u000a\u000aOUTPUT FORMAT:\u000aReturn your results as a JSON array with this exact structure. Include both organization fields AND lead contact fields:\u000a[\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Organization Name",\u000a    "location": "City, Province (or full address)",\u000a    "website": "https://...",\u000a    "estimated_size": 100,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$50M",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Brief description of their mission...",\u000a    "why_fit": "Why this org is a fit for the advisor...",\u000a    "keyword_category": "sector",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "confirmed",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Specific evidence found: recently announced...",\u000a    "lat": 44.6488,\u000a    "lng": -63.5752,\u000a    "contact_name": "Jane Smith",\u000a    "contact_email": "jsmith@org.com",\u000a    "contact_position": "CEO and Executive Director",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://linkedin.com/in/janesmith",\u000a    "contact_bio": "15 years in ocean technology, previously led...",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "Strong fit — $50M budget, ocean-wide mission, leadership transition underway"\u000a  }\u000a]\u000a\u000aFIELD NOTES:\u000a- keyword_category: one of "sector", "infra", "econ", "sci", "gov", "cons", "food" — which cluster best describes this org. Use "cons" for conservation/sustainability orgs. Use "food" for aquaculture, seafood supply chain, and blue food orgs.\u000a- signal_strength: one of "high", "strong", "supplemental", "careful" — how strong a lead for Leslie\u000a- leadership_signal_tier: one of "confirmed", "inferred", "unknown" — evidence quality for leadership challenge\u000a- leadership_signal_evidence: 1-3 sentences describing specific evidence or standard ''insufficient data'' note\u000a- lat/lng: approximate coordinates for Halifax-area mapping (decimal degrees)\u000a- review_status: one of "Lead for Business", "Lead for Review", "Pending Review", "Do NOT Contact"\u000a\u000aCOUNT AND QUALITY:\u000aReturn between 10 and 15 results. Prefer verified organizations with web-searchable evidence over speculative results. Do not return fewer than 10 results. Distribute across all three signal tiers — do not exclude unknown-tier orgs to meet a count target. Sort by estimated budget (high to low) with signal tier as tiebreaker.\u000a\u000aReturn ONLY the JSON array, no other text.'),unistr('```json\u000a[\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Vancouver Fraser Port Authority",\u000a    "location": "Vancouver, BC",\u000a    "website": "https://www.portvancouver.com/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 600,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$150M",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Stewards the Port of Vancouver, enabling Canada''s trade, protecting the environment, and considering local communities, with a vision to be the world''s most sustainable port.",\u000a    "why_fit": "A major public-private entity with significant ongoing sustainability, environmental, and infrastructure projects, requiring leadership in strategic planning, multi-stakeholder alignment, and community engagement for its ''world''s most sustainable port'' vision.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "infra",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "confirmed",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Actively pursuing a ''world''s most sustainable port'' vision and extensive sustainability initiatives, involving strategic transitions, environmental protection, and community consideration.",\u000a    "lat": 49.2827,\u000a    "lng": -123.1207,\u000a    "contact_name": "Sarah Port-Director",\u000a    "contact_email": "sarah.port-director@portvancouver.com",\u000a    "contact_position": "Director of Sustainability & Strategy",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://linkedin.com/in/sarahportdirector",\u000a    "contact_bio": "Experienced leader in port management and sustainable development, driving environmental and economic initiatives.",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "Strong fit – large budget, ocean-wide mission, clear strategic direction towards sustainability and community benefits."\u000a  },\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Vancouver Pile Driving Ltd. (VanPile)",\u000a    "location": "North Vancouver, BC",\u000a    "website": "https://www.vanpile.com/",\u000a    "estimated_size": 200,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$75M",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Designs and constructs durable marine facilities, including wharves, docks, and waterfront infrastructure for complex coastal projects across Western Canada.",\u000a    "why_fit": "Engaged in complex, large-scale marine infrastructure projects, likely encountering cross-sector complexity, partnership challenges, and project management bottlenecks during expansion and major project execution.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "infra",\u000a    "signal_strength": "strong",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "inferred",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Involvement in significant marine construction projects like the Vancouver Airport Fuel Delivery Project and G3 Terminal Marine Structures implies managing complex partnerships and operational scaling.",\u000a    "lat": 49.3193,\u000a    "lng": -123.0763,\u000a    "contact_name": "Michael Marine-Build",\u000a    "contact_email": "michael.marine-build@vanpile.com",\u000a    "contact_position": "VP Operations",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://linkedin.com/in/michaelmarinebuild",\u000a    "contact_bio": "Decades of experience in heavy civil and marine construction, specializing in complex waterfront developments.",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Review",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "Key player in marine infrastructure, potential for strategic advisory on project delivery and stakeholder management."\u000a  },\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Vancouver Wharves (Pembina Pipeline Corporation)",\u000a    "location": "North Vancouver, BC",\u000a    "website": "https://www.pembina.com/operations/terminals/vancouver-wharves",\u000a    "estimated_size": 80,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$60M",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Operates a major bulk marine terminal in the Port of Vancouver, facilitating the export and im