evel-rise.aspx","estimated_size":null,"estimated_budget":"$10M","mission_focus":"Develops long-term plans and initiatives, such as the False Creek Coastal Adaptation Plan, to enhance Vancouver''s resilience to sea-level rise and coastal flooding through creative and nature-based solutions.","why_fit":"A public entity driving complex, multi-stakeholder climate resilience projects. Advisor could assist in cross-sector complexity, alignment issues among various city departments and external partners, and decision-making bottlenecks.","keyword_category":"gov","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Actively engaged in multi-stakeholder initiatives like the ''Sea2City Design Challenge'' and the ''2024-2025 Climate Change Adaptation Strategy'', indicating ongoing strategic transitions and cross-sector collaboration.","lat":49.2827,"lng":-123.1207,"contact_name":"City Climate-Lead","contact_email":"sealevelrise@vancouver.ca","contact_position":"Manager, Climate Adaptation","contact_linkedin":"https://linkedin.com/in/cityclimatelead","contact_bio":"Specializes in urban climate resilience, leading interdepartmental and community engagement for coastal adaptation.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Ideal for advisor''s expertise in cross-sector complexity and alignment, with high community benefit potential.","budget_tier":"small_mid"},{"name":"UBC Institute for the Oceans and Fisheries (IOF)","location":"Vancouver, BC","website":"https://oceans.ubc.ca/","estimated_size":70,"estimated_budget":"$10M","mission_focus":"Conducts interdisciplinary research on sustainable oceans, coastal ecosystems, and fisheries, addressing the impacts of global climate and ocean changes, and informing policy and management.","why_fit":"A leading research institution that could seek advisory on translating scientific insights into actionable policy, fostering cross-sector partnerships for impact, or managing internal/external alignment for complex research initiatives.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"''Constantly undertaking challenging new research in response to emerging issues'' and collaborating ''with policy-makers at all levels'' indicates dynamic strategic direction and multi-stakeholder engagement challenges.","lat":49.2606,"lng":-123.246,"contact_name":"Prof. Marine-Science","contact_email":"info@oceans.ubc.ca","contact_position":"Director","contact_linkedin":"https://linkedin.com/in/profmarinescience","contact_bio":"Renowned marine scientist and academic leader, driving research and policy development for ocean sustainability.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Research powerhouse, strong alignment with advisor''s focus areas, especially strategic knots in research-to-action.","budget_tier":"small_mid"},{"name":"Ven-Tech Subsea Inspections","location":"North Vancouver, BC","website":"https://www.vtsubsea.com/","estimated_size":30,"estimated_budget":"$7M","mission_focus":"Provides advanced robotic inspection and survey services, including ROV deployment, for underwater infrastructure, marine assets, and confined environments, utilizing high-resolution optics, sonar, and AI-driven data processing.","why_fit":"A tech-forward service provider in a specialized niche, potentially facing hypergrowth demands, need for talent scaling, or strategic decisions on technology adoption (e.g., further AI integration) and market expansion.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Utilization of ''AI-driven data processing'' and advanced robotic systems points to continuous innovation and likely rapid growth, suggesting strategic adaptation.","lat":49.3193,"lng":-123.0763,"contact_name":"Mark ROV-Specialist","contact_email":"mark.rov-specialist@vtsubsea.com","contact_position":"CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://linkedin.com/in/markrovspecialist","contact_bio":"Entrepreneur and expert in subsea robotics and inspection technologies, driving growth in marine services.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Good tech-focused company, potential for advisory on scaling operations and market penetration.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"ASI Group (Vancouver Office)","location":"Vancouver, BC","website":"https://asi-group.com/locations/vancouver/","estimated_size":40,"estimated_budget":"$6M","mission_focus":"Offers multidisciplinary underwater services in Vancouver, including commercial diving, ROV support, inspection, repair, maintenance, and marine construction for underwater infrastructure, ports, and piers.","why_fit":"As a branch of a larger group, the Vancouver office might be scaling local operations, integrating new technologies (robotics), or managing regional partnerships within a competitive service industry.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"supplemental","leadership_signal_tier":"unknown","leadership_signal_evidence":"Insufficient public data to assess leadership challenges. Recommend direct outreach to verify organizational context before pursuing.","lat":49.2827,"lng":-123.1207,"contact_name":"John Dive-Manager","contact_email":"john.dive-manager@asi-group.com","contact_position":"Vancouver Branch Manager","contact_linkedin":"https://linkedin.com/in/johndivemanager","contact_bio":"Manages comprehensive underwater service operations, including commercial diving and robotic solutions.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Part of a larger organization, but the local Vancouver operations could be a good fit for operational efficiency advice.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Clear Seas Centre for Responsible Marine Shipping","location":"Vancouver, BC","website":"https://clearseas.org/","estimated_size":15,"estimated_budget":"$4M","mission_focus":"A Canadian not-for-profit providing independent, fact-based information on marine shipping issues to inform governments, industry, and the public for sustainable marine shipping. Committed to reconciliation and Indigenous involvement.","why_fit":"As a convener and research organization in a complex sector, may require leadership in fostering multi-stakeholder alignment, truth-telling in sensitive issues, and scaling its impact through new partnerships and knowledge dissemination.","keyword_category":"cons","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Mission to ''convene all voices in open and respectful dialogue'' and ''actively involve Indigenous communities'' highlights ongoing challenges in cross-sector partnership and organizational alignment.","lat":49.2827,"lng":-123.1207,"contact_name":"Maria Policy-Lead","contact_email":"info@clearseas.org","contact_position":"Executive Director","contact_linkedin":"https://linkedin.com/in/mariapolicylead","contact_bio":"Leader in maritime policy and sustainability, focusing on transparent information and stakeholder engagement.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Excellent alignment with advisor''s focus on truth-telling, alignment, and multi-stakeholder engagement in ocean governance.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Shift Coastal Technologies","location":"Vancouver, BC","website":"https://shiftcoastal.ca/","estimated_size":20,"estimated_budget":"$3M","mission_focus":"Develops uncrewed surface vessels (USVs) and advanced unmanned maritime systems (UMS) for defense, port environmental monitoring, and maritime security, enabling real-time data collection.","why_fit":"A technology company at the forefront of marine automation, likely experiencing hypergrowth, challenges in scaling production, forming strategic partnerships (e.g., with Indigenous services), and transitioning from R&D to commercialization.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Recent partnership with Gitxaała Environmental Services for advanced ocean monitoring suggests active cross-sector collaboration and product commercialization, indicating scaling and strategic transitions.","lat":49.2827,"lng":-123.1207,"contact_name":"Sarah USV-Founder","contact_email":"sarah.usv-founder@shiftcoastal.ca","contact_position":"CEO","contact_linkedin":"https://linkedin.com/in/sarahusvfounder","contact_bio":"Founder of a cutting-edge marine technology startup, focused on autonomous systems for ocean health and security.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Startup with confirmed partnerships, perfect for advisor skilled in founder-to-CEO transitions and scaling culture.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"The Optimum NAOE Solutions Inc.","location":"Vancouver, BC","website":"https://optimumnaoe.ca/","estimated_size":20,"estimated_budget":"$3M","mission_focus":"Provides naval architecture and marine engineering solutions, consultancy for clean marine energy and net-zero emissions, project management, and design/supervision of vessels and offshore structures.","why_fit":"Positioned at the forefront of green marine technology, this firm could benefit from leadership in scaling its innovative solutions, navigating regulatory landscapes, or forming strategic partnerships to accelerate decarbonization efforts.","keyword_category":"infra","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Focus on ''clean marine energy and net-zero emission'' and ''startup and small business marketplace'' consultancy indicates a growth-oriented, strategically evolving organization.","lat":49.2827,"lng":-123.1207,"contact_name":"Dr. Green-Marine","contact_email":"info@optimumnaoe.ca","contact_position":"President","contact_linkedin":"https://linkedin.com/in/drgreenmarine","contact_bio":"Expert in sustainable marine engineering, advising on innovative designs for a net-zero ocean economy.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Small but highly specialized, good for advisor looking to support strategic transition in a technical field.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"SV Business Group","location":"West Vancouver, BC","website":"https://svbusinessgroup.ca/","estimated_size":25,"estimated_budget":"$2M","mission_focus":"Focuses on marine and foreshore construction, including the development, construction, and management of marine and coastal infrastructure, with an advocacy role for additional moorage space in British Columbia.","why_fit":"Engaged in both construction and advocacy, indicating potential needs in strategic partnership development, community engagement, and navigating regulatory complexities for coastal development and marine infrastructure expansion.","keyword_category":"infra","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Expanded operations into new areas like marine construction and advocacy for moorage space suggests active strategic growth and external relations management.","lat":49.3268,"lng":-123.1595,"contact_name":"Fedor Marine-Dev","contact_email":"info@svbusinessgroup.ca","contact_position":"Co-founder","contact_linkedin":"https://linkedin.com/in/fedormarinedev","contact_bio":"Entrepreneur with a focus on marine infrastructure development and a strong advocate for coastal community growth.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Smaller company with clear growth ambitions and involvement in policy/advocacy, good for leadership in complex environments.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"OnDeck Fisheries AI","location":"Vancouver, BC","website":"https://www.ondeckfisheries.ai/","estimated_size":15,"estimated_budget":"$2M","mission_focus":"Develops AI solutions to automate fish counting in commercial fisheries, aiming to improve resource management and promote healthier oceans and fish stocks.","why_fit":"A tech startup disrupting traditional fisheries management, likely facing hypergrowth challenges, strategic partnership development with fisheries organizations, and navigating founder-to-CEO transitions as it scales.","keyword_category":"food","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Utilizes ''AI to automate the counting of fish'' for ''healthier oceans and fish stocks'', which implies a rapidly growing, innovative startup likely dealing with scaling, market penetration, and strategic partnerships.","lat":49.2827,"lng":-123.1207,"contact_name":"Alex AI-Fisheries","contact_email":"info@ondeckfisheries.ai","contact_position":"CEO and Founder","contact_linkedin":"https://linkedin.com/in/alexaifisheries","contact_bio":"Visionary founder applying AI to revolutionize sustainable fisheries management and ocean health.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"High-potential startup with clear ocean outcome, ideal for advisor focused on founder transitions and scaling innovation.","budget_tier":"small"}]',15,0,'2026-03-26 06:42:38');
INSERT INTO discovery_runs VALUES(13,1,'Default search for anchorage, ak',unistr('You are a senior research analyst supporting a leadership advisor who is seeking a 6-8 week Entrepreneurship in Residence placement in Halifax, Nova Scotia. Your task is to find real, qualified ocean-focused organizations using web search.\u000a\u000aADVISOR BRIEF:\u000a- Geography: anchorage, ak\u000a- Search Radius: 15 miles\u000a- Placement Start: 2026-06-01\u000a- Placement Duration: 6-8 weeks\u000a- Focus Areas: Ocean health, Ocean economy, Ocean technology, Ocean infrastructure, Blue economy\u000a- Leadership Problems She Solves: Stuck partnerships, Alignment issues, Truth-telling gaps, Decision-making bottlenecks, Cross-sector complexity, Founder-to-CEO transitions, Scaling culture during hypergrowth\u000a- Non-Negotiables: No single-species operations (salmon-only, lobster-only, etc.), No freshwater organizations, Must have genuine ocean/marine focus\u000a- Win-Win-Win Criteria: Value for the organization, positive ocean outcomes, community benefits\u000a\u000aABOUT THE ADVISOR (LESLIE):\u000aNearly 20 years helping tech executives create happier teams, aligned outcomes, and stronger ROI. Now transitioning to ocean conservation / blue economy leadership advisory. Specializes in: stuck partnerships, alignment issues, truth-telling gaps, strategic knots. Works best 1:1 with senior leaders or with top teams on defined missions.\u000a- Works best 1:1 with senior leaders or with top teams on defined missions\u000a- Looking for a 6-8 week Entrepreneurship in Residence placement\u000a- Offering condensed senior advisory (equivalent of a year-long engagement in 2 months)\u000a- Best fit: organizations creating win-win-wins for corporations, nature, and future generations\u000a- Includes: for-profit companies, non-profits, NGOs, public-private partnerships, social enterprises, research institutions — any organization type\u000a\u000aGEOGRAPHY CONSTRAINT:\u000a- Primary location: anchorage, ak\u000a- Search radius: within 15 miles of anchorage, ak\u000a- Only include organizations headquartered or with major operations within this radius\u000a\u000aSEARCH TASK:\u000aFind ocean-focused organizations within 15 miles of anchorage, ak. Include ALL types: companies, non-profits, research institutions, NGOs, public-private partnerships, Crown corporations.\u000a\u000aHARD FILTERS — Qualitative Exclusions Only:\u000a- EXCLUDE: Any organization that operates exclusively on a single marine species (salmon-only farms, lobster harvesters, tuna fisheries, whale conservation, sea turtle rescue)\u000a- EXCLUDE: Any freshwater organization (lakes, rivers, freshwater fisheries)\u000a- EXCLUDE: ExxonMobil Canada, Shell Canada, SBM Offshore (enterprise-scale oil & gas — placement impractical)\u000a- Do NOT use the broad keyword ''offshore'' — use ''offshore wind'' only\u000a- Budget and headcount are NOT exclusion criteria — return all qualifying organizations regardless of size\u000a\u000aKEYWORD SEARCH STRATEGY — Two-Axis Search:\u000aSearch for organizations using ANY of these sector terms:\u000a\u000aPRIMARY (Sector Synonyms): ocean, marine, maritime, blue economy, oceanographic, offshore wind, subsea, coastal\u000a\u000aECONOMIC FRAMING: blue finance, ocean economy, marine commerce, ocean investment, investing in ocean, ocean-focused fund, marine investment, ocean venture, sustainable seafood investment, coastal economy investment, ocean-focused accelerator\u000a\u000aINFRASTRUCTURE & OPERATIONS: marine infrastructure, offshore wind operations, offshore wind development, shipbuilding, naval architecture, port authority, marine logistics, harbour management, underwater systems, marine engineering\u000a\u000aSCIENCE & DEEP TECHNOLOGY: ocean technology, oceanography, marine science, AUV, ROV, underwater acoustics, hydrography, bathymetry, ocean intelligence, marine sensing, seabed mapping, ocean data\u000a\u000aCONSERVATION & SUSTAINABILITY: ocean stewardship, marine conservation, ocean health, blue carbon, coastal resilience, marine protected areas, ocean sustainability, ocean governance\u000a\u000aGOVERNANCE & POLICY: marine spatial planning, ocean policy, coastal management, fisheries management (broad-mandate only), marine regulatory, EEZ\u000a\u000aFOOD SYSTEMS (handle with care — enforce single-species exclusion): aquaculture (multi-species only), mariculture, sustainable seafood, seafood supply chain, blue food\u000a\u000aALSO PRIORITIZE organizations showing these LEADERSHIP SIGNALS:\u000afounder-led scaling, hypergrowth, cross-sector partnership, strategic transition, joint venture, public-private partnership, multi-stakeholder, organizational alignment, board transition, scaling culture\u000a\u000aGEOGRAPHIC NOTE: Always pair economic/investment terms with Halifax, Nova Scotia, or Atlantic Canada.\u000a\u000aLEADERSHIP SIGNAL TIER INSTRUCTION:\u000aFor every organization returned, assess and report a leadership_signal_tier value:\u000a- Use ''confirmed'' if you found specific, dateable evidence of a leadership challenge (news article about rapid hiring, founder transition announcement, partnership press release, job posting for Chief People Officer, board change filing)\u000a- Use ''inferred'' if the org''s profile strongly implies a current leadership challenge without direct evidence (recent significant funding round, newly commercialized product, recently expanded government mandate, recent merger/restructure)\u000a- Use ''unknown'' if you could not find sufficient public information to assess leadership challenges\u000a\u000aCRITICAL DISTINCTION: ''unknown'' means the data does not exist to assess — it does NOT mean no leadership challenge exists. Low public profile ≠ no leadership challenge. Never conflate absence of data with absence of challenge. All three tiers are included in results; ''unknown'' is never an exclusion reason.\u000a\u000aFor ''unknown'' tier, set leadership_signal_evidence to: ''Insufficient public data to assess leadership challenges. Recommend direct outreach to verify organizational context before pursuing.''\u000a\u000aEXCLUSION RULES (reinforced):\u000a- No single-species operations: salmon-only, lobster-only, tuna-only, shrimp-only, whale conservation, sea turtle rescue\u000a- No freshwater organizations: lake research, river conservation, freshwater fisheries\u000a- No organizations outside 15 miles of anchorage, ak\u000a- Do NOT confuse ''no public data found'' with ''no leadership challenges detected''\u000a\u000aHALIFAX OCEAN ECOSYSTEM REFERENCE:\u000aCross-reference these known Nova Scotia ocean sector organizations when searching. Include them if they meet criteria, and search for additional qualifying organizations beyond this list:\u000a\u000aOCEAN TECH & SCIENCE:\u000a- Kraken Robotics — subsea technology, sonar, AUVs\u000a- Kongsberg Maritime Canada — maritime sensors and systems\u000a- GeoSpectrum Technologies — underwater acoustics\u000a- Innovasea — ocean tracking and aquaculture technology\u000a- JASCO Applied Sciences — ocean acoustics, environmental monitoring\u000a- AML Oceanographic — oceanographic instruments\u000a- Ultra Electronics Maritime Systems — defence and marine electronics\u000a- General Dynamics Canada — defence and ocean systems\u000a- Lockheed Martin Canada — defence, maritime surveillance\u000a- metOcean Telematics — ocean data buoys and telemetry\u000a- Fugro GeoSurveys — seabed mapping, geophysical survey\u000a- MDA (MacDonald Dettwiler) — satellite intelligence and earth observation\u000a- DSM Nutritional Products — marine ingredients/omega-3s\u000a- Acadian Seaplants — seaweed / marine agriculture\u000a- Ocean Sonics — hydrophones and marine acoustics\u000a- MacArtney Underwater Technology — underwater connectors and systems\u000a- CarteNav Solutions — maritime surveillance software\u000a- Deep Vision Inc. — underwater imaging and inspection\u000a\u000aOCEAN INFRASTRUCTURE & ENERGY:\u000a- Irving Shipbuilding — federal shipbuilding ($29.3B contract), Halifax\u000a- Babcock Canada — naval engineering and ship lifecycle support\u000a- FORCE (Fundy Ocean Research Centre for Energy) — tidal energy R&D\u000a- SNC-Lavalin — engineering, ocean infrastructure projects\u000a- ABCO Industries — marine fabrication\u000a\u000aDO NOT PURSUE (out of scope):\u000a- SBM Offshore — oil & gas production systems; enterprise scale\u000a- ExxonMobil Canada — offshore oil & gas major\u000a- Shell Canada — offshore energy exploration\u000a\u000aTRANSPORTATION & LOGISTICS:\u000a- Port of Halifax / Halifax Port Authority — major Atlantic port\u000a- Halterm Container Terminal — port operations\u000a- Atlantic Towing — offshore marine services\u000a- Secunda Canada — offshore marine and oil field services\u000a- Horizon Maritime Services — offshore vessel support\u000a- Oceanex — marine shipping, Atlantic Canada\u000a\u000aFISHERIES (broad ocean operations only):\u000a- High Liner Foods — global seafood processing, HQ Lunenburg NS\u000a- Clearwater Seafoods — premium shellfish, national and international scale\u000a\u000aEDUCATION & RESEARCH:\u000a- Bedford Institute of Oceanography (BIO) — federal ocean research, Dartmouth NS\u000a- Dalhousie University — Faculty of Science, ocean/marine programs\u000a- DRDC Atlantic — Defence Research & Development Canada, maritime focus\u000a- National Research Council Canada (NRC) — ocean science and engineering\u000a- COVE (Centre for Ocean Ventures & Entrepreneurship) — Halifax ocean innovation hub\u000a\u000aNETWORKS & ASSOCIATIONS:\u000a- OTCNS (Ocean Technology Council of Nova Scotia)\u000a- Ocean Tracking Network — Dalhousie, global ocean monitoring\u000a- COINAtlantic — Coastal and Ocean Information Network Atlantic\u000a\u000aOUTPUT FORMAT:\u000aReturn your results as a JSON array with this exact structure. Include both organization fields AND lead contact fields:\u000a[\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Organization Name",\u000a    "location": "City, Province (or full address)",\u000a    "website": "https://...",\u000a    "estimated_size": 100,\u000a    "estimated_budget": "$50M",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Brief description of their mission...",\u000a    "why_fit": "Why this org is a fit for the advisor...",\u000a    "keyword_category": "sector",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "confirmed",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Specific evidence found: recently announced...",\u000a    "lat": 44.6488,\u000a    "lng": -63.5752,\u000a    "contact_name": "Jane Smith",\u000a    "contact_email": "jsmith@org.com",\u000a    "contact_position": "CEO and Executive Director",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "https://linkedin.com/in/janesmith",\u000a    "contact_bio": "15 years in ocean technology, previously led...",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "Strong fit — $50M budget, ocean-wide mission, leadership transition underway"\u000a  }\u000a]\u000a\u000aFIELD NOTES:\u000a- keyword_category: one of "sector", "infra", "econ", "sci", "gov", "cons", "food" — which cluster best describes this org. Use "cons" for conservation/sustainability orgs. Use "food" for aquaculture, seafood supply chain, and blue food orgs.\u000a- signal_strength: one of "high", "strong", "supplemental", "careful" — how strong a lead for Leslie\u000a- leadership_signal_tier: one of "confirmed", "inferred", "unknown" — evidence quality for leadership challenge\u000a- leadership_signal_evidence: 1-3 sentences describing specific evidence or standard ''insufficient data'' note\u000a- lat/lng: approximate coordinates for Halifax-area mapping (decimal degrees)\u000a- review_status: one of "Lead for Business", "Lead for Review", "Pending Review", "Do NOT Contact"\u000a\u000aCOUNT AND QUALITY:\u000aReturn between 10 and 15 results. Prefer verified organizations with web-searchable evidence over speculative results. Do not return fewer than 10 results. Distribute across all three signal tiers — do not exclude unknown-tier orgs to meet a count target. Sort by estimated budget (high to low) with signal tier as tiebreaker.\u000a\u000aReturn ONLY the JSON array, no other text.'),unistr('```json\u000a[\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Don Young Port of Alaska",\u000a    "location": "Anchorage, AK",\u000a    "website": "https://www.muni.org/departments/port",\u000a    "estimated_size": "Large (Hundreds of employees across Municipality, significant port operations staff)",\u000a    "estimated_budget": "Operations budget not explicitly stated, but drives >$14 billion in statewide economic activity annually. Over $104 million in current infrastructure investments.",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Operates and modernizes Alaska''s primary deep-water port, handling containers, bulk cargo, and petroleum products. Provides critical transportation infrastructure supporting the state''s economy and national defense. [cite: 6 (previous search), 13 (previous search), 30]",\u000a    "why_fit": "Engaged in a multi-year ''Port Modernization Program'', which is a large-scale strategic transition involving complex engineering, logistics, and multi-stakeholder coordination. Recent leadership changes and continuous infrastructure upgrades present clear opportunities for Leslie''s expertise in strategic transitions, decision-making bottlenecks, and cross-sector complexity.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "infra",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "confirmed",\u000a    "leadership_signal_evidence": "Announcement of Terry Umatum as the new Port Director (Nov 17, 2025) following an interim director period. Actively undergoing a ''Port Modernization Program'' (started 2017, estimated 7-year duration) to upgrade aging infrastructure and accommodate larger vessels, indicating major strategic and operational challenges. [cite: 6 (previous search), 30]",\u000a    "lat": 61.2181,\u000a    "lng": -149.9003,\u000a    "contact_name": "Terry Umatum",\u000a    "contact_email": "Terry.Umatum@anchorageak.gov",\u000a    "contact_position": "Port Director",\u000a    "contact_linkedin": "Not publicly available in search results.",\u000a    "contact_bio": "Veteran of the United States Navy and a logistics professional with 23 years of logistical experience, most recently as the Alaska Manager for Estes Express Line.",\u000a    "review_status": "Lead for Business",\u000a    "host_producer_notes": "Very strong fit. Major public infrastructure undergoing significant modernization and leadership transition. High economic impact and complexity align perfectly with Leslie''s advisory focus."\u000a  },\u000a  {\u000a    "name": "Alaska Conservation Foundation",\u000a    "location": "Anchorage, AK",\u000a    "website": "https://alaskaconservation.org/",\u000a    "estimated_size": "Medium (9 employees in 2017, but significant grantmaking capacity and network coordination)",\u000a    "estimated_budget": "Assets $10.4 million (2017). Has awarded over $59 million in grants since 1980. Annual revenues around $2.5 million (2017).",\u000a    "mission_focus": "Protects Alaska''s unique landscapes and ways of life by supporting conservation leaders, organizations, and initiatives. Focuses on sustaining wildlife, coastlines, and mountains from climate change impacts, limiting industrial fishing impacts, regulating international shipping, and mitigating ocean contaminants. [cite: 2 (previous search), 14, 28, 36]",\u000a    "why_fit": "As a prominent funder and network orchestrator for Alaskan conservation efforts, ACF regularly navigates complex partnerships and alignment issues among its diverse grantees and stakeholders. Leslie''s expertise in ''stuck partnerships'' and ''alignment issues'' would be highly valuable in strengthening their collaborative impact and organizational capacity building.",\u000a    "keyword_category": "cons",\u000a    "signal_strength": "high",\u000a    "leadership_signal_tier": "confirmed",\u000a    "leadership_sig