 position also suggests internal organizational shifts.","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"high","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Announcement of a ''new position announcement: finance Officer'' (Oct 28, 2025) indicates internal growth or restructuring. ''NPRB Seeking Nominations for Gulf of Alaska and Arctic Advisory Panel Members'' (Dec 11, 2025) highlights ongoing governance and strategic planning.","lat":61.2181,"lng":-149.9003,"contact_name":"Lynn Palensky","contact_email":"admin@nprb.org","contact_position":"Executive Director","contact_linkedin":"Not publicly available in search results.","contact_bio":"Lynn Palensky has served as NPRB''s Executive Director since 2020, bringing over two decades of fisheries-related grants and program management experience. She focuses on bridging the gap from science to policy and implementation.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Key player in Alaskan marine research funding. Challenges in coordinating scientific priorities, managing partnerships, and internal operational improvements make this a strong match for Leslie.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Foss Maritime Company, LLC (Anchorage Office)","location":"Anchorage, AK","website":"https://www.foss.com/","estimated_size":"Large (Major marine services company with global operations, significant fleet and personnel)","estimated_budget":"Not publicly available in search results. Implied substantial due to size and scope of operations and investments in innovative fleet.","mission_focus":"Provides comprehensive marine transportation, logistics, engineering, and harbor services (ship assist, tanker escort, ocean towing) across the U.S. West Coast, Alaska, and Hawaii. Emphasizes industry innovation, safety, and sustainable solutions.","why_fit":"Foss''s long history of industry innovation, including developing hybrid tugs and VSP systems, indicates a leadership dedicated to strategic transitions and operational excellence in marine technology. Their involvement in large-scale transportation projects and emergency response aligns with Leslie''s expertise in complex operations and decision-making.","keyword_category":"infra","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Continual investment in ''state-of-the-art vessels'' and developing ''first Tractor tugs and one-of-a-kind hybrid tugs'' demonstrates a clear strategic focus on technological innovation and fleet optimization. Commitment to ''environmental initiatives'' like using ultra-low sulfur diesel fuel.","lat":61.2181,"lng":-149.9003,"contact_name":"Not found for specific Anchorage leadership in search results. Gary Faber was President and CEO in 2011.","contact_email":"Not publicly available for specific Anchorage office contact.","contact_position":"Not specific to Anchorage office from search results.","contact_linkedin":"Not publicly available in search results.","contact_bio":"Not available.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"A leading marine transportation and engineering firm with a strong innovation bent. Potential for advisory on scaling culture or strategic transitions in a large, established company.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Turnagain Marine Construction","location":"Anchorage, AK","website":"https://www.turnagain.build/","estimated_size":"Medium (11 employees in 2024, workforce up to 45 for projects)","estimated_budget":"Revenue between $1-10 million (2024, inferred). Has completed over $150 million in successful Alaskan projects.","mission_focus":"Heavy civil marine design, engineering, and construction, specializing in harbor construction, breakwater construction, and waterfront development. Utilizes a proprietary ''END² integrated design-build program'' to deliver projects efficiently.","why_fit":"Their core business model explicitly addresses inefficiencies and challenges common in marine construction projects (''over-extended timelines, blown budgets, and uncompleted projects''), directly aligning with Leslie''s expertise in decision-making bottlenecks and cross-sector complexity. Their focus on innovation for the Alaskan marine environment also aligns with ''ocean infrastructure''.","keyword_category":"infra","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Tim Cunha recently became President, having previously served as Operations Manager and VP of Operations, indicating a leadership transition and growth. Co-founder Jason Davis developed their ''proprietary END² integrated design-build program'', emphasizing strategic innovation.","lat":61.2181,"lng":-149.9003,"contact_name":"Tim Cunha","contact_email":"business@turnagain.us","contact_position":"President","contact_linkedin":"Not publicly available in search results.","contact_bio":"Over two decades of experience in heavy civil and marine construction, with prior roles overseeing operations, personnel, and project management.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Innovative and growing company tackling complex marine construction challenges. Their internal process for project delivery makes them an excellent fit for Leslie''s strategic advisory.","budget_tier":"enterprise"},{"name":"Alaska Ocean Observing System (AOOS)","location":"Anchorage, AK","website":"https://www.aoos.org/","estimated_size":"Medium (Part of national IOOS network, operates with a Governance Board from 19 organizations, small core staff)","estimated_budget":"Not explicitly stated in search results. Funded by NOAA. [cite: 42 (previous search)]","mission_focus":"Provides ocean and coastal observation data and information products to improve maritime safety, enhance the economy, and protect the environment. Focus areas include safe marine operations, coastal hazard mitigation, ecosystem and climate trends, and water quality monitoring.","why_fit":"AOOS''s mission inherently involves connecting and aligning diverse stakeholders (Tribal, state, federal agencies, research, industry, NGOs) to address complex ocean challenges, directly fitting Leslie''s expertise in ''stuck partnerships'' and ''cross-sector complexity''. Recent board member changes demonstrate ongoing governance evolution. [cite: 9, 11, 34 (previous search)]","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Announced ''new board members'' (Oct 4, 2024), including representatives from various Alaska Native Organizations and tribal governments. Plans to add three additional Alaska Native seats in 2024. [cite: 34 (previous search)]. The 2026 Winter Advisory Board Meeting in Anchorage also points to active governance and strategic discussions.","lat":61.2181,"lng":-149.9003,"contact_name":"Steve White","contact_email":"information@aoos.org","contact_position":"Board Chair","contact_linkedin":"Not publicly available in search results.","contact_bio":"Not publicly available in search results.","review_status":"Lead for Business","host_producer_notes":"Critical data infrastructure for blue economy and ocean health in Alaska. Strong multi-stakeholder governance and recent board changes make this a very relevant leadership advisory opportunity.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"PND Engineers","location":"Anchorage, AK (Headquarters)","website":"https://pndengineers.com/","estimated_size":"Medium-Large (Multi-office engineering firm, staff not explicitly numbered in snippets)","estimated_budget":"Not publicly available in search results. Implied significant due to large project scale. [cite: 42 (previous search)]","mission_focus":"Provides civil and structural design and analysis services for transportation, marine, construction, energy, and site development industries. Specializes in innovative solutions for marine structures, including their patented OPEN CELL SHEET PILE™ (OCSP™) technology. [cite: 42 (previous search)]","why_fit":"PND''s emphasis on innovation (OCSP™ technology) to provide cost-effective, practical engineering solutions for challenging marine environments in Alaska aligns with Leslie''s interest in impactful problem-solving. Their client-focused approach and long-term relationships suggest potential for improving ''stuck partnerships'' or ''decision-making bottlenecks'' in project delivery. [cite: 42 (previous search)]","keyword_category":"infra","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"The development and widespread application of their patented OPEN CELL SHEET PILE™ (OCSP™) systems demonstrate a culture of continuous innovation and strong technical leadership. [cite: 42 (previous search)]. Their work ''from conception through project completion'' implies comprehensive project management and potential for strategic advisory. [cite: 42 (previous search)]","lat":61.2181,"lng":-149.9003,"contact_name":"Not found directly in search results.","contact_email":"Not publicly available for direct leadership contact.","contact_position":"Not found directly in search results.","contact_linkedin":"Not publicly available in search results.","contact_bio":"Not available.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Engineering firm with demonstrated innovation in marine infrastructure. Good fit for Leslie to explore leadership challenges in R&D commercialization or optimizing project delivery.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"University of Alaska Fairbanks, College of Fisheries and Ocean Sciences - Coastal Marine Institute (Anchorage Office)","location":"Anchorage, AK","website":"https://www.cfos.uaf.edu/research/coastal-marine-institute/","estimated_size":"Medium (Part of a larger university, but the CMI itself has a dedicated research program)","estimated_budget":"Not explicitly stated for CMI''s annual budget, but it funds projects. [cite: 35 (previous search)]","mission_focus":"Conducts multi-disciplinary research on coastal topics related to natural resource development on Alaska''s outer continental shelf. Focuses on fisheries, biomonitoring, oceanography, and oil biodegradation, aiming to collect and disseminate environmental information and strengthen partnerships. [cite: 3 (previous search), 35 (previous search)]","why_fit":"CMI''s work addressing ''OCS oil, gas, and marine minerals decisions'' and ''local and regional OCS-related environmental and resource issues of mutual interest'' involves complex, cross-sector challenges and multi-agency coordination. This aligns well with Leslie''s expertise in ''alignment issues'' and ''cross-sector complexity'' in a scientific and environmental context. [cite: 35 (previous search)]","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Annual Research Reviews and cooperative agreements with the Bureau of Ocean Energy Management (BOEM) indicate continuous strategic planning and multi-agency coordination, suggesting potential ''stuck partnerships'' or ''alignment issues'' within complex research programs. The establishment of the Alaska Blue Economy Center within CFOS also indicates strategic expansion. [cite: 3 (previous search), 35 (previous search)]","lat":61.2181,"lng":-149.9003,"contact_name":"Not found for specific CMI director in Anchorage. Bradley Moran is Dean of CFOS.","contact_email":"uaf-cfos@alaska.edu","contact_position":"General CFOS contact","contact_linkedin":"Not publicly available in search results.","contact_bio":"Not available.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Academic research unit focused on critical ocean resource issues. Offers a unique context for Leslie''s expertise in managing complex scientific collaborations and policy implications.","budget_tier":"enterprise"},{"name":"Alaska Sea Grant (Anchorage Office)","location":"Anchorage, AK (with offices in CFOS downtown)","website":"https://alaskaseagrant.org/","estimated_size":"Medium (Part of UAF and NOAA, with staff across Alaska, Davin Holen in Anchorage)","estimated_budget":"Not explicitly stated for Anchorage office. Supports researchers, graduate students, workshops, and fellowships. [cite: 12 (previous search), 23 (previous search), 41 (previous search)]","mission_focus":"Enhances sustainable use and conservation of Alaska''s marine and freshwater resources through research, outreach, and education. Supports coastal communities, sustainable fisheries (multi-species), mariculture, and marine literacy. [cite: 12 (previous search), 23 (previous search)]","why_fit":"Despite its dual marine/freshwater mandate, Alaska Sea Grant has a strong marine focus evident in its mariculture, coastal resilience, and marine policy work, aligning with ''ocean health'' and ''blue economy''. Their extensive partnerships (over 200 organizations) and outreach programs present significant opportunities for Leslie to address ''stuck partnerships'' and ''cross-sector complexity''. [cite: 12 (previous search), 23 (previous search), 45 (previous search)]","keyword_category":"cons","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Organizes significant events like the ''Mariculture Conference of Alaska'' (March 2026) and ''Building Connections to Strengthen Guardians and Indigenous-led Stewardship'' (March 2026), indicating ongoing strategic initiatives and multi-stakeholder engagement. [cite: 44 (previous search), 45 (previous search)] Their mission explicitly involves ''bridging the gap'' between science and communities.","lat":61.2181,"lng":-149.9003,"contact_name":"Davin Holen","contact_email":"davin.holen@alaska.edu","contact_position":"Coastal Community Resilience Specialist, Anchorage","contact_linkedin":"Not publicly available in search results.","contact_bio":"Helped develop the Community-Engaged Fellowship at the national level and leads workshops on oil spill preparedness and recovery.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Strong community and resilience focus with broad marine relevance. The advisory role could help navigate the complexities of their extensive partnership network and resource management strategies.","budget_tier":"small"},{"name":"Alaska Marine Community Coalition (formerly Alaska Marine Conservation Council)","location":"Anchorage, AK","website":"https://akmarine.org/","estimated_size":"Small (9 employees in 2024)","estimated_budget":"Total revenues $642,057, total expenses $668,587 (2024). [cite: 5 (previous search)]","mission_focus":"Fishermen-led nonprofit dedicated to protecting Alaska''s marine ecosystems, strengthening sustainable fisheries (multi-species), protecting critical fish habitat, and promoting local stewardship. Works to minimize bycatch, prevent overfishing, and support community-based fishing. [cite: 4 (previous search), 5 (previous search)]","why_fit":"The organization''s recent name change signals a strategic transition and potential for organizational realignment. Their mission of empowering Alaskans in fisheries management and strengthening local food systems inherently involves navigating ''cross-sector complexity'' and addressing ''alignment issues'' among various fishing communities and policy makers. [cite: 4 (previous search), 5 (previous search), 10 (previous search)]","keyword_category":"cons","signal_strength":"strong","leadership_signal_tier":"confirmed","leadership_signal_evidence":"Underwent a recent name change from Alaska Marine Conservation Council to Alaska Marine Community Coalition (announced Feb 2, 2026 via website banner from previous search), indicating a strategic rebranding or mission refinement. [cite: 10 (previous search)] Actively ''educates, advocates, and works with stakeholders on management strategies''. [cite: 5 (previous search)]","lat":61.2181,"lng":-149.9003,"contact_name":"Not explicitly found for top leadership in search results, but general inquiry is available.","contact_email":"fish@akmarine.org","contact_position":"General Inquiry (Suggest direct outreach for specific leadership contact)","contact_linkedin":"Not publicly available in search results.","contact_bio":"Not available.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Community-based conservation with a recent strategic shift. Leslie''s expertise could help them refine their new brand, strengthen partnerships, and optimize their advocacy strategies.","budget_tier":"enterprise"},{"name":"Alaska Center for Conservation Science (Oceanography, UAA)","location":"Anchorage, AK (University of Alaska Anchorage)","website":"https://accs.uaa.alaska.edu/research/oceanography/","estimated_size":"Small (Part of a larger university, specific program staff likely small)","estimated_budget":"Not publicly available in search results.","mission_focus":"Conducts research on oceanographic conditions in Kachemak Bay, focusing on climate change impacts (warming waters, glacial melt, ocean acidification) on marine ecosystems. Involved in the System-Wide Monitoring Program for estuarine ecosystems. [cite: 38 (previous search)]","why_fit":"Directly addresses critical ''ocean health'' issues like climate change and ocean acidification, which are inherently ''cross-sector complexity'' problems. The need to understand and communicate the impacts of these changes on marine life and fisheries presents leadership challenges in research strategy and public engagement, aligning with Leslie''s problem-solving skills. [cite: 38 (previous search)]","keyword_category":"sci","signal_strength":"supplemental","leadership_signal_tier":"inferred","leadership_signal_evidence":"Research focus on ''changes in ocean circulation have large impacts on global climate and marine ecosystems'' and ''a myriad of issues from warming waters... and ocean acidification'' implies ongoing complex scientific and communication challenges requiring strategic direction. [cite: 38 (previous search)]","lat":61.2181,"lng":-149.9003,"contact_name":"Not found directly for Oceanography program lead in search results.","contact_email":"accs@uaa.alaska.edu","contact_position":"General ACCS contact","contact_linkedin":"Not publicly available in search results.","contact_bio":"Not available.","review_status":"Lead for Review","host_producer_notes":"Academic research with a clear focus on ocean health and climate change impacts. Might be a good fit for an EiR focused on scientific communication, stakeholder engagement, or strategic research planning.","budget_tier":"small"}]',11,0,'2026-03-26 06:50:45');
